label: fertilization defective
description: Any perturbation that disrupts the fusion of male and female gametes (sperm and oocyte) during sexual reproduction.

label: reproductive system physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the reproductive system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: intestinal microvilli variant
description: Any variation in the formation of intestinal microvilli. Microvilli are actin-based cellular structures that form plasma membrane projections into the extracellular space and whose specialized shape provides increased cellular surface area. Microvilli are a crucial component of the terminal differentiation process for many epithelial cell types, usually ones that play an absorptive or filtering role.

label: intestinal cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of an intestinal cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: response to multiple stressors variant
description: Any variation in an animal's response to exposure to multiple stressors occuring simultaneously or during an overlapping temporal window compared to control.

label: organism environmental stimulus response variant
description: The response to a change in the environment is altered compared to control.

label: posterior pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency of the posterior body axis compared to control.

label: body axis pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency along a particular body axis compared to control.

label: acetylcholinesterase inhibitor hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to an acetylcholinesterase inhibitor at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: acetylcholinesterase inhibitor response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific acetylcholinesterase inhibitor compared to that observed in control animals.

label: drug hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to a specific drug at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: spermatocyte meiosis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the meiotic divisions undergone by the primary and secondary spermatocytes to produce haploid spermatids (non-motile sperm) compared to control.

label: spermatogenesis variant
description: Any variation in the processes that influence the generation and maturation of spermatozoa (motile sperm) compared to control.

label: spermatid maturation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the ability of a relatively unspecialized spermatocyte to acquire the properties of a spermatid cell compared to control.

label: endoreduplication variant
description: Any variation in the multiple rounds of DNA replication that take place without chromosome condensation, segregation or cytokinesis compared to control. In C. elegans this process is normally seen in intestinal nuclei during each larval lethargus which results in adult intestinal nuclei with 32 copies (32C) of each chromosome(Wormatlas).

label: DNA metabolism variant
description: Variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of DNA in the organism compared to control.

label: germ cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the germ cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to cues, compared to control animals.

label: cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell, in any physical or chemical process required for the cell to carry out its normal functions or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: energy expenditure variant
description: Variations in the amount of energy consumed by an organism compared to control. Energy expenditure is often determined by assaying oxygen consumption.

label: organism metabolism processing variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform chemical substances compared to control.

label: mRNA splicing variant
description: Variations in the processes regulating the excision of intervening introns from the primary mRNA transcript, compared to control.

label: RNA processing variant
description: Variations in the processes involved in the conversion of one or more primary RNA transcripts into one or more mature RNA molecules compared to control.

label: nuclear division variant
description: Any variation in the process by which a cell nucleus is divided into two nuclei, with DNA and other nuclear contents distributed between the daughter nuclei, compared to control.

label: gland cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the gland cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to signals, compared to control animals.

label: membrane trafficking variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of substances in a cell, from one side of a membrane to another, compared to control.

label: blast cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the blast cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to cues, compared to control animals.

label: left handed roller
description: The body of the animal rotates around its long axis as the animal moves, causing the animal to move in a circular pattern in the left-handed direction. In liquid media, wave propogation is helical rather than planar.

label: roller
description: The body of the animal rotates around its long axis as the animal moves, causing the animal to move in a circular pattern. In liquid media, wave propogation is helical rather than planar.

label: right handed roller
description: The body of the animal rotates around its long axis as the animal moves, causing the animal to move in a circular pattern in the right-handed direction. In liquid media, wave propogation is helical rather than planar.

label: epithelial cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the epithelial cell to carry out its normal functions or activities, compared to control animals.

label: nuclear pore variant
description: Any variation that disrupts the assembly, distribution, localization or organization of any of the numerous similar discrete openings in the nuclear envelope, where the inner and outer nuclear membranes are joined.

label: nuclear envelope organization variant
description: The appearance and association of components along the double lipid bilayer enclosing the nucleus differs from controls. The NE separates nuclear contents from the rest of the cytoplasm and includes the intermembrane space, perinuclear space.

label: acetylcholine levels variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of acetylcholine compared to control animals at a defined stage. Acetylcholine is the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline.

label: phorbol ester resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of phorbol esters that elicit a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. Phorbol esters such as PMA act as DAG mimetics.

label: drug resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of a drug that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. Animals are not affected by exposure to the drug.

label: drug induced gene expression variant
description: Gene expression of an animal is not influenced by drug treatment in the same manner as control animals.

label: gene expression variant
description: Variations in the processes that convert a gene's coding sequence into a mature gene product or products (proteins or RNA), compared to control.

label: nonsense mRNA accumulation
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the regulated breakdown of mRNA transcripts in which an amino-acid codon has changed to a premature stop codon and the 3 prime end is not protected by a poly(A) tail.

label: diet induced life span variant
description: Life span of the animal is not influenced by changes in diet in the same manner as control animals.

label: life span variant
description: Adult life span is either longer or shorter than typical of control animals.

label: male ray morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan compared to control animals. In C. elegans, nine bilateral rays project from the tail in a radial pattern with a smooth and slightly tapered appearance. Although one neuronal member of each ray sensillum is exposed to the outside, male rays rarely take up dye.

label: male nervous system morphology variant
description: Male animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any component that is part of the complement of organ tissues that serve to detect, relay and coordinate information about an animal's internal and external environments and to initiate and integrate its effector responses and activities, compared to that in control animals.

label: sensillum morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the sense organs comprised of ciliated sensory nerve endings enveloped by sheath and/or socket cells, from that observed in control animals.

label: marginal cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit deviations at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell, in any physical or chemical process required for a marginal cell to carry out its normal function and activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli.

label: bursa swollen
description: The adult male tail, including the lateral fan and rays, appears bloated or distended.

label: bursa morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the adult male tail including the lateral fan and rays compared to control.

label: eggshell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of the protective barrier which isolates the embryo from the external environment, compared to control .

label: egg morphology variant
description: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of fertilized oocytes that are laid compared to those laid by control animals.

label: sperm pseudopod variant
description: Variation in the morphological appearance or composition of the pseudopod, a cellular projection that facilitates motility of the spermatozoa.

label: sperm morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the mature male gamete, which merges with an oocyte to create a fertilized embryo copared to control (Wormatlas).

label: muscle cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the muscle cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: neuron physiology variant
description: Activity of the neuron varies from that observed for control animals or neurons. In C. elegans neuron activity is often assayed by observing calcium spikes.

label: intestinal contractions variant
description: Any variations in the contraction of the enteric muscles that are involved in defecation motor program compared to control.

label: defecation contraction variant
description: Any variation in the stereotyped muscle contractions that result in defecation compared to control . In C. elegans these contractions include posterior body contraction (pBoc), anterior body contraction (aBoc), expulsion of gut contents by enteric muscle contraction (Emc) and opening of anus (Exp).

label: vulval invagination variant L4
description: The characteristic Christmas-tree shaped invagination formed by the terminal vulval cells at the mid-late L4 stage is altered.

label: vulva morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the gross structure or organization of the reproductive organ required for depositing eggs and for influencing male mating behavior compared to control.

label: vulva development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the egg-laying organ of female and hermaphrodite nematodes over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control. In nematodes, the vulva is formed from ventral epidermal cells during larval stages to give rise to a fully formed vulva in the adult.

label: drug withdrawal response variant
description: Any variation in the state or activity of an organism as a result of abrupt discontinuation or decreased dosage of a drug, compared to control.

label: drug response variant
description: Any variation in the characteristic response(s) to drug(s) as defined by control animals.

label: second messenger mediated signaling variant
description: Any variation in a series of molecular signals that help relay a receptor mediated signal within the cell, compared to control. Second messengers often comprise of ions (eg: Ca2+) or small molecules (cGMP, cAMP etc) that are formed or released into the cytosol.

label: metabolic pathway variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in processes that are responsible for chemical changes compared to control animals. Metabolic processes typically transform small molecules, but also include macromolecular processes such as DNA repair and replication, and protein synthesis and degradation.

label: nuclear positioning variant
description: Variations in the directed movement of the nucleus to a specific location within a cell compared to control.

label: organelle organization biogenesis variant
description: Intracellular membrane bound compartments vary in shape or size from that observed in control animals.

label: response to injury variant
description: Variations in the processes that restore integrity to a damaged tissue following an injury, compared to control.

label: cell stress response variant
description: Variations in the activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress, compared to control. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

label: high sodium chloride concentration osmotic avoidance defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to high concentrations of sodium chloride solution. C. elegans typically avoids high concentrations of sodium chloride solution.

label: high sodium chloride concentration osmotic avoidance variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their avoidance response to high concentrations of sodium chloride solution compared to control.

label: anal depressor contraction defect
description: Animals fail to contract the anal depressor muscle.

label: larval defecation defect
description: Animals fail to expel fecal matter during the larval stage.

label: rubber band
description: When prodded on the head, worm contracts and then relaxes along its entire body without moving backwards, compared to a control worm which contracts its anterior end and backs away in response to prodding.

label: mechanosensation variant
description: Any variation with respect to perception or response to mechanical stimuli compared to control animals.

label: thermophilic
description: Animals tend to track and stay within high temperature environments.

label: isothermal tracking behavior variant
description: Variations in the ability of an animal to remain within a defined temperature. In C. elegans, animals tend to track and stay within a temperature that is most closely related to their cultivation temperature.

label: phagosome maturation defective
description: Early phagosomes fail to undergo the maturation process following the ingestion of particulate material by phagocytosis; During maturation, phagosomes acquire markers of late endosomes and lysosomes.

label: engulfment variant
description: Any variation in the removal of a cell corpse, by a neighboring cell or a phagocyte compared to control.

label: lipid modification variant
description: Variations in the covalent alteration of one or more components (eg: fatty acids, sterols etc.) in a lipid, resulting in a change in the properties of the lipid, compared to control.

label: lipid metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of an internal store of lipid within the organism or cell compared to control.

label: ventral nerve cord development variant
description: Variations in any process whose specific outcome is the development and/or maintenance of the ventral nerve cord.

label: neuropil development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a dense feltwork of interwoven cytoplasmic processes of nerve cells (dendrites and axons) and support cells, over time from an initial condition to a later condition, compared to control.

label: athermotactic
description: The responses of an animal towards temperature are not influenced by its cultivation temperature.

label: lipid hydrolysis regulation variant
description: Variations in the process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipids, compared to control.

label: VNC nuclear positioning variant
description: Variations in spacing or location were observed between adjacent ventral cord nuclei or between ventral cord nuclei and another nucleus used as a reference point. In C. elegans, these nuclei are distributed equally and predictably, such that they can be unambiguously distinguished by their position.

label: expulsion defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the expulsion of gut contents. In C. elegans, this refers to the final step of the defecation cycle in which the intestinal muscle and anal depressor contractions further pressurize intestinal contents and open the anus to permit expulsion.

label: expulsion variant
description: Any variation in the expulsion of gut contents compared to control. In C. elegans, this refers to the final step of the defecation cycle in which the intestinal muscle and anal depressor contractions further pressurize intestinal contents and open the anus to permit expulsion.

label: cryophilic
description: Animals tend to track and stay within low temperature environments.

label: hormone metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the degradation, biosynthesis or accumulation of hormones within the organism compared to control. Hormones are naturally occurring substances secreted by specialized cells that affect the metabolism or behavior of other cells possessing functional receptors for the hormone.

label: development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: Variant
description: Animals exhibit variations compared to a given control.

label: zinc homeostasis variant
description: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of zinc ions within an organism compared to control.

label: metal homeostasis variant
description: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of metal ions within an organism compared to control.

label: physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the cell, tissue, organ system or organism to carry out its normal functions and activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli compared to control animals.

label: tube morphogenesis variant
description: Variations in the process by which the anatomical structures of a tube are generated and organized, compared to control. Morphogenesis pertains to the creation of form or shape.

label: organ system development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of an organismal system from its formation to the mature structure when compared to control animals.

label: ventral cord disorganized
description: The longitudinal nerve cord of the midbody region, connecting the nerve ring and tail ganglia, is not arranged in the same manner as control animals.

label: ventral cord patterning variant
description: Any variation in the developmental process that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces within the ventral cord to which cells respond and eventually are instructed to differentiate compared to control.

label: behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: sterol induced dauer formation variant
description: Variations in the processes that facilitate/permit dauer entry when exposed to specific sterol molecules, compared to control.

label: dauer induction variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the entry into the dauer stage when exposed to conditions that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: embryonic cell fate specification variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern acquisition of particular cell fates in the embryo, from the time of zygote formation until hatching compared to control.

label: cell fate specification variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern acquisition of particular cell fates compared to control animals.

label: embryonic development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an embryo over time, from zygote formation to hatching compared to control.

label: embryonic somatic cell fate specification variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern acquisition of somatic cell fates in the embryo, from the time of zygote formation until hatching compared to control.

label: odorant imprinting variant
description: Any variation in a learned olfactory response whereby exposure of animals to odorants during specific developmental times or physiological states results in a lasting memory compared to control. In control animals, this imprinting determines the animal's behavior upon encountering the same odorant at a later time.

label: odorant chemosensory response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the chemosensory response to volatile organic compounds compared to control.

label: pattern of transgene expression variant
description: Any variation in the cellular or subcellular pattern of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: transgene expression variant
description: Any variation in the characteristic expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to control animals.

label: level of transgene expression variant
description: Any variation in the measured expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: ventral ganglion development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion which lies ventrally beside the nerve ring in the head, just anterior of the retrovesicular ganglion over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: ganglion development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a cluster of neuron cell bodies (somata) over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control.

label: somatic cell death variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the programmed cell death pathway that is triggered in cells other than germ cells and that is not subject to upstream checkpoint regulation.

label: programmed cell death variant
description: Developmentally regulated termination of a cell or cell group does not occur as in control animals.

label: synapsis defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the stabilization of homologue pairing, which occurs through the initiation and formation of the synaptonemal complex, during meiosis.

label: meiotic chromosome organization variant
description: Any variation in the process of chromosome organization that is involved in meiosis, compared to control.

label: embryonic rupture
description: During development of the embryo, the epidermis loses integrity and the contents of the embryo are expelled.

label: germline mortal
description: Progressive decrease in brood size culminating, over generations, in the loss of reproductive ability and thus becoming effectively sterile.

label: serotonin induced fat reduction variant
description: Animals retain a significantly greater proportion of their fat upon serotonin treatment, compared to control.

label: serotonin resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of serotonin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: serotonin response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of serotonin compared to that observed in control animals. Serotonin is a monoamine neurotransmitter.

label: male pigmentation variant
description: Males exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of the organism compared to control animals.

label: organism pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of the organism.

label: DMPP resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of DMPP that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: DMPP response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to DMPP compared to that observed in control animals.

label: oocyte septum formation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the partitioning of oocytes from each other compared to control animals.

label: somatic gonad development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the components of the gonad that are separate from the germline proper over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: accessory cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure, organization or placement of the cells that support sensory neurons, compared to that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, this category collectively refers to socket cells, sheath cells, and structural cells, or their processes.

label: nervous system morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any component that is part of the complement of organ tissues that serve to detect, relay and coordinate information about an animal's internal and external environments and to initiate and integrate its effector responses and activities, compared to that in control animals.

label: enhanced taste aversion defective
description: The conditioned aversion to a specific chemical compound as a result of that compound being coupled with an unfavorable condition, such as starvation, does not increase to the same extent as observed for control animals.

label: organism starvation response variant
description: Any variation in the state or activity of an organism as a result of deprivation of nourishment, compared to control.

label: aqueous adaptation defective
description: Animals do not exhibit characteristic desensitization to a water-soluble chemo-attractive signal in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control.

label: egg laying circuit variant
description: Neuromuscular signaling between neurons and egg laying musculature varies from that observed for control animals.

label: hermaphrodite physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required to carry out hermaphrodite-specific activities or to be able to perceive and respond to hermaphrodite-specific stimuli compared to control.

label: desynapsis defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the asymmetric diassembly of the synaptonemal complex during progression through meiosis.

label: tail spike variant
description: Any variation in the structure or appearance of the thin cuticle specialization found at the extreme posterior end of the tail compared to control.

label: tail morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of the most posterior region of the body compared to control. The anterior bound of the tail is not well defined though it might range from the position of the post-deirids to the opening of the anus (Wormatlas).

label: crossover defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the number or extent of connections between chromatids that occur during the process of genetic material exchange between homologous segments of non-sister chromatids.

label: pathogen load variant
description: The number of pathogens associated with the animal vary from that associated with control animals.

label: organism pathogen response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to disease causing agents, compared to control. Pathogen response includes prevention, damage control and recovery from the infection caused by the attack.

label: neuron activation variant
description: Activity of the neuron varies from that observed for control animals or neurons. In C. elegans neuron activity is often assayed by observing calcium spikes.

label: neuronal sheath cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the glia-like support cell of neuronal sensilla that ensheathes the dendrite tips and or processes of neurons, from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, sheath cells have highly invaginated and vesiculated surfaces, which provide a specialized environment for dendritic structures.

label: bordering
description: Animals tend to accumulate at the thickest part of the bacterial lawn.

label: foraging behavior variant
description: Variations in the behavior by which an organism locates food compared to control animals. In C. elegans roaming or dwelling activity on food are two examples of parameters used to assess this behavior. Roaming is defined as moving in a high-speed forward direction with brief backward movement, often traversing wide regions. Dwelling is defined as low-speed/high turning movement restricted to a confined region.

label: social behavior variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in actions and responses that occurs predominantly, or only, in individuals that are part of a group, from that observed for animals in a control group.

label: homologous recombination increased
description: Animals exhibit an increased frequency of exchange of genetic material between non-sister chromatids of a pair of homologues.

label: DNA recombination variant
description: Variations in the process by which a new genotype is formed by reassortment of genes resulting in gene combinations different from those that were present in the parents, compared to control.

label: embryonic pigmentation variant
description: Embryos exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter its transparency/translucency compared to control animals .

label: developmental pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of a particular developmental stage of the amimal compared to control animals.

label: anterior pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of the anterior body axis compared to control.

label: meiotic progression prophase variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any process necessary for the progression through prophase during meiosis compared to control animals.

label: meiotic progression during oogenesis variant
description: Developing oocytes show defects in their initial entry or progression through the meiotic pathway (such as failure to exit diakinesis).

label: meiosis variant
description: Variations in the specialized nuclear and cytoplasmic divisions of a single diploid cell, whose specific outcome is the formation of four haploid daughter cells compared to control. Meiosis occurs during the formation of gametes.

label: sperm recruitment variant
description: Any variation in the mechanism by which sperm find their correct target destinations (spermatheca).

label: oocyte physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the oocyte to carry out its normal functions or activities, compared to control animals.

label: somatic gonad morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the components of the gonad that are separate from the germline proper compared to control animals.

label: gonad morphology variant
description: Variations in the form or composition of a specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces the male or female gametes compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: dauer pheromone secretion variant
description: Animals produce pheromone but it does not undergo controlled release into the environment.

label: cell secretion variant
description: Variations in the regulated release of substances by a cell compared to control.

label: excretory secretory system physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the excretory/secretory system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: accessory cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required by a subset of interfacial cells to carry out its normal function or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control. It can refer to socket cells, sheath cells and structural cells or their processes (Wormatlas).

label: nervous system physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the nervous system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: neuronal sheath cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for a neuronal sheath cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: non bordering
description: Animals do not accumulate at the thickest part of the bacterial lawn. Animals do not preferentially deplete bacterial food at the thicker parts of the lawn.

label: RNAi persistence variant
description: Variations in the persistence of an RNAi induced phenotype compared to control.

label: RNAi response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to gene silencing triggered by double stranded RNA (RNAi), compared to control.

label: RNA metabolism variant
description: Variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of RNA in the organism compared to control.

label: cell homeostasis metabolism variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways involved in the maintenance of a steady-state at the level of the cell compared to control.

label: RNA degradation variant
description: Variations in the regulated breakdown of RNA species via the action of cellular enzymes (RNases) compared to control.

label: spermatheca physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the spermatheca to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: somatic gonad physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the somatic gonad to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: spermatheca dilation defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in any physical or chemical process involved in the dilation of the distal spermatheca which is required for the oocyte exit from the gonad arm.

label: rudimentary gonad
description: Animals have very few or no germline nuclei and gonad arms that are very small or missing.

label: premature spermatid activation
description: Any variation that results in the premature differentiation of spermatids into motile spermatozoa compared to control.

label: pharyngeal contraction variant
description: Any variation in the muscle contractions that control feeding compared to control. Contractions are necessary for bacterial uptake from the surrounding environment.

label: pharyngeal pumping variant
description: Any variation in the contraction and relaxation movements of the pharyngeal muscle that mediate feeding in nematodes compared to control.

label: male P lineages variant
description: The descendants of any of the P precursor cells (P1-P12) in male animals exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: male specific lineage variant
description: The descendants of a male specific precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: nervous system development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of nervous tissue over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: neurite development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a neuronal extension (such as axons or dendrites) over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control.

label: neuron development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a neuron over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: male M lineage variant
description: The descendants of the M precursor cell in male animals, exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: accessory cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of an accessory cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control. An accessory cell supports sensory neurons.

label: connective tissue morphology variant
description: Variations in the form, structure or composition of the material made up of fibers forming a framework and support structure for body tissues and organs compared to control.

label: pericellular component morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of pericellular components compared to control animals.

label: cuticle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the appearance or structure of the rigid external coating which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: pharyngeal nervous system development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the pharyngeal nervous system over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals. The nervous system is involved in the coordination and control of bodily activities and the interpretation of information from the senses.

label: pseudocoelom morphology variant
description: Any variation in the appearance of the body cavity compared to control. In C. elegans , an aberrancy in the psedocoelom can involve an accumulation of fluids or fluorescent reporters.

label: neuronal sheath cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a neuronal sheath cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control. A neuronal sheath cell is a structural cell that forms a specialized environment surrounding the sensory endings of a neuron.

label: socket cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a socket cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: dorsorectal ganglia development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion which lies above and behind the rectum in the tail, in close continuity with the anal hypodermal ridge over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: body wall muscle relaxation defective
description: Animals fail to relax their body wall muscles to the same extent as muscles in control animals.

label: body behavior variant
description: Activity characteristic of the body is altered compared to control.

label: axodendritic polarity variant
description: Animals fail to establish or maintain characteristics that delineate the dendrite from the axon. The exclusion of presynaptic components from the dendrite is one indication of axodendritic polarity.

label: lateral ganglia development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the left and right lateral ganglia which lie beside the nerve ring in the head over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: antimicrobial gene expression variant
description: Changes in the levels of innate immune gene products in response to pathogen exposure are significantly different from that observed in control animals.

label: innate immune response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their defense responses that are mediated by germline encoded components that directly recognize components of potential pathogens.

label: anterior ganglion development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a cluster of neuron somata located close to the nerve ring over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: dorsal ganglion development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion that lies dorsally beside the nerve ring in the head over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control. In C. elegans, It contains neuron cell bodies that send their neuronal processes into the ring and longitudinal nerves, but form no local neuropil separate from the nerve ring. The dorsal ganglion is in close contact with the dorsal hypodermal cord (Wormatlas).

label: preanal ganglion development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion which lies at the posterior limit of the ventral nerve cord in the tail over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: protein stabilization variant
description: Any variation in the ability of a protein to resist disintegration via chemical or physical modifications compared to control.

label: protein metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of proteins in the organism compared to control.

label: mitochondria vesiculated
description: Inner membrane of mitochondria are disconnected and form vesicular bodies.

label: mitochondria morphology variant
description: The morphological appearance of mitochondria is varied compared to control animals.

label: retrovesicular ganglion development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the ganglion which lies at the anterior limit of the ventral nerve cord, near the ventral ganglion and nerve ring in the head posterior to the excretory pore over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: fat associated bodies reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the number of fat containing organelles compared to control. In C. elegans this number can be assayed by decreases in the number of Nile Red or BODIPY 493/503 staining bodies.

label: fat associated bodies variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the formation or disassembly of fat containing organelles compared to control.

label: lumbar ganglia development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the left and right lumbar ganglia which lie behind the pre-anal ganglion in the tail, in lateral positions over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: posterior lateral ganglion development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the neuron somata associated with the post-deirid over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: endosome biogenesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the formation or disassembly of membrane bound organelles that traffic material between the plasma membrane and internal compartments of the cell, compared to control.

label: organelle fusion defective
description: The formation of mature intracellular compartments via membrane fusion is disrupted.

label: cell corpse digestion variant
description: The degradation of genomic and or cellular material of the corpse does not occur at the same rate or under the same conditions as observed in control animals undergoing cell death.

label: alternative splicing variant
description: Any variation in the process of generating multiple mRNA molecules from a given set of exons by differential use of exons from the primary transcript(s) to form multiple mature mRNAs that vary in their exon composition compared to control.

label: striated muscle development variant
description: Variations in the progression of muscle cells that contain fibers that are divided by transverse bands into striations, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: muscle system development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the muscle system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: male longitudinal muscle development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of somatic (striated) muscles that run longitudinally in males over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control. In C. elegans males have 3 additional sets of sex-specific longitudinal muscles (anterior and posterior outer, anterior and posterior inner, and caudal) that contribute to the body wall musculature (Wormatlas).

label: sex muscle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the sex muscles compared to control animals.

label: nonstriated muscle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the nonstriated muscle compared to control animals.

label: body wall muscle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the body wall muscle compared to control animals.

label: striated muscle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the striated muscle compared to control animals.

label: muscle system morphology variant
description: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the muscle system, compared to control. The muscle system consists of tissues made up of various elongated cells that are specialized to contract and produce movement and mechanical work.

label: sexually dimorphic physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required to carry out sex-specific activities or to be able to perceive and respond to sex-specific stimuli compared to control.

label: male longitudinal muscle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the male longitudinal muscle compared to control animals.

label: male physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required to carry out male-specific activities or to be able to perceive and respond to male-specific stimuli compared to control.

label: bis phenol A hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to bis phenol A at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure time compared to control animals.

label: bis phenol A response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to bis phenol A compared to that observed in control animals.

label: MS lineage variant
description: The descendants of the MS blastomere exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: embryonic cell lineage variant
description: The descendants of an embryonic precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: sexually dimorphic development variant
description: Variations in the progression of morphogenic processes required for formation or proper placement of sex-specific structures that distinguish the animal as one sex or the other in the population, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: organism development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a worm at any time from its fertilization to adulthood compared to control.

label: chemical response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific chemical compared to that observed in control animals.

label: P4 lineage variant
description: The descendants of the P4 blastomere exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: W lineage variant
description: The descendants of the W precursor cell exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: postembryonic cell lineage variant
description: The descendants of a postembryonic precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: developmental morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts during a given developmental stage compared to control animals.

label: organism morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any part of their anatomy compared to control animals.

label: D lineage variant
description: The descendants of the D blastomere exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: male V lineages variant
description: The descendants of any of the V precursor cells (V1-V6) in male animals, exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: male T lineages variant
description: The descendants of TL or TR cells in male animals exhibit any variation in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: gut granule development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the different inclusions within the intestinal cytoplasm, including birefringent crystalline objects and other dark-staining endosomes over time compared to control. In C. elegans these contents might include glycogen granules (polysaccharide storage), rhabditin (carbohydrate storage), yolk granules (lipid and protein), and concentrated waste products (Wormatlas).

label: ammonium chloride chemotaxis defective
description: Failure in directed movement in response to ammonium chloride compared to control. In C. elegans, NH4Cl is an attractant. NH4Cl has also subsequently been used to assay for Cl- attraction in C. elegans.

label: ammonium chloride chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of ammonium chloride. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, ammonium chloride is an attractant. NH4Cl has also been used to assay for Cl- attraction.

label: aqueous positive chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to move towards attractive water-soluble chemicals.

label: chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific chemical concentration gradient compared to control. Directed movement may be towards a higher concentration (positive chemotaxis) or towards a lower concentration (negative chemotaxis).

label: chemosensory response variant
description: Variations in the state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a chemical stimulus, compared to control.

label: cell polarity variant
description: Contents or structures of a cell are no longer restricted/localized to their typical positions within the cell.

label: cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a cell from when it is first formed to when it becomes a mature structure when compared to control animals.

label: precocious cell fusion
description: Two or more individual cells form a syncytium (a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane) via the fusion of the plasma membranes at an earlier stage of development compared to comparable cells in control animals.

label: precocious heterochronic variations
description: Variations that result in the acceleration of the rate, frequency or extent of the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition, compared to control.

label: cell fusion variant
description: Variations in the ability of two or more individual cells to form a syncytium (a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane) via the fusion of the plasma membranes. Cell fusion is dependent on the merging of lipid bilayer membranes as well as cytoplasmic mixing.

label: UV induced apoptosis increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to the nucleic acid damaging agent, UV irradiation, compared to control.

label: apoptosis increased
description: Any perturbation that causes an elevation in the frequency of cell death by apoptosis compared to control animals.

label: cell UV response variant
description: Cells exhibit variations in their response to ultraviolet radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: bleach hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to bleach at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: bleach response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to bleach compared to that observed in control animals.

label: presynaptic vesicle cluster variant
description: Animals display variations in the organization, accumulation or distribution of transmitter-containing membrane-bound organelles (synaptic vesicles) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: presynaptic region morphology variant
description: Animals display variations in the structure, configuration, distribution or ratio of the components of the vesicle-filled varicosities of the synapse compared to control.

label: over retracted male tail
description: Adult males exhibit a truncated tail, often without a fan or have well-developed fans but squarish, truncated back ends compared to control. In C. elegans this is due to precocious male tail tip retraction beginning in the early L3 stage (normally retraction begins in the L4 stage). Condition can be lethal if the function of the anus is affected.

label: male tail morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the somatic reproductive components of the posterior segment of the male from that observed in control males. In C. elegans, this region of the male includes the terminal canals of the reproductive tract, the digestive tract, and spicule channels along with the male specific sensilla (ray, post-cloacal, hook and spicule) and extends to the tip of the acellular fan.

label: male tail development variant
description: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the male tail over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control.

label: inhibition of ovulation variant
description: Any variation that alters the control mechanisms that inhibit oocyte maturation and release of a mature oocyte into the spermatheca (for subsequent fertilization), compared to control.

label: ovulation variant
description: Any variation that disrupts the release of a mature oocyte into the spermatheca (for subsequent fertilization), compared to control.

label: anion positive chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to move towards attractive anions.

label: anion positive chemotaxis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic movement towards typically attractive anions compared to control.

label: odorant positive chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to move towards attractive volatile organic molecules. In C. elegans, these compounds are sensed by the AWA and AWC neurons.

label: positive chemotaxis defective
description: Variations in the movement towards typically attractive chemicals.

label: odorant positive chemotaxis variant
description: Movement towards typically attractive volatile organic chemicals is altered as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, these odorants are typically sensed by the AWA and AWC neurons.

label: octanol chemotaxis hypersensitive
description: Animals execute a response, via directed movement to octanol at a lower concentration or shorter exposure time compared to control. In C. elegans, animals avoid octanol.

label: octanol chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of octanol. In C. elegans, octanol is typically a repellant.

label: oocyte meiotic maturation variant
description: Variations in the progression of a developing oocyte, from diakinesis to metaphase (meiosis I), in response to a signal compared to control animals. Meiotic maturation is accompanied by nuclear envelope breakdown (germinal vesicle breakdown), cytoskeletal rearrangement and meiotic spindle assembly.

label: inhibition of oocyte maturation variant
description: Variations in the processes that negatively regulate the meiotic progression of oocytes (exit from diakinesis) in the absence of a signal compared to control animals.

label: nose touch hypersensitive
description: Animals tend to initiate a response more often, compared to control, after nose-on collisions with an object. In C. elegans, animals initiate backwards movement in response to nose touch.

label: nose touch variant
description: Variations in the ability of an animal to respond with characteristic backward movement after a nose-on collision with an object compared to control. In C. elegans, this phenotype is usually assayed via stroking with a hair or similar fiber on the anterior most tip of the animal.

label: cell corpse number variant
description: Animals exhibit differences in the number of cell corpses compared to controls at the same developmental life stage.

label: apoptosis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any processes that influence the programmed cell death pathway. Induction of the apoptotic pathway triggers the activity of proteolytic caspases, which in turn lead to the destruction of the cell.

label: metal response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific metal compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cell migration variant
description: Any variation in the orderly movement of a cell from one site to another.

label: sodium acetate chemotaxis defective
description: Failure in directed movement in response to sodium acetate. In C. elegans, sodium acetate is an attractant. Sodium acetate has also subsequently been used to assay for Na+ attraction in C. elegans.

label: sodium acetate chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of sodium acetate. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, sodium acetate is an attractant. Sodium acetate has also been used to assay for Na+ attraction.

label: aqueous positive chemotaxis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the movement towards typically attractive water-soluble chemicals compared to control.

label: head behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the head in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism segment behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of a certain body region of an animal in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: pattern of gene expression variant
description: Any variation in the cellular or subcellular distribution of a gene product compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cation positive chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to move towards attractive cations.

label: cation positive chemotaxis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic movement towards typically attractive cations compared to control.

label: copper response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to copper compared to that observed in control animals.

label: copper hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to copper at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: alimentary system morphology variant
description: Variations in the form, structure or composition of the series of related tissues lying within the body cavity and devoted to feeding and digestion compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: organ system morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any component that is part of the complement of organ tissues that comprise a specific organ system.

label: mRNA expression variant
description: Variations in the biogenesis and stability of messenger RNA molecules compared to control.

label: RNA expression variant
description: Variations in the biogenesis and stability of any class of RNA molecules (rRNAs, miRNAs, tRNAs etc) compared to control.

label: sodium chloride adaptation defective
description: Animals do not exhibit characteristic chemoattractive desensitization to sodium chloride in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control.

label: sodium acetate adaptation defective
description: Animals do not exhibit characteristic chemoattractive desensitization to sodium acetate in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control.

label: coelomic system morphology variant
description: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the coelomic system, compared to control. The coelom is the fluid compartment that is in contact with internal organ.

label: anterior pharynx variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the anterior portion of the pharynx over time compared to control. In C. elegans the anterior region includes the corpus (procorpus and metacorpus - first bulb).

label: pharyngeal development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the pharynx (feeding organ) over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control. In C. elegans the pharynx is divided into the anterior and posterior regions. The anterior region includes the corpus (procorpus and metacorpus - first bulb) and the posterior region includes the isthmus and terminal bulb (second bulb).

label: aqueous chemosensory response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in response to water-soluble chemicals, compared to control.

label: protein expression variant
description: Variations in the biogenesis and stability of protein molecules compared to control.

label: tail behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the tail in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: L2 lethal
description: L2 lethal: Animals die at the L2 stage of the life cycle.

label: early larval lethal
description: Animals die during early larval development. In C.elegans, this occurs during the L1- L2 larval stages of the life cycle.

label: mid larval lethal
description: Animals die in between the early and late larval stages. In C. elegans, this occurs during the L2- L3 larval stages of the life cycle.

label: aqueous negative chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to move away from repellent water soluble chemicals.

label: aqueous negative chemotaxis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations through directed movement, in response to repellant water soluble chemicals, compared to control.

label: protein expression increased
description: Any change that results in higher than normal levels of protein expression compared to control animals.

label: level of protein expression variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the measured expression of a protein compared to that observed in control animals.

label: odorant negative chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to move away from repellant volatile organic chemicals.

label: odorant negative chemotaxis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations through directed movement, in response to repellant volatile organic chemicals, compared to control.

label: larval lethal
description: The animal dies at any time between hatching and onset to adulthood.

label: L1 lethal
description: Animals die at the L1 stage of the life cycle.

label: ammonium chloride adaptation defective
description: Animals do not exhibit characteristic chemoattractive desensitization to ammonium chloride in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control.

label: translation variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a protein, compared to control.

label: coiling frequency increased
description: Animals spend more time with their body posture in a coil or they increase the frequency with which they form coils compared to control animals.

label: coiling frequency
description: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of time spent with its body posture in a coil or the frequency with which they form coils compared to control animals.

label: osmotic avoidance defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic avoidance response to solutions of high osmotic strength as defined by control animals.

label: post translational processing variant
description: Any variation in the posttranslational modification of a protein (which may include cleavage of peptide bonds) leading to the attainment of the full functional capacity of the protein compared to control.

label: garlic chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of garlic compared to control. In C. elegans, garlic is typically a repellant.

label: protein expression reduced
description: Any change that results in lower than normal levels of protein expression compared to control animals.

label: negative chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of an animal in response to chemical repellants as defined by control animals.

label: coiler
description: The body of an animal assumes a coil-like shape when it attempts to move.

label: locomotor coordination variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their ability to maintain characteristic and effective locomotion compared to control.

label: coiling variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the occurrence of a coil-like body posture compared to control animals. This includes the amount of time spent in a coil, the frequency with which coils form and the inappropriate formation of a coil, for example when attempting to locomote.

label: light response variant
description: Variations in the state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a light stimulus (electromagnetic radiation of wavelengths classified as infrared, visible or ultraviolet light) compared to control.

label: organism behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of an organism in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control organisms.

label: bacterially unswollen
description: Animals do not exhibit tail-swelling in response to infection by a bacterial pathogen (such as Microbacterium nematophilum) compared to control.

label: pathogen resistance increased
description: Animals are less prone to infection compared to control.

label: gamma ray induced apoptosis decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to the nucleic acid damaging agent, gamma irradiation, compared to control.

label: cell gamma ray response variant
description: Cells exhibit variations in their response to gamma ray radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: apoptosis reduced
description: Any perturbation that causes a decrease in the frequency of cell death by apoptosis compared to control animals.

label: alae morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the organization of the longitudinal ridges on the cuticle along the length of the animal, from that observed for control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: ventral coiler
description: A coiling body that bends ventrally.

label: parental chromosome mixing defective
description: Parental chromosomes fail to undergo appropriate mixing upon pronuclear fusion resulting in a zygotic nucleus in which parental genomes remain segregated.

label: nucleus defective early emb
description: Nucleus is abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: cuticle carbohydrate surface variant
description: Animals exhibit an altered display of glycosylated proteins or lipids or altered access to glycosylated moieties along their surface from that observed in control animals of the same developmental stage. In C. elegans, variations in surface accessible glycosylated species are often revealed by altered lectin-binding from that observed in control animals.

label: pericellular component physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process taking place in extracellular spaces within or associated with the organism, from that observed for control animals.

label: shrinker
description: The whole body undergoes longitudinal shortening in response to head touch or tail touch (Wormatlas).

label: spastic locomotion
description: Animals exhibit uncharacteristic muscle contractions during the process by which they travel from one location to another.

label: echo defecation cycle
description: Muscle contractions that make up the defecation motor program are repeated before the onset of the next cycle unlike in control animals.

label: defecation cycle variant
description: Any variation in the stereotyped sequence of muscle contractions that result in defecation over a fixed time period compared to control .

label: nuclear number variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the number of nuclei contained in a particular cell type compared to control.

label: protein expression absent
description: Animals fail to express a given protein or class of proteins.

label: axon varicosities
description: Animals display markedly swollen areas along their axons, which are larger than synaptic varicosities in control animals.

label: axon ultrastructure variant
description: Animals display variations in the structure or organization of the components of the axon, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism desiccation response variant
description: Any variation in the state or activity of an organism in response to extreme dryness or drought-like conditions, compared to control .

label: organism stress response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in response to stress stimuli compared to control animals.

label: pathogen adherence defect
description: Pathogens are unable to adhere/colonize the surface of host animals. This defect is often associated with changes in cuticle surface properties of the host.

label: pathogen adherence decreased
description: Pathogens exhibit decreased adherence to the surface of host animals.

label: pathogen adherence variant
description: Animals exhibit variations that result in variations in the ability of or extent to which pathogens adhere to the surface of animals, compared to control.

label: glutathione levels variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of glutathione compared to control animals at a defined stage. Glutathione, the tripeptide glutamylcysteinylglycine, acts as a coenzyme for some enzymes and as an antioxidant in the protection of sulfhydryl groups in enzymes and other proteins.

label: dorsal coiler
description: A coiling body that bends dorsally.

label: axon morphology variant
description: Animals display variations in the structure, organization of components, or spatial pattern of the projection that conducts signal away from the cell body, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: meiotic sister chromatid segregation variant
description: Variations in the process by which sister chromatids, identical chromosomes resulting from DNA replication, are physically separated during the meiotic cell cycle, compared to control.

label: meiotic chromosome segregation variant
description: Variations in the process by which genetic material, in the form of chromosomes, is organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets during the meiotic cell cycle, compared to control.

label: male mating defective
description: Males exhibit defects in the specific actions or reactions that are associated with reproduction.

label: male mating variant
description: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of the male that are associated with reproduction compared to control.

label: emetine hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to emetine at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: organism hypersensitive desiccation
description: Animals respond to less severe drought-like conditions or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: neuronal outgrowth variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern the extension of neuronal projections.

label: biofilm absent head
description: Animals can move thorough a lawn of bacterially produced biofilm without accumulating an enormous amount of biofilm on its nose. When C. elegans is exposed to certain bacteria (e.g., Y. pestis), a biofilm accumulates on a worm's head. The presence of this biofilm inhibits feeding by the worm, and thereby prevents growth.

label: axon cisternae
description: Axons of animals contain flattened membrane-bound compartments. In C. elegans, these cisternae-like structures are typically absent.

label: axon vesicle variant
description: Axons of animals exhibit variations in the gross structure or organization of its spherical, membrane-bound, fluid-filled organelles, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the organism to carry out its normal function or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli.

label: coelomocyte physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the coelomocyte to carry out its normal functions or activities, compared to control animals.

label: organism homeostasis metabolism variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways involved in the maintenance of a steady-state at the level of the organism compared to control.

label: endocytic transport defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in the directed movement of substances into, out of or mediated by the endosome, a membrane-bound organelle that trafficks material to different compartments of the cell or back to the plasma membrane for recycling.

label: endocytic transport variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the directed movement of substances into, out of or mediated by the endosome, a membrane-bound organelle that trafficks material to different compartments of the cell or back to the plasma membrane for recycling compared to control.

label: excretory canal short
description: The structure made by the processes of the excretory canal cell is reduced in size compared to control. In C. elegans this is an H-shaped structure which extends almost the full length of the body on both sides of the animal, generally in contact with the lateral hypodermis and the pseudocoelom (Wormatlas).

label: excretory canal morphology variant
description: Variations in the form or composition of structures made by the processes of the excretory canal cell compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: organ system physiology variant
