description: Animals exhibit variations in a physical or chemical process required for organs or tissues to carry out their normal functions or for their ability to perceive and respond to stimuli compared to control.

label: intestinal vacuole
description: Vacuoles accumulate in the intestine.

label: intestinal morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the chain of cuboidal cells which form a central lumen lined by microvilli that allow the passage of food, compared to control. Food passes from the posterior pharynx to the intestine where it is digested and then on to the rectum which processes the waste products for excretion (Wormatlas).

label: cytoplasmic appearance variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any cellular contents (excluding plasma membrane and nucleus), compared to control animals.

label: cell organization biogenesis variant
description: Variations in the process(es) involved in the assembly and arrangement of cell structures compared to control.

label: coelomocyte uptake defective
description: Fluid-phase endocytosis by coelomocytes is less frequent or efficient compared to control.

label: body axis development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a discrete axis of an animal's anatomy over time, compared to control animals.

label: body region development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the overall structure or appearance of a discrete region of an animal's anatomy over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: organism segment development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the overall structure or appearance of any anterior/posterior section of an animal's anatomy over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: receptor mediated endocytosis defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the cell-mediated uptake of external materials via receptor activity. Receptor-mediated endocytosis ensures specificity of transport and generally occurs via clathrin-coated pits and vesicles. In C. elegans, this is often judged by the lack of yolk uptake in oocytes.

label: granules cytoplasm
description: Animals accumulate an excess of vesicle-like structures in cells.

label: organism region behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of a certain defined body area of an animal in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: dumpy
description: Worms are shorter and stouter than control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: body width variant
description: Animals vary in the distance between dorsal and ventral sides when measured across the body at right angles to the length, from that observed in control animals.

label: body length variant
description: Animals vary in the distance between anterior and posterior ends of the animal from that observed in control animals.

label: pointed tail tip male
description: Male tails fail to undergo tip retraction thereby forming a 'leptoderan' or 'pointed' adult tail.

label: lysosome organization biogenesis variant
description: Variations in the processes that are carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a lysosome, compared to control.

label: synaptic transmission variant
description: Any variation in the process of communication across a synapse between a neuron and a target cell (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) compared to control animals.

label: transmission of nerve impulse variant
description: Transmission of the signal along the neuron varies from control.  This process includes the flow of information from the neuron cell body to the synapse and across to the postsynaptic cell.

label: body axis morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a discrete axis (dorsal/ventral/anterior/posterior/transverse) of their anatomy, compared to control animals.

label: body region morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a discrete region of their anatomy compared to control animals.

label: organism segment morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any anterior/posterior section of their anatomy compared to control animals.

label: forward kinker
description: Forward movement is often characterized by severe bending motions, more sharply angled and/or much deeper than stereotypical sinusoidal body bends of the control. Animal moves forward with uncharacteristic muscle spasms causing loss of smooth sinusoidal motion or body posture (Wormatlas).

label: kinker
description: The animal moves or rests with uncharacteristic muscle spasms causing loss of smooth sinusoidal motion or body posture. Movement is often characterized by severe bending motions, more sharply angled and/or much deeper than stereotypical sinusoidal body bends of the control animals.

label: anaphase bridging
description: Chromosomal masses fail to fully separate and remained linked during anaphase.

label: mitotic chromosome segregation variant
description: Any variation in the cell cycle process whereby replicated homologous chromosomes are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two sets during the mitotic cell cycle compared to control animals.

label: protein neddylation variant
description: Any variation in the conjugation of the ubiquitin-like protein Nedd8 to another protein compared to control.

label: protein modification variant
description: Variations in the covalent alteration of one or more amino acids occurring in proteins, peptides and nascent polypeptides (co-translational, post-translational modifications), compared to control. This includes the modification of charged tRNAs that are destined to occur in a protein (pre-translation modification).

label: backward kinker
description: Backward movement is often characterized by severe bending motions, more sharply angled and/or much deeper than stereotypical sinusoidal body bends of the control. Animal moves backward with uncharacteristic muscle spasms causing loss of smooth sinusoidal motion or body posture (Wormatlas).

label: meiotic spindle assembly defective
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the meiotic spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated and/or homologous chromosomes apart.

label: meiotic spindle defective
description: Cells undergoing meiosis exhibit defects in the overall function or activity of the meiotic spindle.

label: cord commissures fail to reach target
description: Axon tracts fail to complete the connection between nerve cords. In C. elegans, these tracts grow circumferentially around the animal, completing the connection between the ventral and dorsal nerve cords.

label: cord commissures variant
description: Variations in the structure, organization or path of axon tracts that grow circumferentially around the animal in a single, directed trajectory to bridge the ventral and dorsal cords, compared to control animals.

label: fat
description: Animals exhibit an increased girth compared to a control animal of the same developmental stage.

label: drug induced locomotion variant
description: Locomotion of the animal is not influenced by drug exposure in the same manner as control animals.

label: starved
description: Animals exhibit morphological characteristics that are the outcome of nutrient deprivation. In C. elegans, starved worms have fewer refractile granules in intestinal cells, making them appear pale. Strongly starved mutants are small and thin, and tend to retain fewer eggs than control animals.

label: hydroxyurea hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to hydroxyurea at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: hydroxyurea response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of hydroxyurea compared to that observed in control animals. Hydroxyurea stops DNA from being replicated.

label: muscle dystrophy
description: Progressive degeneration of muscle.

label: muscle system physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the muscle system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: nuclear membrane morphology variant
description: Any variation in the structure, form or composition of the membrane-bounded organelle of eukaryotic cells in which chromosomes are housed and replicated, compared to control.

label: egg retention
description: Eggs are retained in the uterus at a later stage when compared with control animals.

label: egg laying defective
description: Eggs are not laid, laid at a slower rate or eggs are laid at a later stage of development compared to control.

label: early eggs laid
description: Eggs are laid at an earlier stage of development when compared with control animals.

label: hyperactive egg laying
description: Eggs are laid at an earlier stage of development, eggs are laid in the presence of inhibitors of egg laying, or the inactive phase of the egg-laying cycle is significantly shorter when compared to control.

label: centriole biogenesis variant
description: Any variation in the formation or disassembly of the cylindrical structures that are composed of groupings of microtubules found close to the nucleus (centrioles) compared to control. Centrioles are arranged perpendicularly and are surrounded by an amorphous mass of dense material (the pericentriolar material). The centrioles and the pericentriolar material constitute the compound structure known as the centrosome.

label: centrosome biogenesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the formation, maturation or disassembly of the centrosome (a subcellular body consisting of two centrioles embedded in a protein matrix).  The centrosome serves as a microtubule organizing center as well as a regulator of cell-cycle progression.

label: head muscle dystrophy
description: Progressive degeneration of the head muscle.

label: head muscle behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the head muscles in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: body muscle dystrophy
description: Progressive degeneration of muscle along the body wall.

label: aneuploidy
description: Any variation in the number of chromosomes in a cell compared to control.

label: chromosome segregation variant
description: Any variation in the processes that regulate the apportionment of chromosomes to each of two daughter cells compared to control.

label: endoplasmic reticulum symmetry variant early emb
description: Any variation in the normally asymmetric distribution of the endoplasmic reticulum during cell divisions of the early embryo. The endoplasmic reticulum (ER) is an irregular network of membranes, that occurs in the cytoplasm, and forms a complex meshwork of tubular channels. The ER has two forms, rough (or granular), with ribosomes adhering to the outer surface, and smooth (with no ribosomes attached).

label: endoplasmic reticulum morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the endoplasmic reticulum compared to control. The endoplasmic reticulum (ER) is an irregular network of membranes, that occurs in the cytoplasm, and forms a complex meshwork of tubular channels. The ER has two forms, rough (or granular), with ribosomes adhering to the outer surface, and smooth (with no ribosomes attached).

label: omega turns variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the rate of sharp head to tail turns compared to control animals.

label: turning variant
description: Variations in the behavior by which an organism alters its trajectory of movement compared to control, excluding shifts from forward to backward movements (this is reversal).

label: cell component morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of the basic structural and functional components of cells compared to control. Includes the nucleus, endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus, mitochondria, endosomes, lysosomes, and peroxisomes as well as other vesicles and organelles.

label: hypoosmotic shock hypersensitive
description: Any variation in the ability to adjust to a decline in ambient solute concentrations, thereby causing the body to swell and explode.

label: osmotic integrity variant
description: Any variation in the process involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of water within an organism, compared to control.

label: cleavage furrow termination defective early emb
description: Embryos exhibit defects in the maintenance or termination of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate during cytokinesis.

label: cleavage furrow defective early emb
description: Embryos exhibit defects in the formation, maintenance or termination of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate during cytokinesis.

label: connected mitochondria
description: Mitochondria are interconnected by thin tubules of mitochondrial inner or outer membrane.

label: cleavage furrow initiation defective early emb
description: Embryos exhibit defects in the formation of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate at the onset of cytokinesis.

label: drug adaptation variant
description: Animals show variations in their decreased responsiveness after prolonged or repeated exposure to a drug compared to that in control.

label: GABA levels variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of GABA compared to control animals at a defined stage.

label: muscle birefringence variant
description: Animals exhibit a weak and abnormal birefringency pattern in muscle fibers when examined using polarized optics.

label: calcium channel modulator response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to specific calcium channel modulators compared to that observed in control animals.

label: calcium mediated signaling variant
description: Any variation in the series of molecular signals in which a cell or tissue uses calcium ions to convert a signal into a response, compared to control.

label: protein expression reduced male
description: Variations that result in a decrease in protein expression in male animals compared to that observed in control animals.

label: body wall muscle sarcomere morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the repeating units of a myofibrils in a muscle cell that are composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments, compared to control.

label: protein aggregation variant
description: Variations that result in the accumulation of soluble/insoluble protein aggregates in a particular cell or tissue, compared to control. Protein aggregates are often formed by interactions between misfolded protein molecules and/or deficiencies in proper protein folding.

label: protein protein interaction variant
description: Variations in the selective and non-covalent physical association between two or more proteins, compared to control.

label: calcium channel modulator hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to a calcium channel modulator at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: fat associated bodies increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the number of fat containing organelles compared to control. In C. elegans this number can be assayed by increases in the number of BODIPY 493/503 staining.

label: ectopic expression antibody
description: Any variation that results in the detection of protein expression in cells/tissues through antibody staining, that is otherwise not observed in control animals.

label: antibody staining variant
description: Any variation in the characteristic expression of a gene product, as detected by antibody staining, compared to control animals.

label: dopamine adaptation variant
description: Animals show variations in their decreased responsiveness after prolonged or repeated exposure to dopamine compared to that in control.

label: dopamine adaptation defective
description: Animals do not exhibit decreased responsiveness after prolonged or repeated exposure to dopamine.

label: excess seam cells
description: Animals execute supernumerary cell divisions during the development of the lateral, alae-producing epithelial cells, resulting in a larger number of these cells than control animals.

label: epithelial development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the epithelia over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control. This process involves autonomously generated changes in epidermal cell shape and position, and interactions with internal tissues, including the developing nervous system and body wall muscles to affect epidermal enclosure, cell intercalation, and epidermal elongation.

label: cell number increased
description: The number of cells in the organism is increased compared to control animals.

label: antibody subcellular localization variant
description: Any variation in the placement of a protein, as detected by antibody staining, within in a cell or cellular compartment compared to control.

label: protein expression ectopic
description: Any variation that results in the cellular expression of a protein in cells/tissues, that is otherwise not observed in control animals.

label: pattern protein expression variant
description: Any variation in the cellular or subcellular distribution of a protein compared to that observed in control animals.

label: protein expression reduced cell specific
description: Variations that result in a decrease in protein expression in specific cells compared to that observed in control animals.

label: head levamisole resistant
description: The heads of animals fail to respond to the concentration of levamisole that elicits a response in control animals. In C. elegans, heads contract at >10uM for intact animals and >1uM for cut animals.

label: levamisole resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of levamisole that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans resistance to levamisole is often assayed via body contraction response, ventral tail curling response etc.

label: mitochondrial membrane potential reduced
description: Any reduction in the membrane potential (voltage gradient) across the inner mitochondrial membrane compared to control.

label: mitochondrial metabolism variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways of the mitochondria compared to control.

label: glycogen levels variant
description: Any variation in the levels of the polymerized form of glucose throughout the body of the animal as compared to controls.

label: body levamisole resistant
description: The bodies of animals fail to respond to the concentration of levamisole that elicits a response in control animals.

label: M line variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a planar structure within the muscle sarcomere which lies midway within the thick filament (A) band, attaching to the plasma membrane at its base and running up towards the inward surface of the myofilament lattice, compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: calcium channel modulator resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of calcium channel modulators that elicit a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: body wall muscle dense body variant
description: Any variation in the attachment plaque for thin filaments onto the cell membrane. The dense body in body wall muscles is especially large, indenting far into the cytoplasm to border each sarcomere, thus providing a long row of coherent attachment sites at regular intervals (WormAtlas).

label: pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency.

label: AAD response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to the amino-acetonitrile derivatives (AADs) class of synthetic anthelmintics, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: antihelmintic response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to an agent that destroys or causes the expulsion of parasitic intestinal worms compared to that observed in control animals.

label: pesticide response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to any chemical substance that is used for killing pests, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: radiation induced reproductive cell death variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in radiation induced non-apoptotic death of multipotential precursor cells or tissues (clonogens) compared to control. Elimination of clonogens results in normal tissue damage as well as solid-tumor eradication.

label: induced cell death variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the extent of activation of programmed cell death, compared to control.

label: non apoptotic cell death variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the specific activation or halting of processes within a cell that occur through necrosis or programmed cell death pathways different from apoptosis, so that its vital functions markedly cease, rather than simply deteriorating gradually over time, which culminates in cell death, compared to control.

label: morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts compared to control animals.

label: radiation induced germ cell apoptosis resistant
description: Programmed cell death of germ cells caused by exposure to ionizing energy does not occur to the same extent as it does in control animals.

label: mutagen induced apoptosis variant
description: Programmed cell death of germ cells caused by exposure to physical or chemical DNA-damaging agents does not occur to the same extent as it does in control animals.

label: germ cell resistant ionizing radiation
description: Germ cells fail to respond to the dosage of ion producing radiation that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, germ cells require a higher dosage or a longer exposure to ion producing radiation to elicit the same response as control animals.

label: pathogen induced gene expression variant
description: Gene expression of an animal is not influenced by the exposure to disease causing agents in the same manner as control animals.

label: ivermectin response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to ivermectin, an agonist of glutamate-gated chloride channels, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cell pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of a cell.

label: fluoride resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of fluoride ions that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to fluoride ions to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: chemical resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of a specific chemical that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: organism toxic chemical response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific toxic chemical compared to that observed in control animals.

label: benomyl response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to the microtubule-depolymerizing drug benomyl, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: Dosage compensation complex assembly variant
description: Any variation in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins on DNA or RNA to form the complex that mediates dosage compensation on one or more X chromosomes, compared to control.

label: dosage compensation variant
description: Variations in the process of normalizing the expression level of X-linked genes between XX and XO animals compared to control.

label: suppression of head oscillations defective
description: Animals fail to suppress head oscillations in response to anterior touch. In C. elegans, this behavior is a result of tyraminergic signaling.

label: endocytic recycling defective
description: Variations in the directed movement of membrane-bounded vesicles from recycling endosomes back to the plasma membrane where they are recycled for further rounds of transport, compared to control.

label: protein transport variant
description: Any variation in the processes that modulate the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein into, out of, within or between cells by means of some external agent such as a transporter or pore compared to control.

label: manganese response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to manganese compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of the basic structural and functional unit of all organisms compared to control. Includes the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: manganese homeostasis variant
description: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of manganese ions within an organism compared to control.

label: environmental stimuli induced gene expression variant
description: Gene expression of an animal is not influenced by environmental changes in the same manner as control animals.

label: mitotic spindle asters defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubule spindle asters during a mitotic cell cycle.

label: mitotic spindle defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubule spindle during a mitotic cell cycle.

label: aster defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the array of microtubules emanating from a spindle pole that do not connect to kinetochores.

label: reduced pathogen accumulation
description: Animals exhibit a reduction in pathogen accumulation, persistent colonization, and luminal distension of the intestine.

label: protein ubiquitination variant
description: Variations in the process by which one or more ubiquitin moieties are added to a protein, compared to control.

label: dorsal nerve cord development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the anatomical structures that consist of processes of ventral cord motor neurons that send commissures to the dorsal side, as well as processes of certain head and tail neurons, over time from initial formation to mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: meiotic spindle positioning defective
description: Cells undergoing meiosis exhibit defects in the positioning of the meiotic spindle.

label: drug induced life span variant
description: Life span of the animal is not influenced by drug exposure in the same manner as control animals.

label: meiotic spindle rotation defective
description: Cells undergoing meiosis exhibit defects in the rotation of the meiotic spindle.

label: muscle arm development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the process extension from the muscle belly by which the muscle cells reach to the nerve cords to obtain innervation over time from initial formation to mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: body wall cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a body wall muscle cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: reduced protein oxidation levels
description: Protein oxidation levels, as measured by carbonylated protein levels for example, are reduced compared to controls.

label: oxidative stress response variant
description: Any variation in the state or activity of a cell (in terms of secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) in response to high levels of reactive oxygen species, compared to control.

label: hypersensitive to zinc deficiency
description: Animals exhibit detrimental responses to zinc deficiency more readily than control animals

label: copper homeostasis variant
description: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of copper ions within an organism compared to control.

label: progeny variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the progeny of an animal at any time from its fertilization to adulthood compared to control.

label: endogenous zinc levels increased
description: Animals exhibit increased levels of endogenous zinc compared to control animals.

label: cell membrane morphology variant
description: Any variation in the structure, form or composition of the semipermeable lipid bilayer that creates a boundary between the interior and exterior environment for cells, cellular organelles and tissues, within an organism compared to control.

label: male morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the outcome of morphogenic processes required for formation or proper placement of sex-specific structures that distinguish the animal as a male in the population, from that observed for control males.

label: increased susceptibility to viral infection
description: Animals are more prone to infection by virus compared to control animals.

label: pathogen susceptibility increased
description: Animals are more prone to infection compared to control.

label: silver nanoparticle hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to silver nanoparticles (AgNPs) at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: silver hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to silver at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: genetic pathway variant
description: Any variation in the set of interactions occurring between a group of genes who depend on each other's individual functions in order to make the aggregate function of the network available to the cell, compared to control.

label: head morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of their anterior end (which typically includes the anterior sensilla, pharynx and all muscles that are innervated by the nerve ring) compared to control.

label: body morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of their anatomy between the head and the tail compared to control animals.

label: cuticle shedding defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement.

label: molt defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in the process of periodic shedding, of part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates each larval stage.

label: selenium response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to selenium compared to that observed in control animals.

label: amino acid metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of amino acids within the organism or cell compared to control.

label: seam cells stacked
description: The hypodermal cells, which lie along the lateral body wall to form longitudinal stripes of epithelial cells underlying the alae, are misplaced such that they are stacked along the dorsal-ventral axis rather than forming a continuous row of adjacent cells .

label: epithelial morphology variant
description: Variations in the form, composition or structure of the layer of cells that cover the external surface of an organism and form the inner lining between the tissues and organs of that organism and the external environment compared to control. In C. elegans epithelial cells include epithelium of the alimentary tract, intestinal cells, hypodermis, interfacial cells and somatic gonad cells (Wormatlas).

label: 3 prime target RNA uridylation reduced
description: 3' uridylation of mRNA targeted for silencing does not occur at the same rate or extent of targeted mRNA in control animals.

label: cuticle attachment variant
description: Any variation in the attachment of the rigid external coating (which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells) to the outer body of an animal compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: cuticle development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the formation of the rigid external coating (which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells) over time compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: epithelial attachment variant
description: Variations in the adhesion of the layer of cells that cover the external surface of an organism which serves to protect the animal from external environment compared to control.

label: epithelial system physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the epithelial system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: 22G RNA expression reduced
description: Animals exhibit lowered levels of any or all of the clades of 22G RNA molecules, compared to control.

label: dendritic termini number reduced
description: The number of terminal regions of a neuron's dendrite is less that that observed for control animals.

label: dendrite development variant
description: Any variation in the processes that influence the generation of neuronal extensions, that carry afferent (incoming) action potentials towards the cell body compared to control.

label: nickel toxicity resistant
description: Animals fail to exhibit toxicity to the concentration of nickel that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans toxic responses to nickel include delayed development or lethality.

label: branched adult alae
description: The small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle of adults are branched as opposed to having an unbiforcated arrangement, lengthwise along the body (Wormatlas).

label: iron hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to iron at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: no anterior pharynx
description: Animals lack the anterior portion of the pharynx.

label: no pharynx
description: Embryos fail to generate cells that exhibit pharyngeal specification.

label: L1 arrest
description: The developmental program of the animals does not continue past the first larval stage (L1).

label: L1 larval development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a newly hatched animal through the first larval molt compared to control.

label: early larval arrest
description: Larvae arrest during early larval development. In C. elegans, this occurs during the L1 or L2 stages of larval development.

label: L4 arrest
description: The developmental program of the animals does not continue past the fourth larval stage (L4).

label: L4 larval development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the fourth larval stage compared to control.

label: late larval arrest
description: Larvae arrest during late larval development. In C. elegans, larval arrest occurs during the L3 or L4 stages of larval development.

label: mitochondrial membrane potential increased
description:
Any increase in the membrane potential (voltage gradient) across the inner
mitochondrial membrane compared to control.

label: postsynaptic component localization variant
description: Animals display variations in the distribution of the constituents of the postsynaptic side of the active zone, compared to control animals, that are required for receiving signals from the presynaptic side.

label: postsynaptic region morphology variant
description: The region opposite to the presynaptic region deviates in the structure, configuration or ratio of its components specific for receiving signals from the other side of the synapse compared to control.

label: swollen intestine
description: The intestinal lumen is expanded and can often be shown to be filled with bacteria.

label: neurite connectivity defective
description: An effective connection between reciprocal target neurons is not established properly.

label: L2 arrest
description: The developmental program of the animals does not continue past the second larval stage (L2).

label: L2 larval development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the second larval stage compared to control.

label: mid larval arrest
description: Animals arrest during the stage between early and late larval development. In C. elegans, mid larval arrest occurs during the L2 to L3 stages of development.

label: L3 arrest
description: The developmental program of the animals does not continue past the third larval stage (L3).

label: L3 larval development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the third larval stage compared to control.

label: gamete necrotic death increased
description: Ooctyes and or sperm appear vacuolated and degenerated compared to gametes in control animals. This degeneration is not due to normal programmed cell death.

label: necrotic cell death increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the cell death process that is morphologically characterized by a gain in cell volume (oncosis), swelling of organelles, plasma membrane rupture and subsequent loss of intracellular contents, compared to control.

label: body muscle displaced
description: The arrangement of the principal muscle cell type whose contractile activity generates body motion in the nematode differs from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans they consist of 95 unfused cells in the adult organized into four muscle quadrants. Their sarcomeres are obliquely striated and lie lengthwise along the body wall (Wormatlas).

label: body wall muscle development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the principal muscle cell type whose contractile activity generates body motion in the nematode over time compared to control. In C. elegans they consist of 95 unfused cells in the adult organized into four muscle quadrants. Their sarcomeres are obliquely striated and lie lengthwise along the body wall (Wormatlas).

label: mitochondrial content increased
description: Animals exhibit increases in the overall amount of mitochondria present in the animal, as determined by, for example, Mitotracker staining.

label: mitochondrial content variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the overall amount of mitochondria present in the animal, as determined by, for example, Mitotracker staining.

label: alpha amanitin resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of alpha amanitin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: lysosome-related organelle biogenesis variant
description: Variations in the processes that are carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosome-related organelles (LROs) that, like lysosomes, have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell but are distinct in function, composition, and morphology, compared to control.

label: shrunken intestine
description: Intestine is shrunken and may appear constricted.

label: muscle cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a muscle cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: ATP levels increased
description:
Animals exhibit an increase in the cellular levels of Adenosine-5'-triphosphate (ATP), compared to control. ATP is a nucleotide
that plays a versatile role in cell biology.

label: ATP levels variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the cellular levels of Adenosine-5'-triphosphate (ATP), compared to control. ATP is a nucleotide that plays a versatile role in cell biology.

label: hatching variant
description: Variations in the ability of an animal to emerge from the protective egg shell compared to control animals.

label: lead response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to lead compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cobalt hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to cobalt at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: postembryonic development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of an animal over time, from hatching to adulthood, compared to control.

label: lead hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to lead at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: pace of P lineage defective early emb
description: More than five minutes between AB and P1 divisions.

label: cell division variant
description: Any variation that alters the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells compared to control.

label: gastrulation variant
description: Variations in the process by which the germ layers become positioned in an embryo compared to control animals. Gastrulation involves the proper ingression of small groups of cells at various times into the blastocoel space.

label: mercury hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to mercury at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: break induced focus formation variant
description: Variations in the generation of foci that mark crossover recombination events, compared to control. These foci mark the boundary of asymmetric synaptonemal complex disassembly.

label: cell ionizing radiation response variant
description: Cells exhibit variations in their response to ionizing radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: DNA damage induced focus formation variant
description: Variations in the aggregation of molecules at the site of DNA strand breakage or damage compared to control.

label: chromium response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to chromium compared to that observed in control animals.

label: aluminum response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to aluminum compared to that observed in control animals.

label: embryonic terminal arrest variable emb
description: The developmental program does not continue past embryogenesis; stage of arrest is not consistent from animal to animal.

label: terminal arrest variable
description: Variations that cause developmental progression to cease at different stages of the lifecycle.

label: metal accumulation increased
description: Animals exhibited higher amounts of internal metal concentrations compared to control animals.

label: protein methylation variant
description: Variations in the processes that incorporate methyl groups to one or more amino acids within a protein, compared to control.

label: maternal effect lethal emb
description: Lethality caused by the perturbation of maternal gene products that are contributed to oogenesis and are required during embryogenesis.

label: embryonic lethal
description: Animals die during embryonic development. In C. elegans, often assayed as refractile eggs that fail to hatch; when applied to large-scale RNAi screens in C. elegans, more than 10% of embryos die.

label: anoxia resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to trace amounts of oxygen that elicit a response in control animals.

label: anoxia response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in response to anoxia, trace oxygen conditions, compared to controls.

label: lethal
description: Animals die prematurely at any stage of the life cycle.

label: anoxia hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to anoxic (trace oxygen levels) stress after a shorter exposure time compared to control.

label: larval arrest
description: The developmental program of the animals halts at any larval stage and thus fails to reach adulthood. In C.elegans, this occurs anytime during L1-L4 stage.

label: increased acidified compartments
description: Animals contain excess acidified intracellular compartments. These compartments are positive for indicators such as Acridine Orange as well as LysoTracker Red, in a lysosome-like manner.

label: cell acidification variant
description: Variations in the processes that reduce the internal pH of a cell (measured by the concentration of the hydrogen ion), compared to control.

label: fertilization defect male
description: Failure of male-derived sperm to fuse with an oocyte during sexual reproduction.

label: osmolarity modulated swimming variant
description: The swimming behavior of animals are influenced or modulate by the osmolarity of the swimming buffer. The swimming of wild-type C. elegans animals are not affected by the osmolarity of the swimming liquid.

label: osmotic stress response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the response to osmotic stress compared to control. In C. elegans, exposure to stress-inducing osmotic conditions invokes cellular changes, including transcriptional up or down-regulation of genes.

label: fertilization defective hermaphrodite
description: Any perturbation that disrupts the fusion of male and female gametes (sperm and oocyte) in adult hermaphrodites during sexual reproduction.

label: synaptic remodeling variant
description: The polarity reversal process by which synaptic components are removed from one side of the synapse and then reformed on the opposite cell does not occur or occurs in a different manner than in controls. In C. elegans, at the end of the L1 stage, the DD neurons undergo a complete polarity reversal such that the ventral synapses disappear and new synapses are formed on opposing dorsal body muscles.

label: synaptogenesis variant
description: Any variation in the biosynthesis of a synapse compared to control.

label: precocious oogenesis
description: Relatively unspecialized germ cells prematurely acquire the specialized properties of mature oocytes.

label: oogenesis variant
description: Any aberrancy in the processes that influence the generation and maturation of oocytes compared to control animals.

label: paralyzed arrested elongation two fold
description: Movement and elongation ceases at the two-fold stage. The myofilament lattice in body wall muscle cells is variant. However, development in embryos continues. Embryos hatch as inviable larvae.

label: two fold arrest
description: Cessation of development that normally occurs in C. elegans 460-520 min after the first cleavage at 20C, the stage between the 1.5-fold and 3-fold embryo.

label: manganese induced oxidative stress response
description: Oxidative stress induced by manganese differs from that of control worms.

label: fertility reduced
description: Animals exhibit a reduction in the production of new individuals that contain some portion of their genetic material inherited from that organism as a result of defective gametes.

label: fertility variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the time of onset or duration of the fertile period, or production of new individuals that contain some portion of their genetic material inherited from that organism compared to control.

label: larval growth variant
description: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) during the larval stages compared to control animals.

label: larval development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a larva over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control. The larva is the early, immature form of an animal between hatching and adulthood.

label: increased levels of reactive oxygen species
description: Animals exhibit increased endogenous levels of reactive oxygen species (chemically reactive molecules containing oxygen) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: reactive oxygen species homeostasis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in endogenous levels of reactive oxygen species (chemically reactive molecules containing oxygen) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: endocytic recycling compartment organization and biogenesis defective
description: Animals exhibit disruptions in tubular or tubulo-vesicular structures that function in endocytic transport from early to recycling endosomes.

label: endo lysosomal degradation pathway defective
description: The degradation of endocytosed and intracellular material does not occur to the same extent as it does in control animals.

label: cell gamma ray resistant
description: Cells fail to respond to the dosage of gamma irradiation that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, cells require longer exposure times to gamma irradiation to mimic the response observed in control animals.

label: late larval lethal
description: Animals die during late larval development. In C. elegans, this occurs during the L3- L4 larval stages of the life cycle.

label: growth defective on low phosphate media
description: Animals are unable to grow on media depleted of phosphate.

label: organism hypersensitive gamma irradiation
description: Organisms respond to a lower dosage of gamma rays or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: organism gamma ray response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to gamma ray radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism hypersensitive ionizing radiation
description: Animals exhibit increased sensitivity to the effects of ion producing radiation compared to control animals.

label: reduced levels of reactive oxygen species
description: Animals exhibit reduced endogenous levels of reactive oxygen species (chemically reactive molecules containing oxygen) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cell UV hypersensitive
description: Cells respond to a lower dosage of UV or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: feeding reduced
description: Animals consume less food than control animals

label: feeding behavior variant
description: Behavior associated with the intake of food is altered compared to control.

label: cell acidification defective
description: Animals lack the capacity to reduce the internal pH of a cell.

label: gut granule morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphology of the different inclusions within the intestinal cytoplasm, including birefringent crystalline objects and other dark-staining endosomes compared to control. In C. elegans these contents might include glycogen granules (polysaccharide storage), rhabditin (carbohydrate storage), yolk granules (lipid and protein), and concentrated waste products (Wormatlas).

label: intestinal cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of intestinal cells compared to control animals.

label: cell cycle arrest
description: Cells of the animals cease during one of its replicative phases (G1, S, G2, M).

label: cell cycle progression variant
description: Cells of the animals exhibit variations in the progression or exit from the biochemical and morphological processes that occur during successive replication or nuclear replication events from that observed for control animals.

label: adult lethal
description: Premature lethality during the adult stage. When applied to large-scale RNAi screens in C. elegans, this phenotype is present in at least 10% of analyzed worms, or at least 30% in the case of rrf-3 perturbed background.

label: extended life span
description: The duration of viability in the adult phase of the life-cycle surpasses that of control animals.

label: gamma ray induced apoptosis increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to the nucleic acid damaging agent, gamma irradiation, compared to control.

label: XX lethal
description: XX-bearing individuals die preferentially over other animals in the population. In C.elegans, XX animals die preferentially over X0 animals.

label: sexually dimorphic lethality
description: Animals die prematurely at any stage of the life cycle in a sex dependent manner.

label: endogenous zinc levels reduced
description: Animals exhibit reduced levels of endogenous zinc compared to control animals.

label: neurite morphology variant
description: Animals display variations in the structure, organization of components, or spatial pattern of any projection stemming from a neuronal cell, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: neuron morphology variant
description: Animals display variations in the structure or organization of components of the neuronal cell internal to the cell itself or in relation to the cellular environment compared to control. A neuron is a major cell type of nervous tissue specialized for transmission of information in the form of patterns of impulses.

label: arsenic hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to arsenic at a lower concentration or at a shorter exposure time compared to control animals.

label: necrotic cell death variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the cell death process that is morphologically characterized by a gain in cell volume (oncosis), swelling of organelles, plasma membrane rupture and subsequent loss of intracellular contents, compared to control.

label: phytochelatin synthesis deficient
description: Animals do not produce the same amount of functional phytochelatins as measured in control worms. Phytochelatins are any of a group of peptides that bind metals (Cd, Zn, Cu, Pb, Hg) in thiolate coordination complexes.

label: biosynthesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the energy-requiring part of metabolism in which simpler substances are transformed into more complex ones compared to control.

label: pumping absent
description: Animals completely lack any pharyngeal pumping motion.

label: pharyngeal pumping rate variant
description: The number of coordinated contraction-relaxation cycles (pumps) exhibited by the pharyngeal muscle deviates from that observed for control animals.

label: X0 lethal
description: XO-bearing individuals die preferentially over other animals in the population. In C.elegans, X0 animals die preferentially over XX animals.

label: body vacuole
description: Vacuoles accumulate in the body. A vacuole is a closed structure, found only in eukaryotic cells, that is completely surrounded by unit membrane and contains liquid material.

label: hypersensitive to iron deficiency
description: Animals exhibit detrimental responses to iron deficiency more readily than control animals.

label: iron homeostasis variant
description: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of iron within an organism compared to control.

label: lipid depleted
description: Animals are unable to take up or store lipids. In C. elegans, this defect results in pale, skinny and arrested larva.

label: fat content reduced
description: Animals exhibit less fat or lipid than observed in control animals.

label: hypersensitive to galactose
description: Animals exhibit negative effects on growth, development, or metabolism when exposed to a galactose-rich diet, compared to control animals.

label: procorpus contraction defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the muscle contractions of the anterior region of corpus, the area responsible for allowing food to enter the corpus.

label: corpus contraction defect
description: Any defect in the muscle contractions of the extended anterior region of the pharynx lying just anterior to the isthmus and terminal bulb (Wormatlas).

label: male gonad morphology variant
description: Variations in the form or composition of a specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces the male gametes compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: corpse morphology variant
description: Corpses resulting from programmed cell death appear different in size or shape from those of corpses in control animals.

label: male sex muscle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the muscles of the adult male reproductive system compared to control. In C. elegans males, the M myoblast gives rise to a much larger set of specialized muscles, compared to hermaphrodites, which differentiate within the tail region (Wormatlas).

label: blistered
description: Fluid-filled blisters appear on the cuticle.

label: pharynx extension defective
description: Embryos exhibit defects in the extension of pharyngeal cells toward the buccal opening during embryogenesis compared to controls.

label: pharynx unattached
description: The pharynx or pharyngeal muscle does not form a functional connection to the mouth or buccal cavity.

label: reproductive system morphology variant
description: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the reproductive system, compared to control. The reproductive system is involved in the generation of progeny which contain genetic material inherited from the parents.

label: hook development variant
description: Any variation in the development of the structure that lies on the ventral surface just anterior and central to the base of the spicule openings (small lump on the gubernaculum of the male tail) and contains a sensory structure called the hook sensillum, compared to control. In C. elegans the hook is necessary for proper male mating.

label: antibody temporal expression variant
description: The expression of a protein, as determined by antibody staining, varied from controls with respect to timing such that the protein was observed to be expressed at earlier timepoints or later timepoints than controls.

label: missing gonad arms
description: Animals are missing one or both gonad arms, the normally U-shaped projections of the gonad that extend into the anterior or posterior of the animal and bends back towards the center of the animal.

label: systemic RNAi variant
description: Animals are defective for RNAi introduced by environmental means such as in the cases of RNAi triggered by soaking or feeding.

label: galactose metabolism variant
description: Animals process dietary galactose differently than control animals, these differences can result in increased and or decreased levels of intermediary galactose metabolites.

label: proctodeum morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure and organization of the chamber in the male tail that extends from the termination of four canals (vas deferens, gut, and left and right spicule channels) to just before the cloaca, from that observed in control animals.

label: chromosome condensation variant
description: Any variation in the progressive compaction of dispersed interphase chromatin into threadlike chromosomes prior to mitotic or meiotic nuclear division, or during apoptosis, in eukaryotic cells compared to control.

label: mitosis variant
description: Any variation in the division of the eukaryotic cell nucleus to produce two daughter nuclei that contain the identical chromosome complement of their mother compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite self sterile
description: Hermaphrodites fail to produce any viable progeny via self-fertilization. However, such hermaphrodites can successfully reproduce if mated to control males.

label: hermaphrodite sterile
description: Hermaphrodites fail to generate viable self-progeny and/or cross-progeny.

label: growth variant
description: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) compared to control animals.

label: developmental timing variant
description: The timing of specific developmental events in some tissues is altered relative to the timing of events in other tissues.

label: amphid dye filling defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in dye-filling of the neuronal cells of the amphid sensilla. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling with FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: amphid morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the neuronal cells of the amphid sensillum, from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling experiments using FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: male bursa development variant
description: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the male bursa over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control. The male bursa consists of the lateral fan and rays (WormAtlas).

label: phasmid dye filling defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in dye-filling of the neuronal cells of the phasmid sensilla. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling with FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: phasmid morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the neuronal cells of the phasmid sensillum, from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling experiments using FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: male fan morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the flattened structure extending laterally at the extreme tip of the adult male consisting of nine pairs of sensory rays that lie within a web-like cuticle compared to control.

label: embryonic polarity variant
description: Contents or structures of an embryonic cell are not restricted/localized to the same positions (or poles) compared with control animals.

label: extra rays
description: Animals exhibit an extra number of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan.

label: male tail sensory ray development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan from its formation to the mature structure when compared to control animals.

label: head cavity
description: The head contains cavities, possibly indicative of inappropriate cell death.

label: slow growth
description: Any variation that causes a reduction in growth rate compared to control.

label: retarded heterochronic variations
description: Variations that result in the deceleration of the rate, frequency or extent of the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition, compared to control.

label: general pace of development variant
description: Variations in the progression time of an animal from pronuclei meeting to adulthood compared to control animals.

label: sick
description: Animals exhibit some combination of abnormal features relating to size, movement, body integrity, pigmentation, viability, fertility etc.

label: chromosome condensation failure
description: The progressive compaction of dispersed interphase chromatin into threadlike chromosomes prior to mitotic or meiotic nuclear division, or during apoptosis in eukaryotic cells is abolished.

label: pattern antibody staining variant
description: Any variation in the cellular or subcellular distribution of a gene product, as detected by antibody staining, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: protein interaction variant
description: Variations in the selective and non-covalent physical association between two or more proteins, or a protein and nucleic acid/macromolecular complex, compared to control.

label: fewer body wall muscles
description: Any variation that results in a fewer than control number of body wall muscle cells.

label: muscle missing
description: Any variation that results in a fewer than control number of muscle cells.

label: spermatheca absent
description: Animals lack the somatic gonad structure that connects the distal gonad arm to the uterus.

label: spermatheca development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the somatic gonad structure that connects the distal gonad arm to the uterus over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: exploded through vulva
description: The animal is ruptured at the vulva and displays an extrusion of internal organs at the site of rupture.

label: epithelial system development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the epithelial system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: extra pharyngeal muscle cells
description: Animals contain an excess number of pharyngeal muscle cells compared to control. In C. elegans, pharyngeal cells are derived from MS-blastomere. The overproduction of pharyngeal tissues is a result of other blastomeres adopting an MS-like fate.

label: excess pharyngeal cells
description: Animals contain an excess number of pharyngeal cells compared to control. In C. elegans, pharyngeal cells are derived from MS-blastomere. The overproduction of pharyngeal tissues is a result of other blastomeres adopting an MS-like fate.

label: proctodeum development variant
description: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the male proctodeum over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control. The union of the vas deferens and the intestine give rise to the proctodeum which contains copulatory spicules.

label: larval body morphology variant
description: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of the animal as it progresses from hatching to adult compared to control animals.

label: adult body morphology variant
description: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of the animal after it has completed progression through the larval stages compared to control animals.

label: kinase activity reduced
description: Any variation that results in a decrease in the catalytic phosphorylation activity of a kinase enzyme compared to control. Catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component). Kinases are enzymes capable of phosphorylating their respective substrates.

label: enzyme activity reduced
description: Any variation that results in a decrease in the catalytic activity of an enzyme compared to control. Catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component).

label: male fan development variant
description: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the male fan over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control.

label: fluoranthene hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to fluoranthene at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: chemical hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to a specific chemical at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: arsenite hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to arsenite at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: antimony hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to antimony at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: one cell arrest early emb
description: Embryos fail to divide and arrest as one-cell embryos.

label: early embryonic lethal
description: Animal dies prior to the gastrulation stage of embryogenesis.

label: protein DNA interaction variant
description: Variations in the selective and non-covalent physical association between a protein and a specific DNA sequence, compared to control.

label: protein RNA interaction variant
description: Variations in the selective and non-covalent physical association between a protein and a specific RNA sequence, compared to control.

label: egg size defective early emb
description: Egg is smaller or larger compared to eggs of control animals.

label: egg size variant
description: Any variation in the overall size of fertilized oocytes that are laid compared to those laid by control animals.

label: manganese hypersensitivity
description: Animals respond at a faster rate or to lower concentrations of manganese that that observed for control animals.

label: transgene expression undetectable cell specific
description: The expression of a gene product produced by DNA coded for by exogenous genetic material that has been introduced into the organism is reduced below the threshold of detection in specific cells.

label: transgene expression undetectable
description: The expression of a gene product produced by DNA coded for by exogenous genetic material that has been introduced into the organism is reduced below the threshold of detection.

label: uterus vacuole
description: The uterus contains cavities, possibly indicative of inappropriate cell death.

label: transgene expression reduced
description: Any decrease in the intensity of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: developmental delay postembryonic
description: The developmental progression of an animal after the embryonic stage, over time, from its formation to its mature structure is delayed compared to control.

label: developmental delay
description: The developmental progression of an animal over time, from its formation to its mature structure is delayed compared to control.

label: pharyngeal vacuole
description: The pharynx contains cavities, possibly indicative of inappropriate cell death.

label: pronuclear nuclear appearance variant emb
description: The shape and size of nuclei as well as the distribution of nucleoporins are strongly affected.

label: embryonic cell organization biogenesis variant
description: Variations in the processes that are carried out at in the embryo which results in its formation or the arrangement of constituent parts, compared to control.

label: slow embryonic development
description: The progression through stages between fertilization to hatching are temporally retarded.

label: slow development
description: The developmental progression of an animal, from its formation to its mature structure occurs over a longer time period compared to control.

label: antimonite hypersensitivity
description: Animals respond to antimonite at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: protein rna interaction abolished
description: Animals lack a specific protein-RNA interaction observed in control animals.

label: constitutive egg laying
description: Eggs are laid under conditions where egg laying is normally inhibited.

label: chloroquinone hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to chloroquinone at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: male mating efficiency eliminated
description: Males sire no cross progeny.

label: male mating efficiency reduced
description: The number of cross progeny sired by males is reduced compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite reproductive system morphology variant
description: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the hermaphrodite reproductive system, compared to control. The reproductive system is involved in the generation of progeny which contain genetic material inherited from the parents.

label: egg laying variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the stage of eggs laid, egg laying cycle, number of eggs or egg laying in response to stimuli compared to control.

label: chloroquinone resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of chloroquinone that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: hermaphrodite sex muscle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the muscles of the adult hermaphrodite reproductive system compared to control. In C. elegans hermaphrodites these muscles include the vulval and uterine muscles, located near the vulva in the midbody, which all derive from the M myoblast (Wormatlas).

label: colchicine hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to colchicine at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: colchicine resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of colchicine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: neuron cell body absent misplaced
description: The body of a neuron is not where it should be when compared to control animals; it is absent or misplaced.

label: anesthetic hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to anesthetic at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: anesthetic response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific anesthetic compared to that observed in control animals.

label: egg laying levamisole resistant
description: Animals are not induced to lay eggs in reponse to exogenous levamisole. In C. elegans, levamisole stimulates egg-laying.

label: egg laying response to drug variant
description: Characteristic response to drugs with respect to egg-laying behavior varies compared to control.

label: anesthetic resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of anesthetic that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: phentolamine resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of phentolamine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: adrenergic receptor antagonist response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific adrenergic receptor antagonist compared to that observed in control animals.

label: bag of worms
description: A worm carcass is formed with retained eggs that hatch inside.

label: bloated
description: Worms appears turgid or swollen as a result of an excess number of eggs being retained in the uterus.

label: isthmus morphology defective
description: Any observed morphological defects of the isthmus.

label: pharyngeal morphology variant
description: Variations in the form or composition of the mouthparts at the anterior end of the digestive tract which contain a series of radial muscles, related neurons and epithelial cells, and several gland cells which may aid in digestion compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: corpus morphology defective
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the extended anterior region of the pharynx lying just anterior to the isthmus and terminal bulb compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: pharynx disorganized
description: The components of the feeding organ fail to be arranged in the same manner as control animals.

label: ray ectopic
description: Animals have finger-like sensory sensilla (rays) that are present in places they are normally not found, when compared to the number or location in control animals.

label: ectopic cell
description: Animals have extra cells, which are present in places they are normally not found, when compared to the number or location of these cells in control animals.

label: meiotic spindle defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubule spindle during a meiotic cell cycle.

label: spindle defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during a cell cycle.

label: egg laying imipramine hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to exogenous imipramine at a lower concentration or within a shorter time period than control animals under the same conditions.

label: dauer constitutive
description: Formation of dauer larvae under conditions that do not favor dauer formation.

label: dauer formation variant
description: Characteristic entry into the dauer stage is altered compared to control animals.

label: male postdeirid sensilla absent
description: Males lack the specialized sensory papillae that lie along the posterior half of the body.

label: male nervous system development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the male nervous system over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals. The nervous system is involved in the coordination and control of bodily activities and the interpretation of information from the senses.

label: egg laying phentolamine resistant
description: Animals are not induced to lay eggs in reponse to exogenous phentolamine. In C. elegans, phentolamine stimulates egg-laying.

label: metacorpus morphology defective
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the first pharyngeal bulb compared to control.
