label: late embryonic arrest
description: Cessation of development during the final stages of embryogenesis. In C. elegans, this stage normally occurs 620-800 min after the first cleavage at 20C and is the stage after elongation.

label: egg laying imipramine resistant
description: Animals are not induced to lay eggs in reponse to exogenous imipramine. In C. elegans, imipramine stimulates egg-laying.

label: imipramine resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of imipramine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: positive chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of an animal in response to chemical attractants as defined by control animals.

label: ethyl methanesulfonate response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to ethyl methanesulfonate (EMS) compared to that observed in control animals.

label: intestinal calcium signaling variant
description: Any variation in the series of molecular signals in which an intestinal cell uses calcium ions to convert an extracellular signal into a response, compared to control.

label: intestinal physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the intestine to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: actin cytoskeleton dynamics variant
description: Any variation in the dynamic structural changes to the arrangement of constituent parts of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins compared to control.

label: actin organization biogenesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the formation and/or arrangement of actin, an abundant cytoskeletal protein in most cells, often linked to the plasma membrane and concentrated at cell junctions compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: aldicarb hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to aldicarb at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: aldicarb response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to aldicarb compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cytoskeleton organization biogenesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure, composition or arrangement of any of the various filamentous elements that form the internal framework of cells, compared to control. The various elements of the cytoskeleton not only serve in the maintenance of cellular shape but also have roles in other cellular functions, including cellular movement, cell division, endocytosis, and movement of organelles.

label: dauer defective
description: Failure to form dauer larvae under dauer-inducing conditions.

label: organism ionizing radiation response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response ionizing radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: commissure variant
description: Animals display variations in the structure, organization or path of the part of the axon that forms a bridge between body regions, compared to that in control animals.

label: methyl methanesulfonate response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to methyl methanesulfonate compared to that observed in control animals.

label: pharyngeal pumping reduced
description: Pharyngeal pumping motion occurs at a slower rate than control animals.

label: protein phosphorylation variant
description: Variations in the processes that incorporate phosphate groups to one or more amino acids within a protein, compared to control.

label: aldicarb resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of aldicarb that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: acetylcholinesterase inhibitor resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of acetylcholinesterase inhibitor that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: pharyngeal pumping increased
description: The contraction and relaxation movements of the pharynx occur at a greater frequency compared to that observed for control animals.

label: chromosome morphology variant
description: Variations in the form or composition of a structure in the cell nucleus which contains the genetic material encoded as DNA and surrounded by histone proteins and other regulatory elements compared to control. In C. elegans the normal cell contains 5 pairs of 'autosomes' and one or two X chromosomes (Wormatlas).

label: nuclear appearance variant
description: The morphological appearance of nuclei differs from control animals.

label: protein phosphorylation increased
description: Animals exhibit higher levels of protein phosphorylation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: long
description: Animals are longer than control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: apoptotic DNA degradation defective
description: Dying animals cells exhibit defects in the fragmentation of chromosomal DNA into oligonucleosomal-length fragments compared to control animals. This process can be monitored by the quantity and quality of TUNEL (TdT-mediated dUTP nick end labeling)-positive nuclei.

label: actin cytoskeleton filament morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure, composition or arrangement of actin, an abundant cytoskeletal protein in most cells, often linked to the plasma membrane and concentrated at cell junctions compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: oviduct muscle defective
description: Variations in the progression of the muscles of the adult hermaphrodite oviduct over time from their initial formation to their mature structure compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite sex muscle development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the muscles of the adult hermaphrodite reproductive system over time form their initial formation to their mature structure compared to control.

label: centration defective early emb
description: The coordinated movement during prophase of the two centrosomes and the two pronuclei towards the center of the one cell embryo is abolished.

label: pronuclear migration defective early emb
description: Pronucleus migration is abnormal in the inviable embryo.

label: serotonin hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to serotonin at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: endoplasmic reticulum metabolism variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways of the endoplasmic reticulum compared to control.

label: organelle metabolism variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways of an organelle compared to control.

label: pharyngeal pumping irregular
description: Pharyngeal pumping motion occurs at intervals that vary from control animals.

label: squat
description: Squat animals are dumpy as homozygotes, but roll as heterozygotes.

label: body size variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the physical dimensions of its body compared to control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: protein phosphorylation reduced
description: Animals exhibit decreased levels of protein phosphorylation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: slowing response on food variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in modulating their locomotory rate in response to its food , compared to control. Basal slowing response refers to when well-fed animals move more slowly in the presence of bacteria than in the absence of bacteria . Second , food-deprived control animals , when transferred to bacteria , display a dramatically enhanced slowing response that ensures that the animals do not leave their newly encountered source of food.

label: sexually dimorphic mechanosensation variant
description: Any variation with respect to perception or response to mechanical stimuli in a sex dependent manner compared to control animals.

label: germ cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of germ cells compared to control animals.

label: cell type morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of specialized cell types, compared to control. Includes the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: marginal cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of marginal cells compared to control animals.

label: muscle cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of muscle cells compared to control animals.

label: gland cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of gland cells compared to control animals.

label: anus morphology variant
description: Any variation in the structural appearance of the caudal opening of the rectum in the tail compared to control animals.

label: cloacal morphology variant
description: Any variation in the structural appearance of the epithelial chamber that links the genital and alimentary tracts to the exterior via the anus (cloacal opening) compared to control animals.

label: uterine vulval cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the epithelial cells that form the interface between the uterus and the vulva (likely via a multilayered set of flaps) compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: pharyngeal intestinal valve morphology variant
description: Any variation in the structure or appearance of the cells that form a narrow passage connecting the posterior bulb of the pharynx to the anterior intestine compared to control. In C. elegans this valve is composed of 3 pairs of cells each forming a flattened disc-like ring and is lined by a layer of cuticle (Wormatlas).

label: male response to hermaphrodite variant
description: Any variation in the response by the male to a hermaphrodite after initial contact following mate finding compared to control. In C. elegans the male stops forward locomotion, presses the ventral side of his tail against his partner's body, and begins moving backward along the hermaphrodite. Male response behavior is initiated when sensory neurons located in the rays of his tail contact a potential mate.

label: mate searching variant
description: Any variation in the ability of an animal to search for a mate compared to control. In C. elegans, this is defined by failure of the leaving assay.

label: pre hermaphrodite contact variant
description: Males exhibit variations in mating behavior prior to contacting its mate compared to control.

label: rectal morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the rectum compared to control animals.

label: coelomocyte morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of coelomocytes compared to control animals.

label: excretory gland cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a pair of large cells in the head that fuse to form a single gland whose contents are released into the excretory duct through a specialized secretory membrane, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: excretory secretory system morphology variant
description: Variations in the form, structure or composition of related tissues that allow the animal to secrete saline fluid and maintain a proper salt balance compared to control. In C. elegans, four cell types (1 pore cell, 1 duct cell, 1 canal cell and a fused pair of gland cells) make up the excretory system (Wormatlas).

label: pale adult
description: Adults show deficiencies in chroma resulting in increased translucency.

label: adult pigmentation variant
description: Adult animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter its transparency/translucency compared to control animals.

label: pale
description: Animals show deficiencies in chroma resulting in increased translucency.

label: basal lamina morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the basal lamina compared to control animals.

label: epithelial system morphology variant
description: Variations in the form, composition or structure of the epithelial system that serves to protect the organism from the external environment compared to control.

label: excretory socket cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the excretory socket cell compared to control animals.

label: body wall muscle cell spindle development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the region of a body wall muscle cell that contains the myofilament lattice (adjacent to the hypodermis) over time, from its initial state to the fully differentiated state compared to control.

label: excretory cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the excretory cell compared to control animals.

label: excretory duct cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the excretory duct cell compared to control animals.

label: post hermaphrodite contact variant
description: Males exhibit variations in mating behavior after contacting its mate compared to control.

label: periodic spicule prodding defective
description: Males exhibit defects in the continuous prodding of spicule tips at the vulva prior to prolonged spicule insertion.

label: spicule insertion defective
description: Males exhibit defects in the insertion of the male copulatory spicules into the mating partner. In C. elegan spicule insertion behavior initiates when the male cloaca contacts the vulva. During most mating encounters, the spicule tips will prod the vulva continuously until they partially penetrate, which then causes the protractors to contract completely so that the spicules extend through the vulva.

label: sustained spicule protraction defective
description: Males exhibit defects in the prolonged, tonic, spicule extrusion through the vulva prior to sperm transfer.

label: spicule protraction variant
description: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of the male that are associated with the protraction of the male copulatory spicules compared to control.

label: approximate vulval location variant
description: Any variation in the mating process that includes the male stopping at the vulva (usually after backing) compared to control. In C. elegans general vulva location (stopping) requires the hook sensillum.

label: vulva location variant
description: Any variation in the male's ability to locate his partner's vulva when backing along the ventral side of the partner during mating compared to control. In C. elegans the male stops at the vulva, coordinates his movements to the hermaphrodite's, and positions his tail precisely over the vulva so that he may insert his spicules and ejaculate.

label: sperm release defective
description: Any variation in the initial movement of sperm through the vas deferens, exiting the cloaca, compared to control.

label: sperm transfer defective
description: Any defect in the process whereby a male inseminates his partner by introducing sperm into the genital tract.

label: post male contact variant
description: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of a hermaphrodite after male contact during mating compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite mating variant
description: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of a hermaphrodite during mating compared to control.

label: pre male contact variant
description: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of a hermaphrodite prior to male contact during mating compared to control.

label: dauer nictation behavior variant
description: Any variation in the behavior exhibited by dauer larva in which they crawl up upon the substrate and wave back and forth while standing on their tail compared to control. Nictation is often associated with the search for a new host.

label: dauer behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of dauer stage animals in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: precise vulval location variant
description: Any variation in the mating process that includes the male positioning his tail precisely over the vulva so that he may insert his spicules and ejaculate compared to control. In C. elegans precise vulva location (coordinating movement and tail positioning) requires the post cloacal sensillium and the spicules.

label: sperm transfer cessation defective
description: Any variation in the retraction of spicules after all sperm that exit the seminal vesicle have been released compared to control.

label: sperm transfer continuation defective
description: Any variation in the continued movement of sperm through the vas deferens, exiting the cloaca, compared to control. In C. elegans, when all sperm that exit the seminal vesicle have been released, the spicules retract into the male.

label: locomotion variant
description: Animals exhibit deviations in self-propelled movement on a solid medium compared to control animals.

label: sinusoidal movement variant
description: Any variation in the propagation of the contraction sine wave along the body while an animal travels from one location to another, compared to control.

label: wavelength of movement variant
description: Any variation in the distance in the line of advance of a body wave from any one point to the next point of corresponding phase compared to control.

label: velocity of movement variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the net velocity of an animal, that is, the maximum distance an animal traverses over an extended period of time, from that observed for control animals.

label: activity level variant
description: Any variation in the degree of movement compared to control animals.

label: plate tap reflex variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to substrate vibration compared to control.

label: amplitude of sinusoidal movement variant
description: Any variation in the extent of a vibratory movement (as a worm bend) measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control.

label: body bend variant
description: Any variation in the maximum ventral and dorsal flex of the animal compared to control animals.

label: frequency of body bend variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the frequency of oscillations between adjacent body segments from that observed for control animals.

label: body posture amplitude decreased
description: Animals exhibit variations in body posture caused by a decrease in the extent of displacement measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control animals.

label: body posture amplitude variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in body posture with regard to the extent of displacement measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control animals.

label: body posture variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in body posture compared to control animals. For example, in C. elegans characteristic sinusoidal body posture is altered.

label: tail bend angle decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of the maximum flex of the most posterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: tail bend angle variant
description: Any variation in the extent of the maximum flex of the most posterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: body posture wavelength increased
description: Animals exhibit variations in body posture caused by an increase in the distance between repeating units of a wave pattern compared to control animals. In C. elegans, characteristic sinusoidal body posture is sinusoidal.

label: body posture wavelength variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in body posture with regard to the distance between repeating units of a wave pattern compared to control animals. In C. elegans, characteristic sinusoidal body posture is sinusoidal.

label: body posture wavelength decreased
description: Animals exhibit variations in body posture caused by a decrease in the distance between repeating units of a wave pattern compared to control animals. In C. elegans, characteristic sinusoidal body posture is sinusoidal.

label: body posture amplitude increased
description: Animals exhibit variations in body posture caused by an increase in the extent of displacement measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control animals.

label: coiling frequency decreased
description: Animals spend less time with their body posture in a coil or they decrease the frequency with which they form coils compared to control animals.

label: attraction signal defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the production of the sensory signal to attract males.

label: mate finding defective
description: Males exhibit defects in their response to the mate-finding cue.

label: male response to contact defective
description: The inability of a male to respond properly to a potential mate after contact. In C.elegans, proper response includes apposing the ventral side of his tail to the hermaphrodite's body and swimming backward.

label: copulation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any processes that lead to the successful transfer of sperm from one organism to another.

label: hermaphrodite behavior variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in hermaphrodite-specific behaviors compared to control.

label: oxygen consumption increased
description: Animals exhibit an increased rate of oxygen utilization compared to control animals.

label: oxygen consumption variant
description: Variations in the process of gaseous oxygen intake between an organism and its environment compared to control animals.

label: mitochondrial content decreased
description: Animals exhibit decreases in the overall amount of mitochondria present in the animal, as determined by, for example, Mitotracker staining.

label: epidermis muscle detached
description: The cell(s) whose principal function is to provide contractile forces, is separated from the adjacent epidermis.

label: muscle attachment variant
description: Any variation in the connection of the cell(s) whose principal function is to provide contractile forces with its neighboring cells or tissues compared to control.

label: metabolite content decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the quantity of metabolites, small molecule products or intermediates required for the metabolic functioning of the cell or organism

label: intestinal cell proliferation variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern the expansion of intestinal cell populations compared to control.

label: epidermis cuticle detached
description: Animals are deficient in the adhesion of the cuticle to the epidermal surface of the animal.

label: M lineage variant
description: The descendants of the M precursor cell exhibit variations in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.  In C. elegans the M lineage is a postembryonic mesodermal lineage.

label: plugged on body
description: Males receive copulatory plugs from other males, deposited elsewhere on their bodies, in the absence of any orifice. This typically involves penetration of the depositing male's spicules directly through the cuticle of the recipient male.

label: mating plug production variant
description: Males differ from control animals in their ability to form copulatory plugs or their placement of these plugs. In C. elegans, males of the Hawaiian strain (CB4856) typically form mating plugs.

label: dietary sugar response variant
description: Animals exhibit enhanced negative effects on growth, health, development or metabolism, in response to dietary sugar-rich diets, compared to controls.

label: cloacal development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the epithelial chamber that links the genital and alimentary tracts to the exterior via the anus (cloacal opening) over time compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: alimentary system development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the alimentary system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control. The alimentary system includes all the body structures involved in preparing food for absorption into the body and excretion of waste products.

label: protein carbonylation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the covalent modification of one or more native amino acid side chains in proteins to carbonyl derivatives such as an aldehyde or ketone.

label: lineage variant
description: The descendants of a particular precursor cell exhibit variations in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: anus development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the caudal opening of the rectum in the tail over time compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: food absorption rate variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the rate at which food is absorbed by the intestine, as determined by a time-course recording of fat staining (by C1-BODIPY-C12, for example) normalized to controls

label: P lineages variant
description: The descendants of any of the P precursor cells exhibit variations in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: acute functional tolerance to alcohol defective
description: Animals do not develop acute functional tolerance to alcohol after a short exposure, unlike that observed in control animals

label: dauer lifespan extended
description: The life span of dauer-staged animals is longer than that observed in control dauer animals.

label: dauer lifespan variant
description: The life span of dauer-staged animals is either longer or shorter than that observed in control dauer animals.

label: dauer lifespan shortened
description: The life span of dauer-staged animals is shorter than that observed in control dauer animals.

label: AB lineage variant
description: The descendants of the AB blastomere exhibit variations in developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: pharyngeal intestinal valve development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the cells that form a narrow passage connecting the posterior bulb of the pharynx to the anterior intestine over time compared to control. In C. elegans this valve is composed of 3 pairs of cells each forming a flattened disc-like ring and is lined by a layer of cuticle (Wormatlas).

label: plugged excretory pore
description: Males receive copulatory plugs from other males, deposited on their excretory pores. This phenotype is polymorphic among C. elegans strains and also in C. briggsae.

label: fat associated body size decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the size of fat containing organelles compared to control. In C. elegans this can be assayed by BODIPY 493/503 staining.

label: organism osmostic stress hypersensitive
description: Animals exhibit hypersensitivty to osmotic stress compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism osmotic stress response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to osmotic stress compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism osmostic stress resistant
description: Animals exhibit resistance to osmotic stress compared to that observed in control animals.

label: head bend angle decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of the maximum flex of the most anterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: head bend angle variant
description: Any variation in the extent of the maximum flex of the most anterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: head movement variant
description: The anterior portion of the animal exhibits variations in its movement compared to control.

label: autophagy reduced
description: Animals exhibit reduced levels of the process by which their cells digest parts of their own cytoplasm, compared to control.

label: autophagy variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the process by which their cells digest parts of their own cytoplasm, compared to control.

label: autophagy increased
description: Animals exhibit increased levels of the process by which their cells digest parts of their own cytoplasm, compared to control.

label: tail bend angle increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of the maximum flex of the most posterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: tail movement variant
description: The most posterior portion of the animal exhibits variations in its movement compared to control.

label: localized movement variant
description: Specific body regions of an animal display variations in movement compared to that observed in control animals.

label: head bend angle increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of the maximum flex of the most anterior portion of the animal compared to control animals.

label: rhythmic tolerance to osmotic stress variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in light/dark cycle recurrence of reactions to osmotic stress compared to that observed for control animals.

label: rhythmic tolerance to stress variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in light/dark cycle recurrence of reactions to stress conditions compared to that observed for control animals.

label: male fertility reduced
description: Males exhibit a reduction in the production of new individuals owing to defects in sperm competence and/or function compared to control animals.

label: male fertility variant
description: Males exhibit variations in the time of onset or duration of the fertile period owing to differences in sperm competence and/or function compared to control animals.

label: nonstriated muscle development variant
description: Variations in the progression of muscle cells that lack transverse striations in its constituent fibers and are almost always involuntary, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: germ cell arrest
description: Germ cells fail to undergo meiotic differentiation to form mature gametes.

label: germline proliferation variant
description: Nuclear divisions in the germ line are either expanded are reduced compared to control.

label: pirouette variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in turning bouts, consisting of one or more sharp turning events separating consecutive runs, which serve to orient the animal within a gradient, compared to control.

label: locomotory rhythm variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in locomotor activity during its light/dark cycle from that observed in control animals.

label: rhythmic behavior variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in actions or responses that occur with measurable periodicity, from that observed for control animals.

label: embryonic arrest
description: Cessation of development during any stage occurring after fertilization and until hatching compared to control.

label: circadian rhythm behavior variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the actions or reactions that recur with a periodicity associated with light/dark cycles, compared to control.

label: early elongation arrest
description: Cessation of development during the initial period of elongation. In C. elegans, this period refers to the conversion of the bean-shaped embryo into the two-fold- shaped embryo.

label: amphid sheath cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for a amphid sheath cell to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: amphid physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for an amphid to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: instantaneous velocity variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the mean translocation of the points along the animal's track compared to control.

label: centroid velocity variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the translocation of the mean position of the rear two-thirds (centroid position) of the animal over time, from that observed for control animals.

label: forward point velocity variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the velocity of forward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: paralyzed body
description: All parts of the animal are immobilized except for the head.

label: paralyzed
description: Animals do not move and are not responsive to external mechanical stimulation.

label: pirouette frequency variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the number of directional changes over time from that observed for control animals.

label: unfolded protein response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any of the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of the presence of unfolded proteins in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) and or the mitochondria, compared to control. One such response is the increase in expression of chaperones.

label: G1 checkpoint variant
description: Mitotic cells exhibit variations during the passage through a cell cycle control point late in the G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle just before entry into S phase, compared to control cells.

label: DNA damage checkpoint variant
description: Mitotic cells exhibit variations in the execution of cell-cycle arrest in response to DNA damage.

label: pathogen infected pharynx variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the extent of pathogen invasion into the pharynx compared to control. This is often measured as the percentage of animals exhibiting a pathogen-invaded pharynx within a given population.

label: spermatozoa retro location defective
description: Spermatozoa do not crawl back into the spermatheca after being swept into the uterus by passing oocytes.

label: hermaphrodite sperm fertilization defective
description: Any perturbation that renders hermaphrodite derived sperm incompetent at fertilizing an oocyte.

label: G2 checkpoint variant
description: Mitotic cells exhibit variations during the passage through a cell cycle control point late in the G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle just before entry into M phase, nuclear division, compared to control cells.

label: amphid sheath cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a sheath cell of the amphid sensillum over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: tunicamycin hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to tunicamycin at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: tunicamycin response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of tunicamycin compared to that observed in control animals. Tunicamycin induces the unfolded protein response.

label: chemosensory neuron development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a chemosensory neuron over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: pathogen infected pharynx decrease
description: Animals exhibit a lesser extent of pathogen invasion into the pharynx compared to control.

label: S phase checkpoint variant
description: Mitotic cells exhibit variations during the passage through a cell cycle control point late in the S phase of the mitotic cell cycle, which ensures DNA replication is complete, compared to control cells.

label: pathogen infected pharynx increase
description: Animals exhibit a greater extent of pathogen invasion into the pharynx compared to control.

label: mating plug produced
description: Males form copulatory mating plugs.

label: telomere length regulation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the processes that are required to maintain the length of telomeric DNA from generation to generation compared to control.

label: telomere homeostasis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the processes that affect and monitor the activity of telomeric proteins and the length of telomeric DNA, which allow the chromosome to persist from generation to generation, compared to control.

label: axon development variant
description: Any variation in the processes that influence the generation of neuronal extensions, that carry efferent (outgoing) action potentials from the cell body towards target cells compared to control.

label: cilia mislocalized
description: Animals exhibit variations in the placement of the microtuble-based dendritic projections in relation to the sensillum neuron, from that observed in control animals.

label: ciliated neuron morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of any one of the specialized sensory receptor cells of the nervous system that compared to control animals. In C. elegans, these specialized cells are characterized as having axoneme containing dendritic projections emanating from their cell body.

label: Z4 hermaphrodite lineage variant
description: Z4 descendants exhibit altered developmental programs in the hermaphrodite compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: hermaphrodite gonadal lineage variant
description: The descendants of a gonadal precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs in the hermaphrodite compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: Z1 male lineage variant
description: Z1 descendents exhibit altered developmental programs in the male compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: male gonadal lineage variant
description: The descendants of a gonadal precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs in the male compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: serotonin induced pumping variant
description: Pharyngeal pumping is not influenced by serotonin treatment in the same manner as control animals.

label: induced pharyngeal pumping variant
description: Pharyngeal pumping is not influenced by treatment with specific compounds (eg: serotonin) in the same manner as control animals.

label: levamisole response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of levamisole compared to that observed in control animals. Levamisole is a cholinergic agonist.

label: Z4 male lineage variant
description: Z4 descendants exhibit altered developmental programs in the male compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: sensory system variant
description: Variations in the progression of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the sensory system over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals. The sensory system is involved in the perception of a stimuli, its conversion into a signal and the recognition and characterization of the resulting signal.

label: presynaptic region physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process in the region of the vesicle-filled varicosities of the synapse compared to control.

label: presynaptic component localization variant
description: Animals display variations in the distribution of the constituents that make up the synaptic machinery such as those required for priming, docking or fusion of vesicles at the active zone, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: ciliated neuron physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the ciliated neuron to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: coelomocyte development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a free-floating spherical cell lying in the pseudocoelomic cavity of animals that can endocytose many compounds, possibly for immune surveillance, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: coelomic system development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the coelomic system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: touch resistant anterior body
description: Animal does not respond to stroking in the anterior body region with a hair or similar fiber compared to control. In C. elegans, the anterior region is defined as the body region that lies between the posterior bulb of the pharynx and the vulva.

label: touch resistant
description: Variations in characteristic response with respect to perception or transmission of a touch stimulus compared to responses in control animals.

label: pseudocoelom development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the fluid-filled space which separates the body wall from internal organs over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: pericellular component development variant
description: Variations in the progression of structures/tissues surrounding a cell over time from its initial formation to its mature form compared to control.

label: directionality variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the directional changes that separate consecutive runs, from that observed for control animals. In C. elegans, these aberrations include variations in the form or extent of omega turns or reversals (shifts from forward to backward movements).

label: excretory gland cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a gland cell of the secretory-excretory system over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: excretory secretory system development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the excretory secretory system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control. The excretory secretory system consists of the excretory system and its associated glands.

label: gland cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a gland cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: intraflagellar transport variant
description: Variations in the bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum, compared to control.

label: intraflagellar transport defective
description: Bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum is disrupted.

label: swimming variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in movement in liquid from that observed for control animals.

label: movement variant
description: Variations in the process by which an organism travels from one location to another compared to control.

label: excretory socket cell development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an interfacial epithelial cell which links excretory duct to hypodermis, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: excretory system development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the excretory system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The excretory system is required for the elimination of metabolic waste. In C. elegans, the excretory system is comprised of the excretory cell, excretory duct cell and excretory socket cell.

label: nuclear import defective
description: The directed movement of substances into the nucleus is impaired.

label: nucleocytoplasmic transport defective
description: The directed movement of molecules between the nucleus and the cytoplasm is impaired.

label: nuclear export defective
description: The directed movement of substances out of the nucleus is impaired.

label: excretory cell development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a protokidney cell with an internal lumen that is suggested to collect and secrete salt solutions outward via the excretory sinus, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: excretory duct cell development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an interfacial epithelial cell which forms a lumen to receive the outflow of the excretory gland and excretory canal cells, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: multiple alae
description: Alae contain more cuticular ridges than control animals. In C. elegans alae are composed of three cuticular ridges.

label: protein export from nucleus defective
description: The directed movement of a protein from the nucleus into the cytoplasm is impaired.

label: sex determination variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern the sexually dimorphic development of germline or somatic tissue compared to control.

label: germ cell development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the immature germ cell over time, from its formation from precursors to the mature structure (gamete) compared to control.

label: embryonic behavior variant
description: Activity characteristic of an embryo is altered compared to control.

label: developmental behavior variant
description: Any variation in the behavior characteristic during certain developmental stage(s) compared to control.

label: sexually dimorphic behavior variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in sex-specific behaviors compared to control.

label: H lineages variant
description: The descendants of H1 or H2 cells exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: V lineages variant
description: The descendants of any of the V precursor cells (V1-V6) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: T lineages variant
description: The descendants of TL or TR cells exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: Q lineage variant
description: The descendants of Q L or QR cells exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: B lineage variant
description: The descendants of the B cell (which divides only in the males) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: U lineage variant
description: The descendants of the U cell (which divides only in the males) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: E lineage variant
description: The descendants of the E blastomere exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: Y lineage variant
description: The descendants of the Y cell (which divides only in the males) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: C lineage variant
description: The descendants of the C blastomere exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: gonadal lineage variant
description: The descendants of a gonadal precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: F lineage variant
description: The descendants of the F cell (which divides only in the males) exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: Z1 hermaphrodite lineage variant
description: Z1 descendants exhibit altered developmental programs in the hermaphrodite compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: posterior region development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an animal's anatomy contained in the posterior region over time, compared to control animals.

label: ventral region development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an animal's anatomy contained in the ventral region over time, compared to control animals.

label: body development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the overall structure or appearance of the animal over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: tail development variant
description: Any variation in the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the tail over time, from its formation to the mature structure, compared to control. The tail includes the posterior region that spans from the rectum to the end.

label: dorsal region development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an animal's anatomy contained in the dorsal region over time, compared to control animals.

label: head development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the anterior end of the animal over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: K lineage variant
description: The descendants of the K precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: hermaphrodite fertility variant
description: Hermaphrodites exhibit variations in the time of onset or duration of the fertile period, or variations in the production of viable offspring, including number and state of fertilized eggs laid, compared to controls.

label: G lineages variant
description: The descendants of the G1 or G2 exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals.

label: epithelial cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of an epithelial cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: gametogenesis variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern the generation and maintenance of gametes compared to control.

label: blast cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a blast cell (precursor cell) over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: marginal cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of a marginal cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control. A marginal cell is a pharyngeal cell that connects the basement membrane to the apices of the triangle-shaped pharyngeal lumen.

label: postembryonic behavior variant
description: Behavior characteristic of postembryonic stage(s) is altered compared to control.

label: uterine vulval cell development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the epithelial cells that form the interface between the uterus and the vulva (likely via a multilayered set of flaps) over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: adult behavior variant
description: Activity characteristic of an adult worm is altered compared to control.

label: high oxygen hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to hyperoxic (high oxygen tension) conditions after a shorter exposure time compared to control.

label: oxygen response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to oxygen compared to that observed in control animals.

label: inhibition of synaptogenesis defective
description: The processes that inhibit the location or frequency of formation of synapses are downregulated resulting in the formation of synapses or synapse-like structures in areas of the neuron that are typically devoid of synapses in control animals.

label: vulval muscle variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the sex-specific muscles in the hermaphrodite, over time, that are specialized for egg-laying compared to control. In C. elegans the contractions of the vulval muscles open the lips of the vulva to help in expelling an egg from the uterus (Wormatlas).

label: pachytene arrested germline nuclei
description: Germline nuclei do not progress through pachytene to diplotene.

label: pachytene progression during oogenesis variant
description: Developing oocytes show defects in their entry, progression through or exit from the pachytene stage compared to control animals. Pachytene is a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the third stage of prophase I in meiosis, in which crossing over occurs between a chromatid in one partner and another chromatid in the homologous chromosome.

label: uterine muscle variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the sex-specific muscles of the hermaphrodite, over time, whose contractions squeeze on the uterus to help move eggs towards the vulval opening compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: age associated fluorescence increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the intensity of fluorescence signals in intestinal cells with advancing age, compared to control.

label: organism hypersensitive interstrand cross link agents
description: Animals exhibit increased sensitivity to interstrand cross-linking agents, such as HN2 (nitrogen mustard) and CDDP (cisplatin) compared to control. In C. elegans, increased sensitivity to these agents is often observed as a decrease in survival compared to control animals after exposure to the agent.

label: neuron number variant
description: The quantity of neuronal cells, as a whole or of a specific class of neuron in the animal deviates from that observed in control animals.

label: high oxygen resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the high concentrations of oxygen that elicit a response in control animals.

label: microsatellite instability
description: Animals exhibit variations in repeat lengths of microsatellite genomic sequences compared to control.

label: chromosome instability
description: Variations in the frequencies of translocations, inversions, deletions, or gene amplifications and variations in chromosome fusion events and or chromosomal loss compared to control.

label: protein expression reduced hermaphrodite
description: Variations that result in a decrease in protein expression in hermaphrodites compared to that observed in control animals.

label: endogenous synaptic events variant
description: Any variation in the currents observed in the absence of presynaptic action potentials and that are elicited by fusion of a single endogenous vesicle of transmitter compared to control.

label: electrophysiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the electrical properties of any of its cells or tissues compared to control.

label: evoked postsynaptic amplitude reduced
description: The amplitudes of synaptic currents that are elicited by firing an action potential in a population of axons are decreased, compared to those observed in control animals.

label: evoked postsynaptic current variant
description: Variations in the synaptic currents that are elicited by firing an action potential in a population of axons, compared to control.

label: age associated fluorescence reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the intensity of fluorescence signals in intestinal cells with advancing age, compared to control.

label: Q neuroblast lineage migration variant
description: The daughters of the Q neuroblasts exhibit variation in their characteristic movements compared to control animals.

label: neuron migration variant
description: Any variation in the normal orderly movement of neurons from one site to another compared to control.

label: inhibition of synaptogenesis hyperactive
description: The processes that inhibit the location or frequency of formation of synapses are upregulated compared to control.

label: endogenous synaptic event frequency reduced
description: The rate (frequency) of currents elicited by fusion of a single endogenous vesicle of transmitter in the absence of presynaptic action potentials is decreased compared to control. Changes in frequency are indicative of presynaptic modifications.

label: HSN migration variant
description: Any variation in the normal anterior movement of the HSN motor neurons from their birthplace in the tail to positions near the middle of the embryo compared to control animals.

label: anterior neuron migration defective
description: The orderly movement of neurons along the anterior axis of the animal is abolished, misdirected or incomplete compared to control.

label: progressive paralysis
description: Animals become increasingly sluggish/immobilized as they age.

label: synapse morphology variant
description: Animals display variations in the appearance of the subcellular junctional structure composed of a presynaptic terminal directly opposite the post-synaptic target and separated by a synaptic cleft.

label: endogenous synaptic amplitude variant
description: The amplitude (magnitude) of currents elicited by fusion of a single endogenous vesicle of transmitter in the absence of presynaptic action potentials is altered compared to control. Changes in amplitude are often interpreted as alterations of postsynaptic responsiveness to the transmitter.

label: ALM migration variant
description: Any variation in the normal posterior movement of the ALM mechanosensory neurons from their birthplace (anterior to the V1 hypodermal cell) to positions in between the V2 and V3 cells in the embryo compared to control animals.

label: posterior neuron migration variant
description: Any variation in the orderly movement of neurons along the posterior axis of the animal(abolished, misdirected or incomplete) compared to control.

label: endoderm absent
description: Animals lack the early blast cells that give rise to the gut tissue (Wormatlas).

label: nucleolus refraction variant
description: Any variation in the change in direction of a wave of light after passage through the nucleolus compared to control. The nucleolus is a small dense body in the nucleus.

label: nucleolus variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the appearance of nucleoli compared to control animals.

label: backing not sustained
description: Animals initiate but do not continue backward movement, similar to control animals.

label: backward locomotion variant
description: Variations in the spontaneous or induced backward crawling locomotion of an animal compared to control.

label: vesicle morphology variant
description: Animals display variations in the shape or size of their vesicles, which are spherical, membrane-bound fluid-filled organelles, compared to vesicles observed in control animals.

label: vesicle organization variant
description: Animals display variations in the distribution of spherical membrane-bound fluid-filled organelles, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: muscle detached
description: Animals fail to establish or maintain the connection between cell(s) whose principal function is to provide contractile forces and its neighboring cells or tissues.

label: progressive muscle detachment
description: The connection between cell(s) whose principal function is to provide contractile forces and its neighboring cells or tissues diminishes over time.

label: vesicle number reduced
description: Total presynaptic vesicle number is reduced, possibly refecting a defect in the replenishment of synaptic vesicles compared to control.

label: vesicle number variant
description: Animals display variations in the number of spherical membrane-bound fluid-filled organelles, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: curly
description: Animals exhibit a greater number of bends in their body compared to control. C. elegans posture assumes more than a single sine wave.

label: posterior body dumpy
description: The posterior part of the worm is shorter and stouter compared to control animals.

label: posterior body morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the anatomy contained in the posterior region, compared to control animals.

label: cell gamma ray hypersensitive
description: Cells respond to a lower dosage of gamma rays or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: egg pale
description: Eggs show deficiencies in chroma resulting in increased translucency.

label: pyrazine chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to pyrazine as defined by control animals. In C. elegans pyrazine is typically an attractant.

label: pyrazine chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of pyrazine. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, pyrazine is an attractant.

label: embryo small
description: The organism's size during the embryonic developmental stage is decreased compared to that observed in control.

label: embryonic morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts during any developmental stage ranging from zygote formation to hatching compared to control.

label: motor neuron morphology variant
description: Animals display variations in the structure or organization of components of the motor neuron, internal to the cell itself or in relation to the cellular environment compared to that observed in control animals. A motor neuron is a neuronal cell that synapses to an effector (muscle, gland etc.).

label: dauer death increased
description: The survival of animals in the alternative larval stage which they enter when placed under conditions of environmental stress is reduced.

label: dauer arrest variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the entry/exit into a state of arrested tissue development during the dauer larval stage in response to harsh environmental conditions, compared to control. In C. elegans, the dauer larva enters a state of arrest in which no developmental changes occur, until the animal finds more suitable growing conditions, or until it spontaneously shifts back into a normal developmental schedule. (WormAtlas).

label: egg laying event infrequent
description: The rate of the intrinsic behavioral program that serves to move fertilized eggs down the uterus, through the vulva, and out of the worm onto the substrate is reduced compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: egg laying irregular
description: The rate of the intrinsic behavioral program that serves to move fertilized eggs down the uterus, through the vulva, and out of the worm onto the substrate does not conform to the pattern observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: garlic chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to garlic as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, garlic is typically a repellent.

label: no gut granules
description: Animals lack the different inclusions within the intestinal cytoplasm, including birefringent crystalline objects and other dark-staining endosomes. In C. elegans these contents typically include glycogen granules (polysaccharide storage), rhabditin (carbohydrate storage), yolk granules (lipid and protein), and concentrated waste products (Wormatlas).

label: bursa elongated
description: The length of the adult male tail, including the lateral fan and rays, is extended compared to control.

label: siRNA expression variant
description: Variations in the biogenesis and stability of the small interfering class of RNA molecules compared to control. In C. elegans these molecules are antisense to mRNA's and may be processed from long double-stranded RNA.

label: hormetic temperature induced life span extension defective
description: Pre-treatment with stress-inducing temperatures does not result in a life-span extension as it does in control animals.

label: organism temperature response variant
description: Animals do not respond to changes in temperature or thermal stress in the same manner as control animals. In C.elegans this is often measured by changes in the expression of stress proteins or changes in life span.

label: yolk synthesis in males
description: Males generate yolk, the nutrient protein, normally produced and secreted by hermaphrodite or female intestinal cells.

label: yolk synthesis variant
description: Variations in the generation of the nutrient protein produced by intestinal cells and secreted by them into the pseudocoelom, from which it can be shared with other tissues in the body compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: gut on the exterior
description: An epidermal enclosure defect that results in internal organs lying on the outside of the embryo.

label: larval development retarded
description: The developmental progression of a larva over time, from its formation to its mature structure is delayed compared to control. The larva is the early, immature form of an animal between hatching and adulthood.

label: spicule morphology variant
description: Any variation in the appearance of the elongated sclerotized structures covered by a hardened layer of cuticle in the male tail (which are actively everted during copulation to fasten the male copulatory fan to the vulva) compared to control.

label: enhanced locomotion defective
description: Animals do not exhibit an increase in speed when placed in an environment that relies on a combination of swimming and crawling behaviors compared to control.

label: adult cuticle development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the formation of the rigid external coating (which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells) over time in adults compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: adult development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an animal over time from the end of larval stage to a mature adult compared to control animals.

label: miRNA expression variant
description: Variations in the biogenesis or stability of the microRNA class of molecules compared to control. In C. elegans these molecules are endogenous single-stranded regulatory molecules, 19-25 nucleotides long, with the potential to arise from hairpin, foldback, structures from their primary transcripts.

label: second adult cuticle
description: A duplication of the developmental program that forms the adult-type rigid external coating which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells.

label: nuclear RNAi defective
description: Animals fail to silence nuclear-localized RNAs. Animals still retain sensitivity to RNAi for those RNAs located outside of the nucleus.

label: supernumerary molt
description: Animals execute extra larval molts compared to control.

label: molt variant
description: Animals exhibit variation in timing or ability to molt.

label: pre mRNA levels increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the levels of nuclear mRNA species compared to control.

label: head protrusion
description: Any irregular swelling in discrete regions of the head.

label: ligand gated channel activity variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the actions of a channel that catalyses the transmembrane transfer of a cation when acetylcholine has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts compared to control animals.

label: acetylcholine synaptic transmission variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the process of acetylcholine neurotransmitter-based communication from a neuron to a target cell across a synapse compared to control.

label: anoxia response attenuated
description: Response to trace levels of oxygen is reduced or weakened compared to the response of control animals.

label: tail protrusions
description: Any irregular swelling in discrete regions of the tail, usually caused by a local defect in the normal smooth tapering of the hypodermis and/or cuticle (Wormatlas).

label: hypersensitivity to mutagen
description: Animals are more susceptible than control animals to the effects of a nucleic acid damaging agent. This increased susceptibility is often measured by an increase in the rate of spontaneous mutations or an increased lethality.

label: associative learning variant
description: Variations in the behavioral plasticity induced by the integration of two sensory signals compared to control. In C. elegans animals exhibit enhancement of butanone chemotaxis by preexposure to butanone and food.

label: jerky movement
description: Animals exhibit abrupt transitions while traveling from one location to another.

label: phototaxis defective
description: Animals do not respond via directed movement to light stimuli in the same manner as control animals. In C. elegans, animals move away from light.

label: cell differentiation variant
description: Variations in the processes leading to the specialization of cell. Differentiation impacts diverse cellular properties such as size, shape, polarity, gene expression and responsiveness to signals/cues.

label: neuronal ion channel clustering defective
description: Animals exhibit variations in the targeting, clustering and or maintenance of ion channels in distinct subcellular domains of the neuron compared to control animals.

label: P granule localization defective
description: The restricted localization of P granules to germ cells or germ cell precursors is altered compared to control.

label: P granule defective
description: Localization or structural appearance of P-granules is altered compared to control. P-granules are cytoplasmic structures associated with germ nuclei in the C. elegans gonad, and are localized exclusively to germ cells, or germ cell precursors, throughout the life cycle.

label: memory retention defective
description: Animals are deficient in their recalled and repeated responses to stimuli they are exposed to during learning and memory paradigms.

label: germ cell cytoplasmic morphology variant
description: Any variation in the composition or structure of the contents within a germ cell, excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, compared to control. Germ cells include sperm, oocytes, and their precursors.

label: body protrusions
description: Any irregular swelling in discrete regions of the body region between the head and the tail.

label: head twisted
description: The anterior end (which typically includes the anterior sensilla, pharynx and all muscles that are innervated by the nerve ring)of the body appears distorted, usually due to uncharacteristic winding.

label: lysosome homeostasis deficient
description: Animals are deficient in the formation or disassembly of lysosomes.

label: reduced body bend
description: The maximum ventral and dorsal flex of the animal is reduced compared to that observed for control animals.

label: male reproductive system morphology variant
description: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the male reproductive system compared to control. The reproductive system is involved in the generation of progeny which contain genetic material inherited from the parents.

label: temperature influenced life span variant
description: Life span of the animal is not influenced by changes in temperature in the same manner as control animals.

label: hook morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of the structure that lies on the ventral surface just anterior and central to the base of the spicule openings (small lump on the gubernaculum of the male tail) and contains a sensory structure called the hook sensillum, compared to control. In C. elegans the hook is necessary for proper male mating.

label: organism starvation hypersensitive
description: Animals show enhanced suceptibility to deprivation of nourishment, compared to control.

label: starvation resistant
description: Animals show enhanced tolerance to deprivation of nourishment, compared to control.

label: resistant to mutagens
description: Animals survive longer than control animals after or during exposure to DNA damaging agents.

label: DNA damage response variant
description: Variations in the activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating damage to its DNA from environmental insults or errors during metabolism, compared to control.

label: hindgut damaged
description: The terminal portion of the intestine exhibits structural defects such as scarring or blockage.

label: hindgut morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the more posterior portion of the intestine, just anterior to the sphincter valve, which is subject to squeezing by the somatal-intestinal muscles compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: amplitude of sinusoidal movement decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of a vibratory movement (as a worm bend) measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control.

label: weak pumping
description: The contraction and relaxation movements of the pharyngeal muscle that mediate feeding is not as robust as compared to control animals.

label: thermoreceptor currents absent
description: Cooling or warming evoked changes in membrane currents are not observed.

label: paraquat hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to paraquat at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: paraquat response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to paraquat compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cytoplasmic processing body variant
description: Discrete foci within the cytoplasm containing congregations of mRNA translational suppression and degradation mechanisms vary in their arrangement, clustering or are otherwise not well-defined compared to control.

label: neuron positioning variant
description: The placement of neuronal cells, as a whole or of a specific class of neuron in the animal, deviates from that observed in control animals.

label: aboc expulsion missing
description: The anterior body contraction and expulsion steps of the defecation cycle are absent; posterior body contractions are still present.

label: defecation missing motor steps
description: Animals lack one or more of the stereotyped muscle contractions that result in defecation compared to control. In C. elegans these contractions include posterior body contraction (pBoc), anterior body contraction (aBoc), expulsion of gut contents by enteric muscle contraction (Emc) and opening of anus (Exp).

label: nuclei small
description: Nuclei of specific cells are smaller compared to control animals.

label: organism oxidative stress response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to oxidative stress compared to that observed in control animals.

label: paraquat resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of paraquat that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: defecation cycle temperature compensation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in temperature dependent differences in the length of their defecation cycle. In C. elegans the length of the cycle is the same at different temperatures, showing temperature compensation.

label: twitcher
description: Animals exhibit spasmodic muscle twitching superimposed on normal sinusoidal motion.

label: endosome to lysosome trafficking defective
description: Contents of endosomes fail to be transported to lysosomal compartments.

label: coelomocyte uptake increased
description: Animals exhibit intensified accumulation of fluids or fluorescent markers etc. within their coelomocytes compared to control animals.

label: head muscle contraction variant
description: Any variation in the contractions of the muscles in the most anterior body region of the animal compared to control.

label: vesicle trafficking variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in vesicle-based directed movement of substances into, out of, or within a cell compared to control.

label: levamisole hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to levamisole at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. Levamisole is a cholinergic agonist.

label: cholinergic agonist hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to a cholinergic agonist at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: cholinergic agonist resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of cholinergic agonist that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: organism hypertonic lethality increased
description: Animals exhibit increased lethality as a result of exposure to environments with a higher solute concentration than their own internal environment, compared to control.

label: stress induced lethality increased
description: Animal populations exhibit a further decrease in survival when exposed to stress stimuli compared to the lethality rate observed in control animals.

label: antibody staining increased
description: Any variation that results in an increase in the characteristic expression of a gene product, as detected by antibody staining, compared to control animals.

label: neuropeptide processing variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways involved in the formation and maturation of specialized peptidergic neurotransmitters encoded as preproproteins that are posttranslationally processed to yield bioactive neuropeptides compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: neuropeptide metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of signalling peptides in the organism compared to control.

label: no cuticle
description: Animals lack the rigid external coating which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells (Wormatlas).

label: UV induced apoptosis decreased
description: Programmed cell death caused by UV radiation is reduced compared to control animals. In C. elegans, this is often measured in the pachytene region of the gonad.

label: antibody staining reduced
