description: Any variation that results in a decrease in the characteristic expression of a gene product, as detected by antibody staining, compared to control animals.

label: UV induced mitotic germ cell arrest defective
description: Animals do not arrest mitotic germ cell division, as control animals, when treated with UV radiation.

label: no adult cuticle
description: Adult animals lack the rigid external coating which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells (Wormatlas).

label: copulatory structure development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the specialized structures of the animal which allow the successful transfer of sperm from one organism to another, compared to control.

label: reproductive system development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the reproductive system over time, from its formation to its mature state compared to control.

label: 21U RNA expression variant
description: Variations in the biogenesis or stability of the 21U-RNA class of molecules compared to control. Molecules are classified as 21U-RNA based on the presence of a 5'U and a conserved upstream motif, which may specify the production of these molecules, in addition these molecules are typically 21nt in length.

label: axon midline crossing variant
description: Regulated ventral midline crossing by axons vary either in the frequency of crossing events or the maintenance through development of process positions compared to control.

label: axon guidance variant
description: Variations in the cue-directed extension of an axon towards a specific target site compared to control. (Axon guidance often depends on a combination of attractive and repulsive cues).

label: G tract instability
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the rate of deletion events in mono-G or G-rich tracts within the genome compared to control.

label: male copulatory structure development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the specialized structures of the male tail which allow the animal to sense the presence of the hermaphrodite, search her body for the vulval opening, grasp onto the vulva, and to transfer sperm over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: DNA synthesis variant
description: Variations in the processes involving the production of new DNA strands compared to control.

label: carbon dioxide avoidance variant
description: Variations in the characteristic movement away from specific CO2 levels compared to control. C. elegans avoids high levels of CO2.

label: carbon dioxide response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to carbon dioxide compared to control.

label: sexual maturation defective
description: The developmental process by which a progressive change in the state of some part of an organism specifically contributing to its ability to form offspring is impaired.

label: uptake by intestinal cell defective
description: Uptake of subtances from the intestine is altered from that observed in control animals.

label: hermaphrodite copulatory structure development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the specialized structures of a hermaphrodite which allow the successful transfer of sperm from a male, compared to control.

label: male copulatory structure absent
description: Animals lack the specialized structures of the male tail which allow the animal to sense the presence of the hermaphrodite, search her body for the vulval opening, grasp onto the vulva, and to transfer sperm (Wormatlas).

label: uptake of yolk defective
description: Yolk is not taken up by oocytes in the same manner or to the same degree as observed for control animals. This often leads to an accumulation of yolk in the pseudocoelom.

label: cytoplasmic RNAi defective
description: Animals fail to silence cytoplasmic-localized RNAs. Nuclear-localized RNAs may still be sensitive to RNAi.

label: commissure number variant
description: Variations in the quantity of circumferential axonal tracts from the number observed in control animals.

label: commissure handedness defective
description: Outgrowth of the commissure occurs on the side of the body different from that observed in control animals.

label: axon trajectory variant
description: Animals display variations in the directed path taken by the axon compared to the path the nerve fiber follows in the nervous system in control animals.

label: protein subcellular localization variant
description: Any variation in the placement of a protein within in a cell or cellular compartment compared to control.

label: cholesterol depletion hypersensitive
description: Animals are more sensitive to the reduction of cholesterol in the environment compared to control animals.

label: excretory canals long
description: The structure made by the processes of the excretory canal cell is increased in size compared to control. In C. elegans this is an H-shaped structure which extends almost the full length of the body on both sides of the animal, generally in contact with the lateral hypodermis and the pseudocoelom (Wormatlas).

label: endogenous transposase levels increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the levels of transposase mRNA, from endogenous transposons, over that measured in control animals.

label: transposon silencing variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the activity of endogenous transposons compared to control. In C. elegans transposon activity is often measured by the rate of reversion of mutations induced by transposon insertions.

label: endo siRNA production variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the length or amount of any endogenous small interfering RNA molecule populations compared to control.

label: tail rounded
description: Tails change shape and undergo retraction thereby forming a 'peloderan' or 'rounded' adult tail.

label: endo siRNA binding variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their selective interactions with small interfering RNA molecules compared to control.

label: somatic gonad primordium development defective
description: The developmental progression of the set of precursor cells that later give rise to the somatic tissues of the gonadal tract is impaired (Wormatlas).

label: AWB morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of either of a set of two ciliated wing neurons, AWBL or AWBR, of the amphid sensilla, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: organism response to pH variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response and ability to survive over a range of pH conditions compared to control.

label: thermal bias in tracking variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the duration of the trajectory of the forward track in a thermal gradient compared to control.

label: no uterus
description: Animals lack the portion of the somatic gonad which encloses the fertilized eggs after their passage through the spermatheca (Wormatlas).

label: mating plug deficient
description: Males do not form copulatory mating plug.

label: nerve ring development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the major zone of overlapping axons in the head, which encircles the isthmus of the pharynx to form a tightly packed ring-like structure on the outside of the pharynx, over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals.

label: delayed hatching
description: The emergence of larvae from their protective egg shells is retarded compared to control animals.

label: male behavior variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in male-specific behaviors compared to control.

label: acetate chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to acetate compared to control animals.

label: muscle cell activity variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction compared to control animals.

label: giant oocytes
description: The size of haploid female germ cells (oocytes) are significantly larger compared to control.

label: oocyte morphology variant
description: Haploid female germ cells (oocytes) exhibit variations in their overall structure, appearance or contents compared to control.

label: starvation suppressed pumping defective
description: Animals deprived of food do not exhibit a decrease in pumping rate similar to that observed for control animals.

label: suppressed pharyngeal pumping defective
description: Animals do not exhibit a decrease in pumping rate when treated with specific compounds (such as pheromones) as is observed for control animals.

label: avoids bacterial lawn
description: Lawn avoidance refers to behavior in which animals initially enter the bacterial lawn but later exit and remain near the edge of the bacteria. Lawn avoidance is often a response to bacterial food, that is pathogenic or low quality to the animal.

label: sperm transfer initiation defective
description: Any defect in the movement of sperm out of the seminal vesicle and into the vas deferens following tonic insertion of spicules into the mating partner compared to control.

label: pheromone suppressed pumping defective
description: Animals treated with pheromone do not exhibit a decrease in pumping rate similar to that observed for control animals.

label: dauer recovery inhibited
description: The process through which a dauer larva reverts to normal developmental programs is blocked.

label: dauer recovery variant
description: Characteristic exit from the dauer stage is altered compared to control animals.

label: aging variant
description: Any variation in an organism's decline over time from its optimal fertility and viability compared to control animals.

label: organism morphology variable
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts at different stages of the lifecycle, compared to control animals.

label: ammonium chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to ammonium compared to control animals.

label: lumpy
description: Animals have protrusions or bumps on their exterior which are not characteristic of control animals.

label: aqueous compound discrimination defective
description: Animals are unable to locate the gradient peak of a water soluble compound, which was generated on a uniform concentration of another compound.

label: clear adult
description: Adult animals appear unusually transparent when compared to control.

label: clear
description: Animals appear unusually transparent when compared to control.

label: hermaphrodite germline proliferation variant
description: Nuclear divisions in the germ line of hermaphrodites are either expanded are reduced compared to control.

label: larval pigmentation variant
description: Larva exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter its transparency/translucency compared to control animals.

label: rod like larval lethal
description: Animals die as rigid, rod-like larva. In C. elegans this defect is often caused by the misspecification of the excretory duct cell.

label: lipid synthesis increased
description: The endogenous anabolism of any lipid species has been increased compared to that observed in control animals.

label: octanol chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to 1-octanol as defined by control animals. In C.elegans 1-octanol is typically a repellant.

label: spontaneous spicule protraction
description: Males exhibit spicule-muscle seizures leading to inappropriately timed protraction compared to control.

label: male germline proliferation variant
description: Nuclear divisions in the germ line of male animals are either expanded are reduced compared to control.

label: no defecation cycle
description: Animals lack the stereotyped sequence of muscle contractions that result in defecation over a fixed time period compared to control.

label: germ cell differentiation variant
description: Variations in the ability of a relatively unspecialized cell to acquire the specialized features of a mature gamete compared to control.

label: organ senescence variant
description: Any variation in the preprogrammed process that occurs in an organism that is associated with the dismantling of an organ and an overall decline in metabolic function compared to control animals. This may include variations in the rate or extent of morphological disarray and of the breakdown or organelles, membranes and other cellular components.

label: epithelial cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of epithelial cells compared to control animals.

label: zinc response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a zinc ion stimulus compared to control.

label: tight junction defective
description: Any perturbation in the belt-like region of very close contact between the plasma membranes of adjacent cells that results in the complete occlusion of the intercellular space.

label: intercellular junction variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the specialized region of connection between two cells compared to control.

label: adherens junction variant
description: Any variation in a cell junction at which the cytoplasmic face of the plasma membrane is attached to actin filaments compared to control.

label: pharyngeal muscle paralyzed
description: Pharyngeal muscle is immobilized resulting in lack of pumping or lack of response to external stimulation.

label: connective tissue development variant
description: Variations in the material made up of fibers forming a framework and support structure for body tissues and organs compared to control.

label: cell fate transformation
description: The cell takes on a different identity from which it was initially committed.

label: blast cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of blast cells compared to control animals.

label: cell adhesion variant
description: Any variation in the attachment of a cell, either to another cell or to an underlying substrate such as the extracellular matrix compared to control.

label: cell junction variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the specialized region of connection between two cells or between a cell and the extracellular matrix compared to control.

label: L3 lethal
description: Animals die at the L3 stage of the life cycle.

label: zinc toxicity hypersensitive
description: The toxic response to zinc occurs at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. In C. elegans hypersensitive animals exhibit delayed development or lethality at concentrations of zinc (e.g. ZnSO4), which has little or no effect on control worms.

label: cell division failure
description: The process of physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells is abolished.

label: intestinal cell division failure
description: The physical partitioning and separation of an intestinal cell into daughter cells is abolished.

label: zinc toxicity resistant
description: Animals fail to exhibit toxicity to the concentration of zinc that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans toxic responses to zinc include delayed development or lethality.

label: leaving assay defective
description: Males remain on food in the absence of mates, a defect in male mate-searching behavior observed in control males.

label: lawn leaving behavior variant
description: Variation of the time an individual spent on a patch of food (bacterial lawn) before leaving, compared to control animals.

label: intraflagellar transport velocity variant
description: Animals exhibit variation rate of directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in nerve cell axons, compared to control.

label: transgene expression reduced male
description: Any decrease in the intensity of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA, exclusively in the male, that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: intestinal fluorescence decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that fluoresce in the intestine.

label: alimentary system pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of the alimentary system.

label: growth inhibition response to chemical
description: Animals do not grow fast or the quality of growth is decreased when exposed to a specific chemical compound when compared to control animals.

label: mitochondrial DNA copy number variant
description: Relative levels of mtDNA differ from that observed for control animals.

label: transgene expression reduced hermaphrodite
description: Any decrease in the intensity of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA, exclusively in the hermaphrodite, that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: coenzyme Q depleted
description: Animals contain a lower level of coenzyme Q, an oil-soluble vitamin-like substance present in most eukaryotic cells, primarily in the mitochondria, compared to control. It is a component of the electron transport chain and participates in aerobic cellular respiration.

label: muscle cell ultrastructure variant
description: Animals display variations in the structure or organization of the components of the muscle, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: post mating variant
description: Males exhibit variations of the behaviors observed in control animals that follow the completion of mating.

label: stuffed pharynx
description: Pharynx becomes clogged with food. In C. elegans, this is often a result of pharyngeal pumping defects.

label: feeding inefficient
description: Animals are unable to ingest nutrients at a rate similar to control animals.

label: organism predator response variant
description: Predator-prey interactions differ from that observed in control interactions.

label: predator escape defective
description: Animals are less successful than controls in evading predators during predator-prey interactions.

label: food suppressed pumping variant
description: Exposure to food does not reduce pharyngeal pumping to the same extent as observed in control animals.

label: response to food variant
description: Any variation in the state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) in response to a food stimulus, compared to control.

label: ooplasmic streaming slow
description: The bulk flow of cytoplasm in the egg, that facilitates mixing of ooplasm, occurs at a reduced rate compared to that measured for controls.

label: cytoplasmic streaming defective
description: The directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of, or within the cytoplasm of a cell is impaired.

label: protein complex organization variant
description: The formation, organization, or stability of a protein complex is altered in comparison to corresponding complexes in control animals.

label: linker cell morphology variant
description: Any variation in the morphological appearance of the linker cell compared to control animals.

label: acquired thermotolerance variant
description: Animals are altered in their capacity to survive a normally lethal temperature treatment as a consequence of pretreatment at an elevated but sublethal temperature.

label: reduced translation initiation
description: The rate of the process preceding formation of the peptide bond between the first two amino acids of a protein is reduced. This process includes the formation of a complex of the ribosome, mRNA, and an initiation complex that contains the first aminoacyl-tRNA.  Increase in free ribosomes (monosomes) are indicative of reduced translation initiation.

label: no anchor cell
description: Animals are missing the anchor cell. In C. elegans the anchor cell is a key organizer of vulval patterning and morphogenesis.

label: cell number decreased
description: The number of cells in the organism is reduced compared to control animals.

label: body twisted
description: Any portion of the animal, between the head and the tail, appears distorted, usually due to uncharacteristic winding.

label: mitochondrial respiratory chain variant
description: The activity, composition, or organization of the complexes of the electron transport chain, embedded in the inner mitochondrial membrane, differ from controls.

label: head bent
description: The most anterior portion of the animal is not aligned with the axis of the body.

label: larval physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the larva to carry out its normal metabolic functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: male attraction response variant
description: Males do not respond to small molecules or compounds that have been shown to attract control males. This phenotype is often measured by an increase in reversal frequency or time spent in a specified scoring region

label: body wall muscle physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the body wall muscle system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: cell division variant male
description: Any variation that alters the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells in male animals compared to control.

label: small RNA germline expression variant
description: Animals exhibit variations from controls in the expression, biogenesis, processing, or stability of any class of small RNA species in the germline. Small RNAs include microRNAs (miRNAs), tiny noncoding RNAs (tncRNAs), cluster of small X-chromosome derived RNAs (X cluster), and endogenous short interfering RNA (endo-siRNAs).

label: siRNA processing defective
description: Animals are unable to produce or maintain short interfering RNA (siRNA) from double stranded RNA (dsRNA). siRNAs are required to initiate interference of gene expression.

label: mitochondrial respiratory complex I variant
description: The protein complex located in the mitochondrial inner membrane that is the first entry point for electrons into the electron transport chain and catalyzes proton translocation coupled to the oxidation of NADH by ubiquinone, differs in activity, composition, or organization from that of controls.

label: lannate resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of lannate that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: mitochondrial respiratory complex II variant
description: The part of the respiratory chain that catalyzes the oxidation of succinate and connects the TCA cycle with the respiratory chain, differs in activity, composition, or organization, from that of controls.

label: hermaphrodite fertility reduced
description: Hermaphrodites exhibit a reduction in the production of new individuals owing to defects in gamete competence and/or function compared to control animals.

label: early endosome localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as early endosomes,  that traffic material from endocytic vesicles (having recently internalized portions of the cell's plasma membrane) to internal compartments of the cell, such as recycling endosomes, late endosomes, or the Golgi apparatus, compared to control.

label: endosome localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as endosomes,  that traffic material between the plasma membrane and internal compartments of the cell, compared to control.

label: RNAi enhanced
description: Animals show increased susceptibility to gene silencing triggered by double stranded RNA (RNAi), compared to control.

label: late endosome localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as late endosomes,  that traffic material from early endosomes to internal compartments of the cell, such as lysosomes or the Golgi apparatus, compared to control.

label: cross link induced focus formation variant
description: Variations in the generation of foci that mark sites of aberrant bonding of molecules to the DNA strand, compared to control.

label: recycling endosome localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes,  that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: lysosome localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosomes, that have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell, compared to control.

label: cell component localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of the basic structural and functional components of cells compared to control. Includes the nucleus, endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus, mitochondria, endosomes, lysosomes, and peroxisomes as well as other vesicles and organelles.

label: drug susceptible
description: Animals are affected by exposure to the drug.

label: RAB-11 recycling endosome localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes, positive for the RAB protein RAB-11, that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: vulval development incomplete
description: The developmental progression of the egg-laying organ of female and hermaphrodite nematodes is halted prior to the formation of the mature structure.

label: genetic pathway activation variant
description: Any variation in triggering of the set of interactions occurring between a group of genes who depend on each other's individual functions in order to make the aggregate function of the network available to the cell, compared to control.

label: synapsis formation variant
description: Animals differ from controls in respect to the formation of paired chromosome loci.

label: synapsis maintenance defective
description: Animals are unable to maintain paired chromosome throughout pachytene.

label: peroxisome physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the peroxisome to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: RME-1 recycling endosome localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes, positive for the endocytosis protein RME-1, that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: peroxisome morphology variant
description: The morphological appearance of peroxisomes is variant compared to control animals.

label: RME-1 recycling endosome morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes, positive for the endocytosis protein RME-1, that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: recycling endosome morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes,  that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: occurences of decapitation
description: Animals exhibit constrictions in the anterior portion of the head that result in decapitation.

label: body constriction
description: Animals contain body regions that are more narrow or drawn together than adjacent body regions.

label: pathogen induced cell death variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to a pathogen or pathogenic cue, compared to control.

label: subviable
description: Animals are barely alive, but not entirely dead.

label: cell death variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any of the processes that lead to the termination of vital functions of a cell.

label: suicidal
description: Animals do not avoid, and perhaps seek, environments that result in their death. In the case of C. elegans, this behavior is exemplified by animals that tend to crawl off the plate.

label: induced contraction rate variant
description: Any variation in the frequency of gonad sheath contractions triggered by internal or external stimuli compared to control.

label: gonad sheath contractions variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the contraction of a thin continuous tube surrounding the proximal portions of the ovary and covering the maturing oocytes to the near portion of the distal gonad arm, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: swimming induced paralysis
description: Animals become paralyzed after a measured amount of time swimming. In C. elegans, more then 80 percent of wild-type animals continue swimming vigorously in liquid even after 30 minutes.

label: alternative splicing defective
description: The process of generating multiple mRNA molecules from differential use of exons in a primary transcript(s) does not occur or occurs with outcomes not observed in control animals.

label: population fitness variant
description: Populations exhibit variations in the ability to survive, grow and reproduce, thus affecting the contribution to the gene pool over generations compared to control populations.  In C. elegans the fitness of a population can by assessed by measuring the rate at which E. coli is consumed.

label: organism heat response variant
description: Any variation in the state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, gene expression, etc.) in response to heat (high temperatures above the optimal temperature for that organism), compared to control.

label: mitochondrial DNA repair variant
description: Any variation in the process of restoring mitochondrial DNA after damage.

label: DNA repair variant
description: Any variation in the process of restoring DNA after damage.  DNA damage can be caused by a many chemical or physical agents, and this damage is repaired by a variety  of different DNA repair pathways.

label: vulval cell induction variant
description: Vulval precursor cells inappropriately adopt fates that are normally restricted to other vulval precursor cells compared to control.

label: vulva cell fate specification variant
description: Any aberrancy in the processes that govern acquisition of vulval cell fates compared to control animals.

label: pathogen induced death increased
description: Animals are more prone to lethality as a result of infection compared to control.

label: pathogen induced cell death reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to a pathogen or pathogenic cue, compared to control.

label: transformer
description: XX animals are transformed into males or pseudomales .

label: masculinized
description: Animals that are not ordinarily male, exhibit male-specific attributes. In C. elegans, XX animals exhibit male-specific attributes.

label: circumferential actin bundles disorganized
description: The distribution or presence of actin in circumferential actin bundles (CFB) differs from that observed in control animals. Contraction of CFBs provide the driving force for epidermal elongation.

label: ectopic expression transgene
description: Any variation in the cellular expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism such that it now expresses in cells/tissues not seen when compared to the expression of that gene product in control animals.

label: histone acetylation variant
description: The pattern or state of acetylation modifications of histones varies from that of controls.

label: protein acetylation variant
description: Variations in the processes that incorporate acetyl groups to one or more amino acids within a protein, compared to control. An acetyl group is CH3CO-.

label: increased genetic pathway signal
description: Any variation that increases the magnitude of a signal generated by a set of gene interactions in a given pathway, compared to control.

label: persistence of paternal mitochondria
description: Mitochondria from spermatazoa persist in the developing embryo and animal as a result of bypassing the degradation mechanism that normally destroys paternal mitochondria immediately after fertilization. This can often lead to a form of heteroplasmy.

label: heteroplasmy
description: The presence of a mixture of more than one type of an organellar genome (mitochondrial DNA (mtDNA) or plastid DNA) within a cell or individual.

label: organism heat hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to heat at a lower temperature or a shorter exposure time compared to control animals.

label: sperm fertility defective
description: Any perturbation that renders sperm incompetent at fertilizing an oocyte.

label: ectopic axon outgrowth
description: Any perturbation that causes an increase in the frequency of axon outgrowth compared to control. As a result, an excess number of axonal projections are generated.

label: axon outgrowth variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern the extension of axons compared to control.

label: ectopic neurite outgrowth
description: Any variation that causes an increase in the frequency of neurite (axon or dendrite) outgrowth. As a result, an excess number of neuronal projections are generated.

label: transgene expression increased
description: Any increase in the intensity of expression of a gene product produced by exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: cell division polarity variant
description: Any variation in the orientation of the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells compared to control.

label: sperm nonmotile
description: The mature male gametes lack self-propelled movement.

label: nonanone chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to nonanone compared to control. In C. elegans, nonanone is a repellant.

label: nonanone chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of nonanone. In C. elegans, nonanone is typically a repellant.

label: mating latency increased
description: Any increase in the length of time required for a male to find a mate and initiate the search for the vulva. In C. elegans, the latency period includes the time males spend to find a hermaphrodite and pause to press its ventral side against the surface of the hermaphrodite and initiate a backing up search for the vulva.

label: male mating latency variant
description: Any variation in the length of time required for a male to find a mate and initiate the search for the vulva. In C. elegans, the latency period includes the time males spend to find a hermaphrodite and pause to press its ventral side against the surface of the hermaphrodite and initiate a backing up search for the vulva.

label: intestinal fluorescence increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that fluoresce in the intestine.

label: male tail sensory ray differentiation variant
description: Variations in the processes leading to the specialization of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan compared to control.

label: cell migration failure
description: Characteristic movement of cells from one site to another is abolished compared to control.

label: spermatid activation defective
description: Spermatids fail to mature into active sperm. In C. elegans round sessile spermatids mature into spermatozoa (polarized cells with a motile pseudopod), upon copulation or treatment with proteases.

label: defecation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the processes involved in eliminating gut contents compared to control animals. In C. elegans the sequence of events during defecation includes posterior body contraction (pBoc), relaxation, anterior body contraction (aBoc), expulsion of gut contents by enteric muscle contraction (Emc) and opening of anus (Exp), and intercycle period (Wormatlas).

label: non reflexed gonad arms
description: Gonadal arms do not bend or curve. In C. elegans gonad arms normally reflex to form a stereotypical U-shaped pattern.

label: intraflagellar transport absent
description: Bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum is completely abolished.

label: intraflagellar transport distance short
description: The bidirectional transport of molecules (cargo) along axonemal microtubules is reduced compared to control.

label: anterograde transport defective
description: The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell body toward the cell periphery in nerve cell axons is disrupted.

label: harsh body touch resistant
description: Animals do not respond to prodding with a fine platinum wire or similar tool compared to controls.

label: intraflagellar transport slow
description: The rate, frequency or extent of bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum is lower compared to control.

label: electrophoretic variant protein
description: Any variation in the movement of a protein through a gel matrix when an electric field is applied compared to control.

label: no differentiated gametes
description: Animals are agametic (lack mature germ cells).

label: wing cilia morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the microtuble-based projections that in control animals invaginate individually into the sheath cell of the neuronal sensillum rather than projecting through the socket cell to the outside. In C. elegans, the cilia of each wing cell has its own unique shape and as they are not exposed to the outside, they do not typically take up dyes.

label: cilia morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the microtubule-based dendritic projections extending from the cell body, compared to that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, cilia are classified as channel cilia or wing cilia depending on their placement within the sensillum. Channel cilia of control animals are cylindrical, extend into the sensillum pore and are exposed to the outside. Wing cilia of control animals vary in shape, are embedded in the sensillum sheath cell and are not typically refractory to dyes indicating exposure to the outside.

label: anterograde transport variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell body toward the cell periphery in nerve cell axons, compared to control.

label: no transport distal segment cilia
description: The bidirectional transport of molecules along the distal segment of axonemal microtubules of the cilia is absent.

label: light body touch resistant
description: Animals do not respond to stroking to the head or tail with a hair or similar fiber, but does respond to stronger mechanical stimuli such as prodding with a fine platinum wire or similar tool compared to controls.

label: gonad development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the organ that produces gametes over time, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control.

label: no transport middle segment cilia
description: The bidirectional transport of molecules along the middle segment of axonemal microtubules of the cilia is absent.

label: amphid channel cilia morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the dendritic projections of the amphid sensory neurons that traverse the sensillum pore to connect with the outside of the animal, compared to that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, amphid channel cilia morphology is frequently assayed by dye-filling experiments using FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: amphid channel axoneme short
description: The microtuble-based fibrillar-bundles of the amphid sensory cilia are reduced in length compared to those in control animals.

label: amphid channel axoneme morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the microtuble-based fibrillar core, axoneme, of the cilia of the neurons that project through the sensillum pore to the outside of the animal, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: axoneme morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the microtubule-based fibrillar bundle (axoneme) that makes up the core of the middle part of the cilium (in a pattern of nine doublet microtubules attached to the membrane and a variable number of smaller singlet microtubules occupying the center). In C. elegans, the axoneme microtubules are arranged in a pattern of nine doublets attached to the membrane with seven smaller singlet microtubules occupying the center.

label: wing cilia bulbous
description: Animals exhibit wing cell sensory cilia that are truncated and swollen unlike that observed in control animals.

label: golgi apparatus localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as the Golgi apparatus, that traffic material from the endoplasmic reticulum or various endosomes, and process proteins for secretion, compared to control.

label: amphid channel cilia bulbous
description: The dendritic processes that normally extend through the amphid sensillum pore to the outside are truncated and have swollen ends as opposed to the extended and finger-like tips of channel cilia in control animals.

label: endoplasmic reticulum localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of the endoplasmic reticulum compared to control. The endoplasmic reticulum (ER) is an irregular network of membranes, that exists in the cytoplasm, and forms a complex meshwork of tubular channels. The ER has two forms, rough (or granular), with ribosomes adhering to the outer surface, and smooth (with no ribosomes attached).

label: wing cilia axoneme short
description: The microtuble-based fibrillar-bundle, axoneme, of the wing cell cilia are reduced in length and do not extend into the sheath cell as far as they do in control animals.

label: wing cilia axoneme morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the microtubule-based fibrillar section, axoneme, of the cilia of the flat sheet-like cells associated with sensory function, from that observed in control animals.

label: comma arrest emb
description: Cessation of development during the middle stage in embryogenesis of the worm in which the embryo is slightly folded within the eggshell (Wormatlas).

label: germ cell mitosis variant
description: Variations in the mitotic expansion of germ cell populations or in the appearance of nuclei during development in the premeiotic region of the germline compared to control.

label: heparan sulfate biosynthesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of the heparan sulfate proteoglycan compared to control.

label: one point five fold arrest emb
description: Cessation of development that normally occurs in C. elegans 420-460 min after the first embryonic cleavage at 20C, the stage between the comma and 2-fold embryo.

label: locomotion reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in any parameter used to measure locomotion compared to control animals.

label: chondroitin biosynthesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of chondroitin sulfate compared to control.

label: embryo osmotic integrity defective early emb
description: Variations in the ability of an embryo to maintain osmotic balance. In C.elegans this can result in an embryo filling the egg shell and lysing.

label: egg integrity defective early emb
description: The structure of the egg is impaired, flawed or no longer intact.

label: three fold arrest
description: Cessation of development that normally occurs in C. elegans 520-620min after the first cleavage at 20C, the stage between the 2-fold and fully elongated embryo.

label: cuticle fragile
description: The strength of the cuticle is less robust than that observed for control animals. In C. elegans the strength of the cuticle is often assayed by it's ability to protect the animal from exposure to bleach or other compounds.

label: cuticle integrity variant
description: The physical strength or function of the cuticle is varies from that observed for control animals.

label: cell survival sexually dimorphic increased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the rate or extent of programmed cell death and thus an increase in cell survival, as it pertains to a sex-specific feature, compared to control populations.

label: cell death sexually dimorphic variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the rate or extent of programmed cell death as it pertains to a sex-specific feature, compared to control populations.

label: germ cell mitosis metaphase to anaphase transition block
description: Germ line cells exhibit variations in the process whereby a cell progresses from metaphase to anaphase during mitosis, compared to control.

label: mitotic metaphase to anaphase transition defect
description: Cells exhibit variations in the process whereby a cell progresses from metaphase to anaphase during mitosis, compared to control. Metaphase is the second stage of chromosome segregation in the cell cycle where chromosomes become aligned on the equatorial plate of the cell and anaphase is the stage where sister chromatids separate and migrate towards the poles of the spindle.

label: pretzel arrest
description: Cessation of development during the final two stages in embryogenesis, 'early pretzel' stage and 'late pretzel' stage, just prior to hatching. The animal now is folded into four lengths within the eggshell and resembles a pretzel. By early pretzel stage, the head begins to move independently from the body (Wormatlas).

label: meiosis metaphase to anaphase transition block
description: Oocyte chromosomes arrest in metaphase of meiosis I without transitioning to anaphase or producing polar bodies.

label: metaphase to anaphase transition defect
description: Cells exhibit variations in the process whereby a cell progresses from metaphase to anaphase, compared to control. Metaphase is the second stage of chromosome segregation in the cell cycle where chromosomes become aligned on the equatorial plate of the cell and anaphase is the stage where sister chromatids (or homologous chromosomes) separate and migrate towards the poles of the spindle.

label: egg long
description: The fertilized oocytes have a greater than standard length measured end to end compared to control.

label: egg shape variable
description: The overall structure or appearance of fertilized oocytes that are laid exhibit nonconsistent and significant deviation from that of control animals.

label: cell division incomplete
description: The physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells is interupted.

label: early divisions prolonged
description: The time interval in which early embryonic cell divisions occur is increased compared to control.

label: transposon mutator
description: Animals exhibit an increase in frequency of transposition events (DNA movement to different positions within the genome of a single cell) causing an accumulation of lesions within the genome, compared to control.

label: spontaneous mutation rate increased
description: Animals accumulate a greater number of genetic lesions than control animals in the absence of an externally controlled mutagen. In C. elegans, this is often measured by observing the number of reversion events of a known mutant gene function over a couple generations.

label: nose touch defective
description: Animal fails to exhibit characteristic response after a nose-on collision with an object compared to control. In C. elegans, this is usually assayed with a hair or similar fiber. The nose is the anterior most tip of the animal.

label: later divisions prolonged
description: The time interval in which late embryonic cell divisions occur is increased compared to control.

label: cell death sexually dimorphic increased
description: Animals exhibit in increase in the rate or extent of programmed cell death as it pertains to a sex-specific feature, compared to control populations.

label: no polar body formation
description: Animals lack the two small cells produced, each during one of the two meiotic cell divisions (Wormatlas).

label: pharyngeal pumping shallow
description: Pharyngeal muscle contractions show less displacement than that observed in control animals.

label: phasmid socket absent
description: Animals are missing the interfacial hypodermal cell (socket cell) of the phasmid sensillum pore.

label: head notched
description: The most anterior portion of the animal contains a V-shaped indentation.

label: no uterine cavity
description: Animals lack the inner space of the uterus through which the fertilized egg passes on its way out of the nematode via the vulva (Wormatlas).

label: uterus morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the portion of the somatic gonad which encloses the fertilized eggs after their passage through the spermatheca compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: canal lumen morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the internal space of the excretory canal compared to control animals.

label: germline RNAi resistant
description: Animals show reduced susceptibility to gene silencing in the germline triggered by double stranded RNA (RNAi), compared to control.

label: RNAi resistant
description: Animals show reduced susceptibility to gene silencing triggered by double stranded RNA (RNAi), compared to control.

label: alae absent
description: Animals lack the small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle, lengthwise along the body (Wormatlas).

label: alae variant
description: Any variation in the small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle, lengthwise along the body compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: commissure absent
description: Animals are missing any one of its commissures, an axon tract that connects one body part to another.

label: serotonin reuptake inhibitor resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of serotonin reuptake inhibitors that elicit a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: serotonin reuptake inhibitor hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to serotonin reuptake inhibitors at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: expulsion infrequent
description: The final step of the defecation motor program does not occur at each cycle, but is activated occasionally. During this step in C. eslegans specialized enteric muscles contract to expel the contents of the gut through the anus.

label: sperm excess
description: Animals produce an increased sperm population compared to control.

label: DAPI staining variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the pattern of a chemical nuclear stain which is commonly used in fixed specimens and produces a bright blue label, compared to control. DAPI (4'-6-Diamidino-2-phenylindole) forms fluorescent complexes with natural double-stranded DNA (Wormatlas).

label: genotoxic induced apoptosis variant
description: Programmed cell death of germ cells caused by exposure to DNA-damaging chemical agents does not occur to the same extent as it does in control animals.

label: intraflagellar transport accelerated
description: The rate, frequency or extent of bidirectional movement of large protein complexes (mediated by motor proteins) along microtubules within a cilium or flagellum is increased compared to control.

label: lipid synthesis defective
description: The de novo synthesis of any lipid species is reduced compared to that observed in control animals.

label: anterior cell migration defective
description: The orderly movement of cells along the anterior axis of the animal is abolished, misdirected or incomplete compared to control.

label: posterior reversed vulval lineage
description: The orientation of the progeny of P7.p mimic those of P5.p and face towards the posterior of the worm, a phenotype referred to as posterior-reversed vulval lineage (P-Rvl).

label: vulval cell lineage variant
description: The descendants of a vulval precursor cell exhibit altered developmental programs compared to their counterparts in control animals. In C. elegans, the VPCs are P3.p-P8.p.

label: extra sex myoblasts
description: Animals produce an excess number of sex myoblasts compared to controls.

label: fewer sex myoblasts
description: Animals produce a reduced number of sex myoblasts compared to controls.

label: fewer hypodermal cells
description: The population of hypodermal cells is reduced compared to control animals.

label: voltage gated channel activity variant
description: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a solute by a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded is altered from that observed for controls.

label: outward rectifying current variant
description: The driving force of the outward flow of ions does not exceed the inward flow for the opposite driving force or is otherwise altered when compared to that measured for control animals.

label: food dependent growth variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in growth rate or the outcome of growth in response to food compared to control. In C. elegans, animals exhibit an increase or decrease in growth rate depending on the type of bacteria they are fed.

label: food dependent body size variant
description: Animals do not differ in size when grown on different food sources to the same extent as that measured for control animals. For example, in C. elegans, wild type worms are 1.65 times larger when grown on HB101 compared to those grown on OP50.

label: neuron calcium transient levels variant
description: The degree of stimulus-evoked calcium concentration changes differs from that of controls.

label: neuromuscular junction organization variant
description: The proper localization and assembly of components at the junction of a neuron with a muscle cell varies from that observed in control animals.

label: reproductive longevity shortened
description: Animals stop producing progeny significantly before the time reproduction stops in control animals.

label: alkaline pH chemotaxis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic movement towards typically attractive alkaline pH (pH higher than 7) compared to control. However animals tend to avoid very high pH levels (pH11).  pH is a measure of the acidity or basicity of an aqueous solution. In C. elegans animals chemotax toward higher alkaline pH.

label: cell number variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the number of cells that make up the organism compared to control animals.

label: pathogen release variant
description: Infected animals exhibit variations in the rate or extent to which they release pathogens back into the environment, compared to control.

label: X ray induced mitotic germ cell arrest defective
description: Animals do not arrest mitotic germ cell division, as control animals, when treated with X-ray radiation.

label: plasma membrane leaflet composition variant
description: Any variation in the components that make up either of the two leaflets of the semipermeable bilayer surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment compared to control.

label: plasma membrane composition variant
description: Any variation in the components that make up the semipermeable bilayer surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment compared to control.

label: seam cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure, organization or placement of the population of the lateral, alae-producing epithelial cells (seam cells), compared to that observed in control animals.

label: extra excretory cells
description: Animals produce an excess number of excretory cells compared to controls.

label: apoptotic cell shedding variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the process by which cells having undergone programmed cell death are shed or extruded into the extracellular environment.

label: ectopic pharyngeal muscle
description: Animals develop pharyngeal muscles from precursor cells that do not normally produce pharyngeal muscles.

label: ectopic endoderm
description: Animals develop endodermal cells/tissue from precursor cells that do not normally produce endodermal cells/tissue.

label: starvation induced apoptosis variant
description: Any variation in the amount of cells undergoing apoptosis in organism as a result of deprivation of nourishment, compared to control. In C. elegans, starvation normally causes increased apoptosis.

label: oxidative DNA damage variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in levels of DNA damage caused by oxidative stress.

label: extra linker cells
description: Animals produce an excess number of linker cells compared to controls.

label: male gonad development variant
description: Males exhibit variations in the reproductive system, from its formation to the mature structure compared to control.

label: male somatic gonad development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the components of the male gonad that are separate from the germline proper over time, from its formation to its mature structure compared to control.  In C. elegans, the male somatic gonad consists of three tissues: distal tip cells (DTCs), the seminal vesicle, and the vas deferens (Wormatlas).

label: ectopic body wall muscle
description: Animals develop body wall muscle from precursor cells that do not normally produce body wall muscle.

label: X cluster small RNA expression variant
description: Animals exhibit variations from controls in the expression, biogenesis, processing, or stability of the small X-chromosome derived RNAs (X cluster) species of small RNA.

label: somatic RNAi resistant
description: Animals show reduced susceptibility to gene silencing in somatic cells triggered by double stranded RNA (dsRNA), compared to control.

label: small RNA somatic expression variant
description: Animals exhibit variations from controls in the expression, biogenesis, processing, or stability of any class of small RNA species in somatic cells. Small RNAs include microRNAs (miRNAs), tiny noncoding RNAs (tncRNAs), cluster of small X-chromosome derived RNAs (X cluster), and endogenous short interfering RNA (endo-siRNAs).

label: dsRNA processing defective
description: The production of silencing RNA from dsRNA is significantly deficient compared to controls. Deficiencies in this process can result in a defective RNAi response compared to controls.

label: mRNA deadenylation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the extent to which polyadenylated mRNA transcripts become deadenylated

label: exo-RNAi response variant
description: RNAi silencing mechanisms triggered by exogenously introduced (foreign) dsRNA, do not work to the same degree as in control animals.

label: translation repression variant
description: The extent of translational repression varies from controls.

label: temperature learning variant
description: Wild-type animals will exhibit an altered temperature preference based on food/temperature conditioning. Temperature learning variants do not exhibit altered responses to temperature after conditioning compared to control animals.

label: pre miRNA processing defective
description: The production of mature miRNA from pre-miRNA is significantly deficient compared to controls. Deficiencies in this process can result in the accumulation of pre-miRNA species and or the absence or smaller amount of mature miRNA compared to controls.

label: polysome mRNA association variant
description: The extent of mRNA ribosome associations varies from controls.

label: increased pathogen accumulation
description: Animals exhibit an increase in pathogen accumulation, persistent colonization, and luminal distension of the intestine.

label: P granule degradation defective
description: The selective elimination of P granule components and subsequent aggregation of degraded components into PGL granules is disrupted.

label: intraflagellar transport complex destabilized
description: The intracellular complex of proteins that participates in bidirectional transport of molecules (cargo) along axonemal microtubules is not made up of or does not maintain the proper number or ratio of components as found in control animals.

label: oxygen consumption decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decreased rate of oxygen utilization compared to control animals.

label: multipolar mitotic spindle
description: Cells exhibit mitotic spindles with more than two poles.

label: mitotic chromatin remodeling variant
description: Animals exhibit variations from controls in the organization of chromatin, including in relation to associated complexes, that occur during the mitotic cell division cycle.

label: transgenerational loss of fertility
description: Animals exhibit a decline in fertility over generations. This is often assessed by counting laid eggs over successive generations.

label: transgenerational accumulation of histone methylation
description: The amount of histone methylation, for example as measured by the amount of H3K4me2, increases over successive generations

label: histone methylation variant
description: The pattern or state of methyl modifications of histone varies from that of controls.

label: muscle membrane potential variant
description: The difference in electrical potential between the interior and the exterior of the muscle cell either in the resting state or during evoked stimulation differs from controls.

label: cell membrane physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the composition, component distribution, or other aspect of membranes of the cell, compared to control animals.

label: muscle excitability variant
description: The extent or other quality of the excitatory postsynaptic potential (EPSP) induced by in vitro stimuli differs from that of controls.

label: current measurement variant
description: Any observed variation in the measurement of current across the cell membrane compared to measurements in control animals. Current is a flow of electric charge through a medium.

label: cell cycle variant
description: Cells of the animals exhibit variations in the initiation, progression or exit from the biochemical and morphological processes that occur during successive replication or nuclear replication events from that observed for control animals.

label: maintenance of gene silencing variant
description: Animals differ from controls in the expression of genes targeted for silencing (gene inactivation) in subsequent generations via transcriptional or post-transcriptional processes.

label: transgene induced cosuppression variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the silencing of endogenous genes after introduction of repetitive exogenous cognate DNA compared to control.

label: pharyngeal contraction defective
description: Any defects in the muscle contractions that control feeding. Contractions are necessary for bacterial uptake from the surrounding environment.

label: asymmetric cell division defective early emb
description: Symmetric (PAR-like) divisions or excessive posterior displacement (zyg-8 like phenotypes).

label: asymmetric cell division variant
description: Any variation in a cell's ability to divide asymmetrically to produce two daughter cells with different developmental potentials compared to control.

label: contraction response to ouabain resistant
description: Animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to ouabain to elicit the rapid muscular contractions seen in control animals.

label: ouabain resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of ouabain that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans, resistance to ouabain is often assayed via body contraction response.

label: L2 L3 molt defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates L2 to L3 transition.

label: mianserin resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of mianserin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: biogenic amine receptor antagonist resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of biogenic amine receptor antagonist that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: cyproheptadine resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of cyproheptadine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: L3 L4 molt defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates L3 to L4 transition.

label: methiothepin resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of methiothepin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: L1 L2 molt defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates L1 to L2 transition.

label: enflurane hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to the anesthetic enflurane at lower concentrations or shorter exposure times than control animals.

label: paralysis response to ethanol hypersensitive
description: Animals become paralyzed in response to ethanol at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: ethanol hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to ethanol at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: L4 adult molt defect
description: Animals exhibit defects in the process of shedding, part or all of its cuticle, during cuticle replacement that punctuates L4 to adult transition.

label: spindle variant
description: Any variation in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the array of microtubules and associated molecules that forms between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis and serves to move the duplicated chromosomes apart compared to control.

label: extended life span response to mianserin resistant
description: Animals do not live longer in response to mianserin compared to control.

label: isoflurane hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to the anesthetic isoflurane at lower concentrations or shorter response times than control animals.

label: spindle orientation defective early emb
description: The alignment of the spindle relative to other cellular structures in the cells of an embryo varies from that observed in control animals.

label: spindle position orientation defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the placement or the alignment of the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis.

label: spindle orientation variant
description: The alignment of the spindle relative to other cellular structures varies from that observed in control animals.

label: protein secretion variant
description: Variations in the regulated release of proteins from a cell or group of cells compared to control.

label: enzyme activity variant
description: Any variation in the function of naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes compared to control. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component).

label: exocytosis variant
description: Variations in the process of secretion by a cell that results in the release of intracellular molecules (e.g. hormones, matrix proteins) contained within a membrane-bounded vesicle by fusion of the vesicle with the plasma membrane of a cell, compared to control.

label: ligand binding variant
description: Any variation of the specific binding of a molecule to its partner, which typically results in a change in cell activity, compared to control.

label: germ cell hypersensitive ionizing radiation
description: Germ cells exhibit increased sensitivity to the effects of ion producing radiation compared to control animals.

label: germ cell ionizing radiation response variant
description: Germ cells exhibit variations in their response to ionizing radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: hypodermal cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the hypodermal system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: endoreduplication of hypodermal nuclei variant
description: Any variation in the regulated re-replication of DNA in the hypodermal cells during a single cell cycle, compared to control.

label: catalysis variant
description: Any variation in the catalysis of a biochemical reaction compared to control. Catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component).

label: epithelial cell fusion failure
description: Any perturbation that renders epithelial cells incompetent at undergoing membrane fusion during development.

label: multivulva
description: Multiple vulva-like protrusions are present along the ventral side of the animal. In C. elegans, this is usually a result of all six vulval precursor cells adopting primary or secondary vulval fates.

label: vulval cell induction increased
description: An excess number of vulval precursor cells receive an inductive signal leading to an increased number of VPCs adopting vulval fates compared to control animals.

label: intestinal development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the intestine over time from its initial formation to its mature structure compared to control.

label: gut granule biogenesis reduced
description: Animals lack birefringent containing compartments in embryonic intestinal cells; however, these compartments appear in adult stages.

label: muscle cell attachment variant
description: Any variation in the connection of a cell whose principal function is to provide contractile forces with its neighboring cells or tissues compared to control.

label: muscle excess
description: Animals exhibit a greater number of embryonic muscle cells compared to control.

label: squashed vulva
description: The apparent partial collapse of the vulval invagination and the elongation of central vulva cells often leading to a flattened appearance.

label: VPC cell division variant
description: Any variation that alters the physical partitioning and separation of a vulval precursor cell into daughter cells compared to control.

label: stage specific cuticle antigenicity variant
description: Animals display cuticle components displayed by animals of a different developmental stage, compared to control.

label: surface antigenicity variant
description: Cuticles of animals or cuticular extracts exhibit an altered pattern of antibody binding compared to Bristol N2 animals of the same developmental stage.

label: touch receptor cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of any neuron within the class of sensory neurons responsible for relaying mechanical stimuli to the animal compared to control.

label: cloacal structures protrude
description: Any of the contents that comprise the epithelial chamber that links the genital and alimentary tracts to the exterior via the anus extend into the external environment through the cloacal opening.

label: telomere morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the sequence or organization of the components of the terminal region of its chromosome, (i.e. telomere, which serves to stabilize the chromosome) compared to control.

label: flaccid
description: A semi-paralysed body phenotype in which muscle tone is lost and the animal fails to actively control its body shape (Wormatlas).

label: multipolar neuron
description: Neurons have more than one process extending from the cell body.

label: rectal development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the cuticle-lined sinus opening on the posterior ventral surface of the animal over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas). The function of the rectum is to excrete waste products from the alimentary system.

label: cuticle physiology variant
description: Animals produce cuticles that vary in components such as proteins or carbohydrates, observed in control animals of the same developmental stage and raised under the same conditions.

label: adoption of fused vulval cell fate
description: Vulval precursor cells forgo further cell division and fuse to the hypodermis instead of adopting their intended fate (becoming primary, secondary or tertiary vulval cells).

label: backing uncoordinated
description: Backward movement is not coordinated as in control. This often causes jerky or spastic backward locomotion.

label: gonad sheath contraction rate reduced
description: Basal contraction rate and or peak contraction rate of the gonadal sheath is reduced relative to control animals.

label: synaptic vesicle homeostasis variant
description: The rates of synaptic vesicle exocytosis and endocytosis vary from that observed in control animals.

label: spermatogenesis defective hermaphrodite
description: Variations that specifically disrupt sperm production in XX hermaphrodites. By contrast, spermatogenesis in XO males remains unaffected.

label: backing increased
description: Animals spend more time backing compared to control animals.

label: organism UV resistant
description: Organisms respond to UV at a higer dose or a longer exposure compared to control animals.

label: organism UV response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to ultraviolet radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: hermaphrodite tail spike variant
description: Any variation in the structure or appearance of the thin cuticle specialization found at the extreme posterior end of the hermaphrodite tail compared to control.

label: failure to hatch
description: Animals fail to emerge from an egg shell.

label: spermatogenesis delayed
description: The progression of immature germ cells to functional sperm is retarded compared to control.

label: muscimol resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of muscimol that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: muscimol response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to muscimol compared to that observed in control animals. Muscimol is a GABA-A receptor agonist.

label: surface coat variant
description: The electron dense, amorphous envelope that comprises the outermost layer of the cuticle varies in composition from that observed in control animals of the same developmental stage. The integrity of the surface coat is often revealed by an altered antigenicity or biochemical make up.

label: nicotine resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of nicotine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: nicotine response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the response to the addition of nicotine compared to that observed in control animals. Nicotine is a cholinergic agonist.

label: unfertilized oocytes laid
description: Animals lay inactivated oocytes. In C elegans this may be due to perturbations that eliminate spermatogenesis or result in the production of defective sperm.

label: nicotine hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to nicotine at lower concentrations or shorter exposure compared to control. Nicotine is a cholinergic agonist.

label: postsynaptic region physiology variant
