description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process in the region, opposite to the presynaptic region, which is required for receiving signals from the other side of the synapse compared to control.

label: HSN differentiation precocious
description: Specialization of HSN precursor cells to mature HSN neurons occurs at an earlier stage of development compared to control.

label: no expulsion defecation
description: Animals lack the stereotyped muscle contractions that result in the opening of anus.

label: protein signaling variant
description: Any variation in a series of protein mediated signals that help relay information within the cell, and thereby affecting changes in the functioning of the cell, compared to control.

label: extra cell division postembryonic
description: Animals execute supernumerary cell divisions post-hatching.

label: muscimol hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to muscimol at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: surface antigen negative
description: Cuticles or cuticular extracts do not bind antibodies that are observed to bind the surfaces or cuticular extracts of Bristol N2 animals of the same developmental stage.

label: skiddy
description: Apparently normal sinusoidal movement, but appear to have poor traction on the agar surface of a culture plate.

label: germ nuclei rachis
description: Germ nuclei are misplaced in the gonad and are observed in the rachis. Sheath cells are observed protruding between these nuclei. Meiotic or mitotic specification of germ nuclei is not affected.

label: rachis morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the nucleus-free core of germ line cytoplasm in the gonad compared to control animals. In the C. elegans germline, nuclei exiting mitosis and entering meiosis are arranged along the cortex of the germline, partially enclosed by cellular membrane, forming a nucleus-free core of germline cytoplasm, called the rachis.

label: constitutive larval display
description: Animals display surface antigens throughout all larval stages, unlike Bristol N2 worms, which display the antigens only during one larval stage.

label: cell division slow
description: Any variation that delays the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells compared to control.

label: glycosyltransferase activity variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their catalytic ability the transfer glycolsyl groups from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor) often measured by a reduction in the amount of glycosylated products compared to that observed in control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: spermatogenesis to oogenesis switch defective
description: Hermaphrodites continue to produce sperm past the time at which the transition to oogenesis normally occurs. Thus, germ cells that would normally become oocytes are transformed into sperm instead.

label: gut granule birefringence misplaced
description: The birefringent inclusions typically found in the intestinal cytoplasm accumulate extracellularly in the intestinal lumen.

label: male posterior alae
description: Males have alae that extend into the tail region. Alae are small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle. In C. elegans alae do not extend into the tail region (Wormatlas).

label: lima bean arrest
description: Cessation of development at an intermediate stage in embryogenesis, immediately following the completion of gastrulation. In C. elegans this occurs around 350-390 minutes after first cleavage, cell number is at approximately 560 cells. At this time cell proliferation ceases and the embryo begins morphogenesis and elongation. The shape of the entire embryo within the eggshell resembles a lima bean (Wormatlas).

label: blastocoel variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the fluid-filled compartment inside the developing embryo at the onset of gastrulation over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: pheromone induced larval display defective
description: Animals are not induced to display surface antigens by exposure to pheromone as observed for Bristol N2 animals.

label: head swollen
description: The most anterior portion of the animal appears bloated or distended.

label: cadmium hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to cadmium at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: cadmium response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to cadmium compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cadmium resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of cadmium that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to cadmium to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: short
description: Animals exhibit a decreased body length compared to control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: nose morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of the extreme anterior part of their body compared to control.

label: nose rounded
description: The extreme anterior part of the body appears blunted in shape.

label: anchor cell invasion variant
description: Any variation in the process by which the gonad anchor cell makes contact with vulval cells in order to create a uterine-vulval connection. In C. elegans, this includes the loss of the basement membranes between these cells and the crossing of the basolateral portion of the anchor cell through this gap.

label: vulva uterus connection defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the continuity of lumen between the vulva and uterus compared to control animals.

label: spermatheca morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of the somatic gonad structure that connects the distal gonad arm to the uterus compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: terminal bulb contraction variant
description: Variations in the rhythmic contractions of the posterior pharynx (terminal bulb), such as timing, strength etc. In C. elegans contraction of the terminal bulb inverts the grinder, allowing bacteria in front of the grinder to be broken up and transported to the intestine.

label: arecoline hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to arecoline at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: arecoline resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of arecoline that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: distal tip cell development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the leader cell that guides and shapes the outgrowth of the gonad while crawling along the body wall to force the germline to extend into a long tubular shape over time from its formation to its mature structure compared to control.

label: pumping asynchronous
description: The rhythmic contractions of pharyngeal compartments are no longer synchronized compared to control. In C. elegans the corpus and terminal bulb normally contract simultaneously.

label: pharyngeal relaxation defective
description: Defects in rhythmic pharyngeal relaxations compared to control animals. In C. elegans pharyngeal relaxation follows a contraction event and facilitates bacterial trapping within the pharynx while expelling liquid.

label: pharyngeal relaxation variant
description: Any variation in the relaxation of pharyngeal muscles after contraction events compared to control.

label: loss of asymmetry AWC
description: The two morphologically bilaterally symmetric olfactory neurons AWC left (AWCL) and AWC right (AWCR) fail to undergo a left/right asymmetric diversification in cell fate.

label: loss of left right asymmetry
description: Bilaterally symmetric cell fail to acquire specific left-right asymmetric properties such as L/R specific cell position, cell death or gene expression.

label: neuronal cell fate specification variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern acquisition of neuronal cell fates compared to control.

label: inhibitors of na k atpase resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of sodium potassium ATPase antagonists that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: loss of asymmetry ASE
description: The two morphologically bilaterally symmetric gustatory neurons ASE left (ASEL) and ASE right (ASER) fail to undergo a left/right asymmetric diversification in cell fate.

label: isthmus corpus slippery
description: Failure of muscle contractions in the corpus and isthmus to trap and transport bacteria posteriorly in the pharynx.

label: pharynx slippery
description: Failure of pharyngeal contractions to trap and transport bacteria posteriorly. In C. elegans this defect results in a distention of the pharyngeal lumen.

label: organism hypersensitive X ray irradiation
description: Animals respond to iononizing radiation at a lower dose or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. Iononizing radiation has a wavelength in the 10 to 0.01 nanometer range. In C. elegans, increased sensitivity to X-ray irradiation is often observed as a decrease in survival upon exposure compared to control animals given the same treatment.

label: organism X ray response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to X-ray radiation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: low incidence male progeny
description: Lower numbers of male progeny occur in the population compared to control populations. In C. elegans, the low incidence of males phenotype in a self-fertilizing hermaphrodite population is a result of an decrease in X chromosome nondisjunction.

label: X chromosome nondisjunction
description: The frequency of sex chromosome segregation is perturbed, resulting in the production of exceptional gametes (e.g. ova or sperm) and populations with a sex ratio altered from the rate of 1:500 as observed for control populations.

label: chromosome disjunction defective
description: Chromosomes fail to segregate away from their homolog, resulting in gametes with no or extra copies of the chromosome.

label: inhibitors of sodium potassium ATPase hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to inhibitors of sodium potassium ATPase at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: pharyngeal pumps brief
description: The time interval of the stereotyped sequence of muscle contractions by individual pharyngeal muscles that act to draw food into the pharynx is shorter compared to that observed in control (Wormatlas).

label: organism oxidative stress resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the levels of reactive oxygen species that elicit a response in control animals.

label: tail swelling
description: Swelling in the post anal region compared to control. In C. elegans this swelling can be associated with infection from the nematode-specific bacterial pathogen, Microbacterium nematophilum.

label: presynaptic vesicle number variant
description: Animals exhibit a variation in the ratio of synaptic vesicles per synapse of a neuron, compared to control animals.

label: transient bloating
description: Worms sporatically appear turgid or swollen as a result of an excess number of eggs being retained in the uterus.

label: oocyte accumulation
description: An increased number of oocytes are retained in the gonad without becoming endomitotic, compared to control.

label: terminal bulb relaxation variant
description: Variations in the rhythmic relaxations of the posterior pharynx (terminal bulb). In C. elegans the relaxation of the terminal bulb returns the grinder to its relaxed forward position.

label: grinder relaxation defective
description: Failure of the grinder to come to a full relaxed position between pumps compared to control.

label: grinder relaxation variant
description: Variations in the rhythmic relaxations of the a highly specialized cuticle region of the pharynx inside the lumen of the second bulb, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: methyl methanesulfonate hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to the chemical mutagen methyl methanesulfonate (MMS) a methanesulfonate ester and alkylating agent at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. In C. elegans, increased sensitivity to MMS can be observed as a decrease in egg hatch upon acute exposure or inhibition of growth after chronic exposure compared to control animals given the same treatment.

label: imipramine hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to imipramine at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: commisure growth variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the extension of the part of the axon that forms a bridge between body regions, compared to control animals.

label: inhibitor of serotonin uptake variant
description: Treatment with inhibitors of serotonin reuptake does not elicit the same response as observed for control animals.

label: presynaptic vesicle number reduced
description: Animals exhibit an overall decrease in the quantity of synaptic vesicles at the synapse compared to control animals.

label: distal tip cell reflex failure
description: A migrating distal tip cell (DTC) fails to follow the stereotypical path. In C. elegans this path is U-shaped and results in the formation of reflexed gonadal arm.

label: distal tip cell migration variant
description: Variations in the migration pattern of distal tip cells compared to control animals. In C. elegans, DTCs located on the anterior and posterior ends of the gonad primordium typically migrate in a symmetrical U-shaped pattern.

label: body part pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of a particular body part compared to control animals.

label: body region pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency or translucency of a particular body region.

label: lethal gamete
description: Animals produce ova/sperm that contain lethal factors as a result of chromosomal disjunction defects.

label: diplo X gamete
description: Animals produce ova/sperm that contain 2 X chromosomes.

label: benzaldehyde chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to benzaldehyde as defined by control animals. In C.elegans benzaldehyde is typically attractive.

label: benzaldehyde chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of benzaldehyde. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, benzaldehyde is an attractant.

label: AWC odorant chemotaxis defective
description: In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards typically attractive volatile organic molecules sensed by the AWC compared to control.

label: nullo X gamete
description: Animals produce ova/sperm that contain no X chromosome in a nonmendelian segregation pattern.

label: M line absent
description: Animals lack the planar structure within the muscle sarcomere which lies midway within the thick filament (A) band, attaching to the plasma membrane at its base and running up towards the inward surface of the myofilament lattice, compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: amphid sheath cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the amphid sensillum cell that ensheathes the dendrite tips of channel neurons and wing cell dedritic processes, from that observed in control animals. Sheath cells in C.elegans have highly invaginated and vesiculated surfaces, which provide a specialized environment for the dendritic structures.

label: amphid phasmid sensillum morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of any specialized chemosensory organs located on the head or along the tail, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: gut obstructed
description: Any variation in the developmental progression of the intestine that leads to a blockage in the alimentary canal.

label: pheromone sensation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any of a series of events in which a pheromone stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal that influences behavior in control animals.

label: fluoxetine hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to fluoxetine at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: no Intestine
description: Embryos fail to generate cells that exhibit intestinal specification. In C. elegans, the E blastomere is the precursor of all the intestinal cells.

label: excess intestinal cells
description: Animals contain an excess number of intestinal cells compared to control. In C. elegans, intestinal cells are derived from E-blastomere. The overproduction of intestinal tissues is a result of other blastomeres adopting an E-like fate or excess cell proliferation in the E lineage.

label: diacetyl chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to diacetyl as defined by control animals. In C.elegans diacetyl is typically attractive.

label: diacetyl chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of diacetyl. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, diacetyl is an attractant.

label: posterior pale
description: Animals have decreased accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that causes increased translucency of the posterior body axis compared to control.

label: isoamyl alcohol chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to isoamyl alcohol as defined by control animals. In C.elegans isoamyl alcohol is typically attractive.

label: isoamyl alcohol chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of isoamyl alcohol. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, isoamyl alcohol is an attractant.

label: anterior pale
description: Animals have decreased accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that causes increased translucency of the anterior body axis compared to control.

label: organism electrophilic stress hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to compounds that elicit electrophilic stress at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: SDS sensitive dauer
description: Any variation that decreases the ability of dauer larva to tolerate the exposure to sodium dodecyl sulfate (a detergent) compared to control.

label: dauer resistance to harsh conditions variant
description: Variations which lead to the decreased ability of dauer larva to survive at extreme conditions, such as high or low temperatures, the presence of dilute acids, detergents, anesthetics, or even fixatives, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: roaming reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in their high-speed movement in the forward direction with brief backward movement compared to control. In C. elegans, Animals do not move more than a few body lengths from their starting position and searches occur locally with pivoting behavior.

label: roaming variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their movement at high-speed in the forward direction with brief backward movement compared to control. During roaming, control animals often traversing wide regions.

label: foraging reduced
description: Animals decrease intensity or rate of roaming and or dwelling activity compared to control animals.

label: dauer pheromone sensation defective
description: Animals fail to detect a pheromone stimulus that induces dauer formation in control animals.

label: dauer pheromone sensation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any of a series of events in which a pheromone stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal that induces dauer formation in control animals.

label: dauer development variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern development of the dauer larva, a developmentally arrested, larval stage that is specialized for survival under harsh, or otherwise unfavorable, environmental conditions. In C. elegans this is an alternative third larval stage.

label: endosome fusion defective
description: Animals are deficient in the formation or disassembly of lysosomes.

label: anterior body morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the anatomy contained in the anterior region, compared to control animals.

label: acidification level defective
description: Animals are unable to acidify compartments to the same level as that observed in control animals given the same stimulus.

label: coelomic system physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the coelomic system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: fluoxetine resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of fluoxetine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: nose resistant to fluoxetine
description: The nose of an animal fails to respond to the concentration of fluoxetine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: dauer pheromone production defective
description: Animals are incapable of synthesizing pheromones that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: organism crowding response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a situation when there is too high a density of nematodes to be supported by the available amount of food and space compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: dauer metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the chemical reactions and pathways that occur during the dauer life stage, compared to control.

label: posterior body uncoordinated
description: The movement of the posterior part of the worm is not coordinated with the rest of the body.

label: posterior body behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the longitudinal axis that spans from the midpoint to the tip of the tail of an animal in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: excess hypodermal cells
description: Embryos generate an excess number of hypodermal cells compared to control.

label: body axis behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of one of the longitudinal axes of the extended body of the worm in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: cell cleavage variant emb
description: Variations that disrupt stereotypical embryonic cleavage patterns (such as cleavage rate, division axes or asymmetric division).

label: cell cleavage variant
description: Variations that disrupt stereotypical cleavage patterns (such as cleavage rate, division axes or asymmetric division) compared to control.

label: cilia absent
description: Neurons lack the finger-like dendritic projections, which are observed extending from similar cells in control animals.

label: posterior body thin
description: The posterior part of the worm exhibits a reduced girth compared to a control animal of the same developmental stage.

label: posterior body wall contraction defective
description: Animals lack or exhibit defects in the posterior body muscle contractions during the defecation cycle.

label: posterior body wall contraction defecation cycle variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the sustained posterior body muscle contractions that precede the remaining contractions of the defecation cycle compared to control animals.

label: touch resistant tail
description: Failure to execute a characteristic response when struck or stroked in the posterior region. In C. elegans, animals move forward movement when struck or stroked in the posterior region, usually with a hair or similar fiber. The posterior region lies between the vulva and the tail.

label: no posterior pharynx
description: Embryos fail to generate cells that give rise to the posterior portion of the pharynx. In C. elegans, the MS blastomere- derived pharyngeal cells constitute the posterior portion of the pharynx.

label: posterior pharynx variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the posterior portion of the pharynx over time compared to control. In C. elegans the posterior region includes the isthmus and terminal bulb (second bulb).

label: head withdrawal defective
description: Animals are deficient in the foraging response in which an animal quickly pulls its head away from a stimulus to the nose (Wormatlas).

label: scrawny
description: Animals are slight or meager in body size compared to control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: anterior body behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of the longitudinal axis that spans from the midpoint to the tip of the head of an animal in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals (Wormatlas).

label: anterior region development variant
description: Variations in the progression of an animal's anatomy contained in the anterior region over time, compared to control animals.

label: protein degradation variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the directed breakdown of a protein (via the destruction of its native, active configuration) compared to control.

label: cell cycle delayed
description: Cells of the animals proceed through their replicative phase at a pace slower than observed for control cells.

label: large
description: Animals have increased girth and increased length compared to control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: Fluorouracil resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of Fluorouracil (5-FU) that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. Elegans Fluorouracil induces germ cell death, inhibits embryogenesis and inhibits larval growth (depending on dose) in control animals.

label: growth arrest response to 5 FU resistant
description: Animals grow well during or after exposure to 5-FU under conditions where control animals are growth inhibited.

label: germ cell death response to 5 FU resistant
description: Germ cell death fails in response to the concentration of 5-FU that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans, in addition to cell death, 5-FU exposed animals exhibit condensed germ cell nuclei or unhealthy nuclei.

label: reduced viability after freezing
description: Animals show a decrease in survivorship after thawing compared to control.

label: embryonic cell physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit deviations at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell, in any physical or chemical process required for an embryonic cell to carry out its normal function and activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli.

label: halothane hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to the lipid-soluble anesthetic halothane at lower concentrations or shorter response times compared to control animals.

label: diethyl ether hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to the anesthetic ether at lower concentrations or shorter response times than control animals.

label: spindle position defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the placement of the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis.

label: spindle position variant
description: Any variation in the placement of the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis compared to control.

label: integrity of membranous organelles defective early emb
description: Sparse or enlarged yolk granules.

label: anticonvulsant resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of compounds that act as anticonvulsants that elicit a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: anticonvulsant response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific anticonvulsant compared to that observed in control animals.

label: cytoplasmic structure defective early emb
description: Areas devoid of yolk granules throughout the embryo.

label: cytoplasmic morphology defective early emb
description: Morphology of the cytoplasm differs from control animals.

label: paralysis response to ethanol resistant
description: Animals in the presence of ethanol continue to respond to touch under conditions when control worms have stopped responding to stimuli.

label: ethanol resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of ethanol that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to ethanol to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C.elegans the phenotype designation Jud is short for JUDang, which is Korean for resistant to alcohol.

label: spindle elongation integrity defective early emb
description: The embryos exhibit defects in the cell cycle process whereby the distance is lengthened between poles of the spindle.

label: centrosome pair and associated pronuclear rotation variant
description: Any variation in the rotation of the centrosome-pronuclear complex after its migration toward the center of the embryo, compared to control.

label: isoflurane resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of the volatile anesthetic isoflurane that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: halothane resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of the anesthetic halothane that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: ethosuximide resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of ethosuximide, which acts as an anticonvulsant, that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: cytoplasmic appearance defective early emb
description: Embryos exhibit defects in the form, structure or composition of any cellular contents (excluding plasma membrane and nucleus), compared to control embryos.

label: trimethadione resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of trimethadione, which acts as an anticonvulsant, that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: embryonic cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the appearance of embryonic cells compared to control.

label: centrosome attachment defective early emb
description: Centrosomes detach from the male pronucleus.

label: egg laying serotonin hypersensitive
description: Animals lay eggs at a greater rate in response to exogenous serotonin compared to control animals.

label: egg laying serotonin variant
description: Any variation in egg laying behavior after application of exogenous serotonin compared to control. In C. elegans, serotonin induces egg laying.

label: organism oxidative stress response hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to a lower concentration of reactive oxygen species or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: sister chromatid segregation defective early emb
description: Daughter nuclei are deformed and stay close to central cortex, cytokinesis defects.

label: cytokinesis defective early emb
description: Cytokinesis is abnormal in the first or second stages of cell division.

label: locomotion rate serotonin variant
description: Any variation in the locomotion rate after application of exogenous serotonin compared to control.

label: male tail curling serotonin hypersensitive
description: Males respond to serotonin by curling their tails at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. In C. elegans males respond to serotonin with a tight ventral curling of the male tail and posterior body.

label: male tail curling serotonin variant
description: Any variation in the posture of the male tail after application of exogenous serotonin compared to control. In C. elegans, males respond with a tight ventral curling of the male tail in response to serotonin.

label: male tail curling serotonin resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of serotonin that elicits a male tail curling response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans males respond to serotonin with a tight ventral curling of the male tail and posterior body.

label: passage through meiosis defective early emb
description: Male and female PNs not visible; embryo often fills egg shell completely.

label: meiosis defective early emb
description: Animals exhibit defects in the progression of meiosis which ultimately result in embryonic lethality.

label: polar body extrusion defective early emb
description: Unextruded or resorbed polar body(ies) leading to an extra PNs in P0 and/or extra karyomeres in AB/P1.

label: polar body defective early emb
description: Polar bodies are abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: locomotion rate serotonin resistant
description: Animals fail to decrease their locomotion rate in response the concentration of serotonin that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: locomotion rate serotonin hypersensitive
description: The decrease in locomotion rate in the presence of serotonin is greater than control animals.

label: body wall muscle thin filament variant
description: Any variation in the extremely thin elongated cytoplasmic filament, usually composed principally of actin protein to form a myofilament lattice, as in muscle cells compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: body wall muscle thick filament variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a robust elongated cytoplasmic filament composed principally of myosin protein compared to control animals. In C. elegans, thick filaments also contain paramyosin and twitchin (Wormatlas).

label: shaker
description: Animals rotate back and forth around their longitudinal axes.

label: cortical blebs present
description: Embryos display cortical protusions during cytokinesis.

label: cytokinesis variant
description: Any variation that disrupts the cytoplasmic division of a cell during development compared to control.

label: pronuclear morphology defective early emb
description: Pronucleus morphology is atypical in the inviable embryo.

label: pronucleus centrosomes defective early emb
description: Pronucleus is abnormal in the inviable embryo.

label: anaphase I progression variant early embryo
description: Compared to controls, embryos exhibit variations in the part meiosis I in which homologous chromosomes separate and migrate away from each other.

label: anaphase variant
description: Any variation in the stage of meiotic or mitotic cell division in which the chromosomes move away from one another to opposite poles of the spindle.

label: pronuclear breakdown asynchronous early emb
description: Instead of breaking down synchronously, the two pronuclei break down asynchronously in the inviable one-cell embryo.

label: pronuclear breakdown defective early emb
description: Pronuclear breakdown is atypical in the inviable embryo.

label: actomyosin cytoskeletal tension variant
description: The tension of the cytoskeleton comprised of the actomyosin network differs from controls. This tension can be measured by laser-cutting of the actomyosin cytoskeleton and observing any differences the recoil velocity of cortex adjacent to the cut site.

label: actomyosin contractility defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the flow rate or targeting of the cortical actomyosin network, which occurs during polarization as well as contraction of the contractile ring, compared to control animals.

label: proteasome core activity variant
description: Animals exhibit variations from controls in their protein degradation machinery, which functions through the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain.

label: glycation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the non-enzymatic glycosylation process of attaching a protein or lipid to a sugar molecule, compared to control animals.

label: pronucleus formation failure early emb
description: Either the maternal or paternal pronucleus is absent.

label: pronuclear number defective early emb
description: There are more than two pronuclei in the inviable embryo.

label: protein turnover variant
description: The dynamics of the replacement of old proteins by newly synthesized or modified proteins varies from that of control animals. This phenotype is often measured by fluorescence recovery after photobleaching (FRAP).

label: maternal pronucleus indistinct early emb
description: Maternal pronucleus has a blurry appearance. The nuclear envelope does not have a crisp circular shape.

label: pronuclear envelope morphology defective early emb
description: Morphology of the pronuclear envelope is atypical in the inviable embryo.

label: pseudocleavage defective early emb
description: Pseudocleavage is atypical in the inviable one-cell embryo.

label: excess paternal pronucleus variant centrosome early emb
description: More than one paternal pronucleus is present in the inviable one-cell embryo or there is a defect in centrosome structure.

label: excess pronucleus early emb
description: There is either more than one maternal or paternal pronucleus in the inviable embryo.

label: univalent meiotic chromosomes
description: Chromosomes fails to pair with homologous chromosomes during the prophase stage of meiosis.

label: excess maternal pronucleus early emb
description: One-cell embryos have two or more maternal pronuclei.

label: bivulva
description: Animals exhibit a secondary vulval invagination that is anterior or posterior to the primary opening depending on the the inappropriate placement of daughter cells along the anterior/posterior axis during vulval development.

label: retarded seam cell fusion
description: Seam cells fuse to form a continuous syncytium along the body wall at a later stage of development compared to control.

label: seam cell fusion variant
description: Variations in the ability of seam cells to fuse to form a continuous syncytium along the body wall late larval development, (separate from the hyp 7 syncytium), compared to control (WormAtlas). Hypodermal seam cells lie along the lateral body wall to form longitudinal stripes of epithelial cells underlying the alae, and are required for alae formation.

label: VPC competence variant
description: Any variation in the ability of multipotent vulval precursor cells to respond to signals compared to control animals.

label: pseudocleavage exaggerated early emb
description: Embryos have more pronounced pseudocleavage than normal.

label: biotin chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to biotin as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, biotin is typically an attractant.

label: pseudocleavage absent early emb
description: No pseudocleavage is observed before or during pronuclear migration.

label: voltage measurement variant
description: Any observed variation in the measurement of voltage across the cell membrane compared to measurements in control animals. Voltage is the difference in electric potential energy per unit charge between two points.

label: fewer eggs in utero
description: Adult animals display a smaller number of eggs inside the uterus compared to controls

label: sterile F0 48 hours post injection
description: Injected worm stops producing embryos 48 hours after RNAi injection and contains no live/developing embryos at this time.

label: maternal sterile
description: Animals produce no or very few embryos as a result of experimental treatment. This is in contrast to sterility due to genetic perturbations (maternal effect sterility).

label: synaptic spike frequency variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the autonomously initiated periodic trains of calcium transients observed at the synapse, which are independent of presynaptic inputs.

label: spike frequency variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the autonomously initiated periodic trains of calcium transients observed either at the cell body or the synaptic region, which are independent of presynaptic inputs.

label: shortened life span
description: The duration of viability in the adult phase of the life-cycle is less than that of control animals.

label: eggshell formation variant
description: Embryos exhibit variations in the processes that lead to the construction of the eggshell, a protective structure that minimizes water loss whilst allowing gas exchanges essential for embryonic respiration, compared to controls

label: cell size decreased
description: The diameter, volume, or area taken up by a cell differs from that measured in control animals.

label: embryo osmotic pressure sensitive early emb
description: Embryos rupture when placed on a 2% agar pad and covered with a coverslip.

label: cell body spike frequency variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the autonomously initiated periodic trains of calcium transients observed in cell bodies, which are independent of presynaptic inputs.

label: one cell shape defective early emb
description: One-cell embryos have an altered shape.

label: embryonic morphology defective early emb
description: Animals exhibit defects in the form, structure or composition of any of its parts during the early embryonic stage.

label: high incidence male progeny
description: Higher numbers of male progeny occur in the population compared to control populations. In C. elegans, the high incidence of males phenotype in a self-fertilizing hermaphrodite population is a result of an increase in X chromosome nondisjunction.

label: no synaptic spike frequency
description: Calcium transients at presynaptic regions do not occur.

label: pronuclear nuclear appearance defective early emb
description: The morphology of pronuclei and nuclei are defective in the early embryo. In C. elegans, this defect is often characterized by pronuclei and nuclei that are small or missing altogether and are often accompanied by spindle defects.

label: embryos small early emb
description: Embryos are produced that are less than fifty percent of the size of control embryos.

label: distal germline variant
description: Variations in the progression of the lineages that gives rise to all germ cells, lying in the region adjacent to the proximal gonad (on the side furthest from the founder cells of the somatic gonad), over time compared to control animals.

label: nuclear envelope assembly variant early emb
description: Nuclear envelope does not reassemble properly.

label: sperm absent
description: Animals lack fully specialized male gametes that are competent for fertilization.

label: organ system pigmentation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that alter transparency/translucency of a organ system.

label: nucleus reforms cell division remnant early emb
description: After division of either one-cell or two-cell embryos, the nuclei reappear next to the cell division remnant.

label: nuclear position defective early emb
description: Embryos show defects in the placement of the nucleus to a specific location within the cell.

label: intestine dark
description: Animals exhibit variations in the accumulation or expression of biochromes or any other substances that decrease the transparency/translucency of the intestine.

label: no oocytes
description: Hermaphrodites lack fully specialized female gametes that are competent for fertilization.

label: rays fused
description: Any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan are joined to one another.

label: polar body number defective early emb
description: Polar body number is abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: polar body number size early emb
description: Defects are either seen in the number or size of the polar bodies in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: rays displaced
description: Any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan are shifted from their customary place.

label: multiple nuclei early emb
description: Embryos contain more than one nucleus per cell in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: multiple nuclei
description: Animals have more than one nucleus in a particular cell type.

label: nuclear number defective early emb
description: Nuclear number is abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: thermotolerance increased
description: Animals are able to survive for longer periods at temperatures above standard culture temperatures than control animals.

label: spicules crumpled
description: The elongated sclerotized structures covered by a hardened layer of cuticle in the male tail (which are actively everted during copulation to fasten the male copulatory fan to the vulva) are deformed. In C. elegans males there are two copulatory spicules.

label: nuclear appearance number defective early emb
description: The size, number and organization of the components of the nuclei in the early embryo deviate from control . In C. elegans, this is characterized by nuclei that are completely missing or are significantly smaller than normal; often accompanied by spindle and cytokinesis defects.

label: polar body reabsorbed early emb
description: Polar body is reabsorbed in the one- to four-cell embryo.

label: polar body size defective early emb
description: Polar body size is abnormal in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: polar body reabsorbed one two early emb
description: A polar body is reabsorbed in either the one cell- or the two-cell embryo.

label: pronuclear size defective early emb
description: Maternal or paternal pronucleus is either too small or too large.

label: hydrogen peroxide homeostasis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in steady-state levels of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) compared to control.

label: pronuclei meet centrally early emb
description: The maternal and paternal pronuclei meet more centrally instead of meeting in the posterior end of the embryo.

label: supernumerary centrosomes
description: A cell or cell of the animal exhibits extra centrosomes (a subcellular body consisting of two centrioles embedded in a protein matrix) compared to control.

label: paternal pronucleus migrates early emb
description: Instead of the maternal pronucleus migrating to the posterior end of the one-cell embryo, the paternal pronucleus migrates to meet the maternal pronucleus in the anterior end.

label: synapse density variant
description: The number of synapses per unit area of a neuron differs in the animal compared to that observed for control animals.

label: pronuclear migration failure early emb
description: Neither of the pronuclei migrate and they never meet.

label: recovery from enhanced locomotion variant
description: Animals that exhibit an increase in locomotion activity do not return to basal level locomotion activity at the same rate as that of control animals.

label: P cell cleavage delayed
description: Any variation that causes a delay in the stereotypical cleavage pattern of the P cell compared to control.

label: cell cleavage delayed
description: Any variation that causes a delay in the stereotypical cleavage event compared to control.

label: acute pumping response to light variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the acute pharyngeal pumping response to light, during which the pharyngeal pumping rate initially (0-5 seconds after light exposure onset) decreases in response to light, compared to controls.

label: pharyngeal pumping rate in response to light variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in pharyngeal pumping rate in response to light, compared to controls.

label: absolute cell cycle timing defective early emb
description: Absolute cell cycle timing during the first four cell divisions is aberrant.

label: cell cycle timing defective early emb
description: Cell cycle timing is abnormal during the first four cell divisions.

label: cell cycle defective early emb
description: The progression of biochemical and morphological processes that occur during successive replication or nuclear replication events is disrupted during the early embryonic stage.

label: ecoptic hypodermis
description: Animals have extra hypodermal cells, which are present in places they are normally not found, when compared to the number or location of these cells in control animals.

label: pyrimidine biosynthesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of pyrimidine nucleobases, 1,3-diazine, organic nitrogenous bases.

label: P1 aster defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the array of microtubules emanating from a spindle pole that do not connect to kinetochores in the P1 cell.

label: cell cycle slow early emb
description: Embryos take longer to divide during the first and second cell divisions.

label: cell position defective early emb
description: Cell position is abnormal in the early embryo.

label: cell position defective
description: a cell (or group of cells) is not found in the correct body position compared the placement in control animals.

label: reduced acute pharyngeal pumping response to light
description: Animals exhibit a reduced acute pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that pharyngeal pumping rate decreases in response to light to a lesser extent than in controls during the first 0-5 seconds after light exposure onset.

label: cell cell contacts defective early emb
description: Cell-cell contacts are abnormal in the early embryo.

label: cell cell contacts defective
description: Cell-cell contacts are made in a similar fashion to control animals.

label: enhanced acute pharyngeal pumping response to light
description: Animals exhibit an enhanced acute pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that pharyngeal pumping rate decreases in response to light to a greater extent than in controls during the first 0-5 seconds after light exposure onset.

label: burst pharyngeal pumping response to light
description: Animals exhibit variations in the burst pharyngeal pumping response to light, during which the pharyngeal pumping rate slightly increases during the5-10 seconds after light exposure onset, compared to controls.

label: pleiotropic defects severe early emb
description: Seemingly unrelated variations that concurrently occur during early embryonic development compared to control animals. In C. elegans, this can include multiple pronuclei, aberrant cytoplasmic texture, decrease in overall pace of development and osmotic sensitivity.

label: other abnormality early emb
description: Unclassified abnormality in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: organism UV hypersensitive
description: Organisms respond to UV at a lower dose or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: enhanced recovery pumping response to light
description: Animals exhibit an enhanced recovery pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that during the 0-10 seconds after removal of light exposure the pharyngeal pumping rate increases to a greater extent than in controls.

label: recovery pumping response to light variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the recovery pharyngeal pumping response to light, during which the pharyngeal pumping rate slowly increases during the 0-10 seconds afterremoval of light exposure, compared to controls.

label: synchronous second division early emb
description: AB and P1 divide synchronously.

label: relative cell cycle timing defective early emb
description: Relative cell cycle timing during the first four cell divisions is aberrant.

label: reversed asynchrony early emb
description: P1 divides before AB.

label: reduced burst pharyngeal pumping response to light
description: Animals exhibit a reduced burst pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that during the5-10 seconds after light exposure onset the pharyngeal pumping rate increases to a lesser extent than in controls.

label: exaggerated asynchrony early emb
description: Asynchrony of the second division is exaggerated and P1 divides more slowly than normal.

label: thrashing reduced
description: The number of body thrashes within an aqueous environment in a given period of time are reduced compared with control worms.

label: dead eggs laid
description: Animals lay eggs that are inviable.

label: enhanced burst pharyngeal pumping response to light
description: Animals exhibit an enhanced burst pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that during the5-10 seconds after light exposure onset the pharyngeal pumping rate increases to a greater extent than in controls.

label: EMS anterior extension fails early emb
description: The EMS blastomere fails to extend anteriorly and make extensive contact (hug) with the ABa blastomere.

label: maternal effect morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of any part of an animal caused by the perturbation of maternal gene products that are contributed to oogenesis and are required during embryogenesis.

label: cell cell contacts variant four emb
description: Aba, ABp, EMS, or P1 contacts fewer of its sister cells than in control embryos.

label: ectopic vulva
description: Formation in the male of the egg-laying organ of female and hermaphrodite nematodes. In nematodes, the vulva is formed from ventral epidermal cells during larval stages to give rise to a fully formed vulva in the adult.

label: P2 EMS synchronous division early emb
description: P2 and EMS divide synchronously.

label: calcium response to light variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the changes in calcium levels in response to light compared to controls.

label: rhythm slow
description: The timing of a biological cycle that recurs with regularity is delayed compared to control.

label: ABa ABp EMS synchronous division early emb
description: EMS divides at the same time that ABa and ABp divide.

label: reduced recovery pumping response to light
description: Animals exhibit a reduced recovery pharyngeal pumping response to light, such that during the 0-10 seconds after removal of light exposure the pharyngeal pumping rate increasesto a lesser extent than in controls.

label: cleavage furrow defective
description: Cells exhibit defects in the formation, maintenance or termination of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate during cytokinesis.

label: EMS anterior extension extreme early emb
description: EMS extends too far anteriorly at the four cell stage.

label: hyperinduction of antimicrobial peptide expression after infection
description: Animals exhibit hyperinduction of expression of an antimicrobial peptide after an infection, compared to control animals.

label: sex muscle development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the muscles of the adult reproductive system over time form their initial formation to their mature structure compared to control.

label: cytokinesis fails early emb
description: Cells of the embryo attempt to divide but fail to form two daughter cells.

label: cytokinesis failure
description: Cells attempt to divide but fail to form two daughter cells.

label: no induction of antimicrobial peptide expression after infection
description: Animals exhibit no induction of expression of an antimicrobial peptide after an infection, unlike control animals.

label: breaks in alae
description: The small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle, lengthwise along the body, contain gaps as opposed to a continuous arrangement (Wormatlas).

label: male sex muscle development variant
description: Variations in the progression of the muscles of the adult male reproductive system over time form their initial formation to their mature structure compared to control.

label: embryo disorganized
description: Embryos fail to be organized in the same manner as observed in control animals.

label: Aba ABp division axis defective early emb
description: ABa or ABp divide in the wrong orientation.

label: division axis defective
description: The cell division axis is not normal.

label: ectopic cleavage furrows early emb
description: Extra cleavage furrows are seen in one or all cells of a one-cell to four-cell embryo.

label: ray tips swollen
description: The extreme ends of any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan appear bloated or distended.

label: pathogen adherence increased
description: Pathogens exhibit increased adherence to the surface of host animals.

label: loose mitotic furrow early emb
description: Once formed, the mitotic furrow can "slide"laterally.

label: defecation cycle variable length
description: Animals exhibit variation in the time of onset of the defecation motor program significantly greater than that observed for control animals.

label: protein aggregation induced behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions in response to external or internal stimuli in response to the aggregation of proteins.

label: mitochondria alignment variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the parallel arrangement of mitochondria within a cell compared to control.

label: sodium chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to sodium as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, sodium is typically an attractant.

label: hypoxia response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in response to hypoxia, low oxygen conditions, compared to controls.

label: mitochondria spacing variant
description: Variations in the spatial distribution of the mitochondria within the cell compared to control.

label: apoptotic arrest
description: Cells fail to complete the form of programmed cell death characterized by rounding-up of the cell, retraction of pseudopodes, reduction of cellular volume (pyknosis), chromatin condensation, nuclear fragmentation (karyorrhexis), classically little or no ultrastructural modifications of cytoplasmic organelles, plasma membrane blebbing (but maintenance of its integrity until the final stages of the process) and engulfment by resident phagocytes.

label: SM migration variant
description: Variations in the movement of sex myoblasts compared to control animals. In C. elegans, the larval SM migrate anteriorly to the precise center of the developing hermaphrodite gonad.

label: tunicamycin resistant
description: Animals respond to tunicamycin at a higher concentration or a longer exposure compared to control animals.

label: ATP levels reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the cellular levels of Adenosine-5'-triphosphate (ATP), compared to control. ATP is a nucleotide that plays a versatile role in cell biology.

label: protein glycosylation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the degree to which some proteins are glycosylated, compared to controls.

label: intestinal degeneration
description: Animals exhibit degeneration of the intestine, compared to control animals.

label: protein aggregation induced associative learning variant
description: Variations in the behavioral plasticity induced by the integration of two sensory signals in response to the aggregation of proteins.

label: osmotic avoidance variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the avoidance response to solutions of a particular osmotic strength compared to control. In C. elegans, animals typically avoid solutions of high osmotic strength.

label: protein aggregation induced reduction of life span
description: The duration of viability in the adult phase of the life-cycle is lowered in response to the aggregation of proteins.

label: X linked gene expression enhanced
description: Levels of transcripts associated with genes on the X chromosome are increased compared to control.

label: nuclear envelope breakdown variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the controlled breakdown of the nuclear envelope, compared to control.

label: octopamine metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving octopamine, 1-(p-hydroxyphenyl)-2-aminoethanol, compared to control.

label: biogenic amine physiology variant
description: Any variation in the levels and/or localization of biogenic amines compared to control animals.

label: neurotransmitter metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving neurotransmitters compared to control animals. Neurotransmitters are any of a group of substances that are released on excitation from the axon terminal of a presynaptic neuron of the central or peripheral nervous system and travel across the synaptic cleft to either excite or inhibit the target cell.

label: movement erratic
description: Animals exhibit a lack of consistency, regularity, or uniformity while traveling from one location to another.

label: EGF-induced sleep variant
description: Animals do not respond with sleeping behavior induced through the EGF pathway. The EGF-induced sleep pathway is thought to represent a distinctmolecular pathway from developmentally linked sleep. The EGF-induced sleep state occurs in two contexts: by overexpressing the EGF ortholog (LIN-3C), or by EGF signaling after stress (such as temperature elevation) in wildtype animals.

label: quiescence variant
description: Exhibition of quiescent behavior under inappropriate conditions and improper recovery from quiescent state. Quiescent behavior is normally coupled with lethargus.

label: chromosome alignment variant
description: Any variation in the movement of chromosomes to the spindle equator during mitosis compared to control animals.

label: alternative lengthening of telomeres
description: A telomerase-independent telomere maintenance pathway that allows for strains to survive in the absence of telomerase.

label: chloride chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to chloride. In C. elegans, chloride is typically an attractant.

label: chloride chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of chloride.

label: mitochondrial DNA damage variant
description: Any variation in the extent of mitochondrial DNA damage observed compared to controls.

label: XXX progeny
description: Animals segregate progeny with 3 X chromosomes.

label: octopamine deficient
description: Animals do not contain or are unable to maintain a perceivable level of octopamine capable of initiating or maintaining dopamine-dependent cell activity.

label: caffeine resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of caffeine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: X linked gene expression reduced
description: Levels of transcripts associated with genes on the X chromosome are decreased compared to control.

label: amphid phasmid morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the neuronal cells of the amphid and phasmid sensilla from that observed in control animals. In C. elegans, these neurons are commonly assayed by dye-filling experiments using FITC, DiI or DiO.

label: high susceptibility to induced DNA damage
description: Nematodes exposed to DNA damaging agents or conditions exhibit greater susceptibility to DNA damage than other animals.

label: P0 spindle position defective early emb
description: Altered P0 spindle placement causes either a symmetric first division, a division in which P1 is larger than AB, or a division in which the asymmetry is exaggerated such that AB is much larger than normal.

label: microtubule nucleation variant
description: Any variation that alters the characteristic de novo formation of a microtubule compared to control.

label: microtubule organization biogenesis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure, composition or arrangement of a robust macromolecular array, composed primarily of tubulin, which forms long extended cytoskeletal elements compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: less susceptibility to induced DNA damage
description: Nematodes exposed to DNA damaging agents or conditions exhibit lower susceptibility to DNA damage than other animals.

label: P0 spindle absent early emb
description: No mitotic spindle is seen in P0.

label: spindle absent early emb
description: Early embryos lack the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis.

label: mitochondrial stress response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to mitochondrial stress, compared to controls.

label: spindle absent
description: Cells lack the array of microtubules and associated molecules that form between opposite poles of a eukaryotic cell during mitosis or meiosis.

label: EGF-induced sleep resistant
description: Animals respond with sleeping behavior induced through the EGF pathway, more rigorously than control animals. The EGF-induced sleep pathway is thought to represent a distinct molecular pathway from developmentally linked sleep. The EGF-induced sleep state occurs in two contexts: by overexpressing the EGF ortholog (LIN-3C), or by EGF signaling after stress (such as temperature elevation) in wildtype animals.

label: multiple anchor cells
description: Animals contain more than one anchor cell. In C. elegans, presumptive ventral uterine cells undergo fate transformation and instead acquire the properties of an anchor cell (often due to defects in lateral signaling).

label: P0 spindle rotation delayed early emb
description: P0 spindle rotates late in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: spindle rotation defective early emb
description: Rotation of the embryonic spindle is aberrant.

label: repetitive transgene expression increased
description: Animals exhibit increased expression of repetitive exogenous DNA compared to control.

label: repetitive transgene expression variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the expression of repetitive exogenous DNA compared to control.

label: P0 spindle rotation failure early emb
description: P0 spindle fails to rotate and extends perpendicular to the long axis of the embryo.

label: repetitive transgene expression reduced
description: Animals exhibit reduced expression of repetitive exogenous DNA compared to control.

label: spindle rotation variant
description: Any variation in the rotation of the spindle compared to control.

label: sheath cell secretion variant
description: Variations in the regulated release of substances by nonneuronal cells that enclose or ensheath the tips of the sensory dendrites compared to control.

label: spindle orientation variant AB or P1 early emb
description: The orientation of the spindle is aberrant in either the AB or the P1 cell.

label: sheath cell secretion failure
description: The regulated release of materials by sheath cells is disrupted.

label: fainter
description: Alternating periods of stopping and moving; Motion is interrupted by periods of inactivity lasting several seconds.

label: pausing variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of time spent in a paused state, which is neither moving forward or backward, compared to control animals.

label: microtubule polymerization variant
description: Any variation that alters the characteristic addition of tubulin heterodimers to one or both ends of a microtubule compared to control.

label: amphid sheath secretion failure
description: Amphid sheath cells lack the ability to secrete vesicles and their contents within the amphid pocket.

label: microtubule depolymerization variant
description: Any variation that alters the characteristic removal of tubulin heterodimers from one or both ends of a microtubule compared to control.

label: cAMP chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to cAMP as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, cAMP is typically an attractant.

label: cAMP chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of cAMP.

label: aster AB resembles P1 aster early emb
description: The morphology of the AB aster resembles that of the P1 aster in the inviable one- to four-cell embryo.

label: aster AB defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the array of microtubules emanating from a spindle pole that do not connect to kinetochores in the AB cell.

label: tail bobbed
description: Swelling of the tail hypodermis resulting in a prematurely-truncated and thickened appearance of the tail. In C. elegans, this is usually applies to hermaphrodites.

label: pharyngeal pump duration increased
description: The duration of the contraction of the pharyngeal muscle during pumping is increased compared to controls.

label: somatic transgene silencing variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the homology-dependent transcriptional level silencing of the expression of exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism, in the soma, compared to control.

label: transgene silencing variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the homology-dependent transcriptional level silencing of the expression of exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism, compared to control. In C. elegans this silencing occurs only in the germline.

label: pharyngeal inter-pump interval increased
description: The time between two pumps of the pharynx is increased compared to control animals.

label: spindle aster variant
description: Any variation in the assembly, disassembly, arrangement, elongation or stabilization of the microtubule spindle asters during a cell cycle.

label: germline transgene silencing variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the homology-dependent transcriptional level silencing of the expression of exogenous DNA that has been introduced into the organism, in the germline, compared to control.

label: axoneme short
description: The microbule-based fibrillar bundle in the core of the cilium is reduced in length compared to axonemes of similar cells in control animals.

label: endosome morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as endosomes,  that traffic material between the plasma membrane and internal compartments of the cell, compared to control.

label: RAB-11 recycling endosome morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as recycling endosomes, positive for the RAB protein RAB-11, that traffic material from early endosomes back to the plasma membrane of the cell, thereby recycling recently endocytosed material to be reused at the plasma membrane.

label: early endosome morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as early endosomes,  that traffic material from endocytic vesicles (having recently internalized portions of the cell's plasma membrane) to internal compartments of the cell, such as recycling endosomes, late endosomes, or the Golgi apparatus, compared to control.

label: late endosome morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as late endosomes,  that traffic material from early endosomes to internal compartments of the cell, such as lysosomes or the Golgi apparatus, compared to control.

label: lysosome morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosomes, that have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell, compared to control.

label: golgi apparatus morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as the Golgi apparatus, that traffic material from the endoplasmic reticulum or various endosomes, and process proteins for secretion, compared to control.

label: lysosome-related organelle morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosome-related organelles (LROs) that, like lysosomes, have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell but are distinct in function, composition, and morphology, compared to control.

label: lysosome-related organelle localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of membrane bound organelles, known as lysosome-related organelles (LROs) that, like lysosomes, have an acidic interior and generally act to digest components of the cell but are distinct in function, composition, and morphology, compared to control.

label: carbohydrate metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any process that involves the maintenance, biosynthesis or accumulation of an internal store of carbohydrates within the organism or cell compared to control.

label: body lengthening response to muscimol variant
description: The length of the animal does not increase to the same extent as observed for control animals, in response to exposure to muscimol.

label: egg laying response to muscimol variant
description: Animals do not mimic control animals in their egg-laying response to muscimol exposure. In C. elegans, muscimol inhibits egg-laying.

label: cortical granule exocytosis variant
description: The process of secretion by a cell that results in the release of intracellular molecules contained within a specialized secretory vesicle that fuses with the plasma membrane during egg activation.

label: centrosome dynamics variant
description: Animals vary in the directed or coordinated movement of their centrosomes during cell division, compared to the pattern of movement observed in control animals.

label: cation homeostasis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of cations within a cell or between a cell and its external environment, compared to control.

label: delayed reproductive maturity
description: The animal's ability to reproduce, or start of reproduction occurs later than that observed for control animals.

label: dopamine resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of a dopamine that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: crossover variant
description: The frequency and distribution of crossover events differs from that observed for controls.

label: peptide uptake by intestinal cell decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the degree to which an intestinal cell is able to uptake peptides (for example, di- or tripeptides) from the intestinal lumen, compared to control animals.

label: peptide uptake by intestinal cell variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the degree to which or manner in which an intestinal cell is able to uptake peptides (for example, di- or tripeptides) from the intestinal lumen, compared to control animals.

label: peptide uptake by intestinal cell increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the degree to which an intestinal cell is able to uptake peptides (for example, di- or tripeptides) from the intestinal lumen, compared to control animals.

label: hydrogen sulfide hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to hydrogen sulfide at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: crossover distribution variant
description: The location-specific frequency of crossover events differs from that of observed in control animals, while the total number of crossover events does not significantly differ.

label: crossover formation variant
description: The number of crossover events differs from that of observed in control animals.

label: crossover interference variant
description: Animals differ from controls in respect to the frequency of expected double crossover events observed.

label: hypersensitive to dauer pheromone
description: Animals respond to dauer pheromone at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: abamectin repsonse variant
description: Animals are not affected to the same degree as control animals under similar conditions of abamectin exposure.

label: abamectin resistant
description: Animals survive longer, or do not respond to the same degree as control animals under similar conditions of abamectin exposure.

label: abamectin sensitive
