description: Animals are do not survive, or become paralyzed in the presence of abamectin.

label: magnesium hypersensitivity
description: Animals exhibit an exaggerated response to magnesium compared to control animals exposed to similar concentrations.

label: ivermectin resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to or exhibit an attenuated response to ivermectin under conditions that elicits a response in control animals.

label: ascaroside biosynthesis defective
description: Animals lack the ability to produce ascarosides that are capable of being produced in control animals.

label: ascaroside biosynthesis variant
description: The production or regulation of ascaroside molecule populations differs from that of control animals.

label: pore forming toxin response variant
description: Animals are not affected to the same degree as control animals under similar conditions of pore forming toxin exposure.

label: Bacillus thuringiensis toxin hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to Bacillus thuringiensis toxins (Bt toxins) at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: eating variant
description: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of an organism causing an alteration in the ingestion of food compared to control animals.  In C. elegans the main food source is bacteria and alterations in eating behavior usually lead to malnutrition.

label: photocurrent defective
description: Animals do not exhibit light-induced currrents to the same extent or with the same quality as control animals.

label: pore forming toxin hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to pore forming toxins at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. Increased susceptibility to pore forming toxins (e.g. Cry5B from Bacillus thuringiensis) is often measured by a decrease in the rate of survival in the presence of pore forming toxins compared to controls.

label: chromosome decondensation variant
description: Any variation in the progressive decompaction of chromatin that changes chromosome structure from the condensed form to a relaxed disperse form.

label: pore forming toxin resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of pore forming toxins that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: basement membrane remodeling variant
description: Animals display variations in the manner in which the basement membrane (a thin, dense, sheet-like structure built on a network of polymeric laminin and type IV collagen) is remodeled, compared to control animals.

label: maintenance of gene silencing defective
description: Animals express genes that had been targeted for heritable silencing in previous generations.

label: chromosome decondensation failure
description: The process of decompaction of chromatin that changes chromosome structure from the condensed form to a relaxed disperse form is abolished.

label: axon termination defective
description: Axons in animals do not end in the same manner as they do in control animals. Some defects described include an overextension of the axon or termination of the axon in the shape of a hook, either large or small.

label: astral microtubule asymmetry defective
description: There is significantly less difference between the number of astral microtubles or other component(s) of the spindle microtuble organizing center at the anterior versus posterior poles of the spindle, than observed in control animals.

label: apical constriction variant
description: Animals differ from control animals in cortical actomyocin dynamics leading to internalization of endodermal precursor cells during gastrulation.

label: basement membrane gap expansion variant
description: Animals display variations in the manner in which an opening in the basement membrane (a thin, dense, sheet-like structure built on a network of polymeric laminin and type IV collagen) expands to make way for intertissue connections, compared to control animals.

label: mechanoreceptor current variant
description: Animals differ from controls in their electrical response to mechanical stimulus.

label: gonad independent vulva differentiation
description: VPCs differentiate in the absence of inductive signals coming from the gonad.

label: differential touch sensitivity variant
description: Animals differ from control animals in response to mechanical stimulation targeting different parts of the same cell. In N2 wild-type animals, response to touch near the ALM cell body is reduced compared with touch of the cell area near the second pharyngeal bulb.

label: accumulated somatic cell corpses
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the quantity of non-germ line cells that have undergone programmed cell death but have not been engulfed.

label: accumulated cell corpses
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the quantity of cells that have undergone programmed cell death but have not been engulfed.

label: accumulated germline cell corpses
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the quantity of germ line cells that have undergone programmed cell death but have not been engulfed.

label: embryonic developmental delay early emb
description: The developmental progression of an early embryo over time, from its formation to its mature structure is delayed compared to control.

label: lectin binding variant
description: Animals differ from controls in the range, specificity, or presence of targets for exogenously applied lectins.

label: lectin response variant
description: Exposure to carbohydrate binding gene products result in an altered action in comparison to controls.

label: fat content increased
description: Animals exhibit a greater amount of fat or lipids than observed in control animals.

label: fat content variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the amount of fat or lipids present in the organism compared to control animals.

label: magnesium homeostasis variant
description: Variations in the regulation of levels, transport, and metabolism of magnesium ions within an organism compared to control.

label: adherens junctions variant pharyngeal muscle
description: Any variation in the cell junctions of the pharyngeal muscle at which the cytoplasmic face of the plasma membrane is attached to actin filaments compared to control.

label: pharyngeal muscle morphology variant
description: Any variations associated with the characteristic morphology of the pharyngeal muscle such as shape, birefringence etc compared to control.

label: susceptible to lectin
description: Exposure to lectin results in altered behavior, growth, or development of the animal compared to controls.

label: radial filament structure variant pharynx
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of radial arrangement of actin within the pharyngeal muscle compared to control animals.

label: resistant to lectin
description: Exposure to lectin has no affect on the behavior, growth, or development of the animal compared to controls.

label: division EMS before P2 early emb
description: EMS divides before P2.

label: lectin binding does not occur
description: Animals are not observed to contain targets for exogenously applied lectins.

label: embryo delayed at pronuclear contact early emb
description: Embryos are either delayed or arrested at pronuclear contact.

label: lectin binding occurs
description: Animals contain targets for exogenously applied lectins.

label: retrograde transport variant
description: Animals exhibit variation in the directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell periphery in nerve cell axons to the cell body, compared to control.

label: ciliary localization defective
description: Proteins show defects in their localization in the cilia compared to control animals.

label: calcium signaling pharynx variant
description: Any variation in the series of molecular signals in which a pharyngeal cell uses calcium ions to convert an extracellular signal into a response, compared to control.

label: pharyngeal muscle physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for muscles in the pharynx to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: pharyngeal physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the pharynx to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: alimentary system physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the alimentary system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: synchronization calcium signal defective pharynx
description: Calcium spikes lack synchrony in the musculature of the corpus and the terminal bulb as seen in control.

label: hermaphrodite mating efficiency reduced
description: The number of cross progeny produced by hermaphrodites is reduced compared to control hermaphrodites.

label: generation calcium signal defective pharynx
description: Rhythmic calcium increases in the pharynx are observed less often than in control animals. In C. elegans, rhythmic increases in intracellular calcium are often observed using a transgenically expressed cameleon, a ratiometric calcium indicator.

label: molting arrhythmic
description: Molting cycles do not occur in a temporally controlled manner and cannot be synchronized across a population.

label: ectopic neuron
description: Animals have extra neurons, which are present in places they are normally not found, when compared to the number or location of these neurons in control animals.

label: disorganized pharyngeal EPG
description: Electropharyngeograms do not show a similar pattern as control animals. C. elegans animals show a repeating regular pattern in which each pump is associated with an excitatory depolarizing wave, often punctuated by brief negative spikes, followed by a plateau phase, and ending with an inhibitory hyperpolarizing wave.

label: asymmetric chromosome segregation
description: Chromosomes are not segregated symmetrically during mitosis.

label: somatic sheath physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the somatic sheath system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: cell corpse number decreased
description: Animals exhibit fewer cell corpses compared to controls at the same developmental life stage.

label: hermaphrodite mating efficiency eliminated
description: Hermaphrodites do not produce cross progeny.

label: germline nuclear positioning variant
description: Variations in the directed movement/or positioning of a nucleus to a specific location within the germline compartment compared to control.

label: pachytene region organization variant
description: Animals exhibit variations from control animals in the organization of the germ cell nuclei in the pachytene stage region of the gonad. In C. elegans the pachytene region begins just proximal to the germline's transition zone, where germ cells coordinately switch into the leptotene/zygotene stage from the premeiosis stage (WormAtlas).

label: diplotene region organization variant
description: Animals exhibit variations from control animals in the organization of the germ cell nuclei in the gonad that are in the diplotene stage. In C. elegans the diplotene region follows the pachytene region and occurs just distal to, and coincident with, the loop in the gonad arm. In the diplotene region germ cell compartments become organized into a single file.

label: diplotene progression during oogenesis variant
description: Developing oocytes show defects in their entry, progression through or exit from the diplotene stage compared to control animals. Diplotene is a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the fourth stage of prophase I in meiosis, in which the homologous chromosomes begin to separate and the synaptonemal complex dissolves.

label: oocytes lack nucleus
description: Haploid female germ cells (oocytes) lack a nucleus.

label: multiple nuclei oocyte
description: Haploid female germ cells (oocytes) contain more than one nucleus.

label: diplotene absent during oogenesis
description: The diplotene stage is not observed in developing oocytes. Diplotene is a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the fourth stage of prophase I in meiosis, in which the homologous chromosomes begin to separate and the synaptonemal complex dissolves.

label: nuclear fallout
description: Nuclei have fallen out of developing germ cell compartments into the rachis.

label: spindle assembly defective early emb
description: Early embryos exhibit defects in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated chromosomes apart.

label: spindle assembly defective
description: Cells exhibit defects in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated chromosomes apart.

label: spindle pole pulling force variant
description: Pulling forces on the astral microtubules at the spindle poles vary from that observed for control spindles.

label: gonad degenerate
description: Animals contain a gonad that initially functioned, but subsequently stopped.  In hermaphrodites or females there is often the presence old embryos and/or hatched larva, but no young embryos, in the uterus.

label: habituation variant
description: Any variation in the decrease in a behavioral response to a repeated stimulus compared to control.

label: gonad small
description: A decrease in size of the specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces the male or female gametes compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: homolog association variant
description: The association of homologs during diakinesis and the maintenance of their association through meiosis I as well as the preservation of centromeric cohesin between sister chromatids does not proceed as it does in control animals.

label: missing distal tip cells
description: Animals produce less distal tip cells compared to controls.

label: axon fasciculation variant
description: The ability of axons to converge and form a bundle of nerve fibres (fascicle) is compromised.

label: reproductive longevity extended
description: Animals continue to produce progeny significantly past the time reproduction stops in control animals.

label: quinine chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute the characteristic response to the bitter tastant quinine, as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, quinine is typically repellent.

label: quinine chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of the bitter tastant quinine, a water soluble molecule. In C. elegans, quinine is typically a repellant.

label: spindle oscillation variant
description: The spindle in the early embryo is aberrant in the characteristic posterior aster oscillations that occur along the transverse longitudinal axis of the spindle.

label: meiotic chromatin reorganization variant
description: Animals differ from control animals in the length of or mechanics of the steps that culminate in the preservation and subsequent disassembly of the synaptonemal complex, the specification of bivalent arms, and proper cohesion of sister chromatids.

label: cell endomembrane physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the composition, component distribution, or other aspect of membranes of within the cell, compared to control animals.

label: neuron degeneration variant
description: Any variation in the ability of neurons to undergo a dramatic decrease in cell volume, collapse of the vacuoles and processes, and complete disintegration of the plasma membrane and most organelles under conditions that ellicit this response in control animals.

label: axon branching variant
description: Animals display variations in the number or pattern of axonal tracts stemming from the neuron cell body, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: dopaminergic fate atypical
description: Animals exhibit differential regulation of the dopaminergic fate among the various classes of dopaminergic neurons.

label: temperature induced dauer formation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the entry into the dauer stage when exposed to temperatures that induce dauer formation in control animals. In C. elegans, many Daf-c animals enter dauer at 25C, whereas Hid animals enter dauer at 27C.

label: germ cell compartment morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of the compartments in the germline of females/hermaphrodites compared to control animals. In C. elegans these compartments contain a nucleus and are connected to a common cytoplasm (rachis).  These compartments eventually undergo cellularization and become oocytes.

label: somatic gonad precursor symmetrical sisters
description: All somatic gonad precursor (SGP) daughters adopt a proximal fate resulting in an increase in the number of AC precursor cells at the expense of distal tip cells (DTC), which are thereby absent.

label: germ cell compartment nuclei number variant
description: Germ cell compartments contain an an atypical number on nuclei compared to control.

label: muscle arm development defective
description: Animals extend altered or fewer numbers of dorsal and or ventral muscle arms compared to control animals.

label: vulval muscle extension variant
description: Any variation in the extension of vulval muscles compared to control.  In C. elegans contralateral vulval muscles fail to meet at the midline.

label: synaptic vesicle tag abnormal in mechanosensory neurons
description: The pattern of localization of presynaptic markers is disrupted compared to control animals.

label: myopodia present
description: Animals exhibit ectopic plasma membrane extensions from muscle, these extensions are random projections that are thinner than the typical muscle arm.

label: muscle arm axon connection variant
description: The morphology or number of connections between muscle arms and commissural motor axons varies from control animals.

label: hypersensitive to protein aggregation induced paralysis
description: Animals respond to protein aggregation at a lower concentration of aggregates or in less time compared to control animals.

label: protein aggregation induced paralysis
description: Animals become paralyzed in response to aggregation of proteins like poly-glutamine or beta-amyloid.

label: resistant to protein aggregation induced paralysis
description: Animals fail to respond to the aggregation of proteins that elicits a paralysis response in control animals.

label: bitter tastant response variant
description: Animals are not repelled by bitter tastants such as quinine, primaquine quinacrine etc., to the same extent as control animals.

label: rachis narrow
description: The nucleus-free core of germline cytoplasm in the gonad is not as wide as control animals.

label: excretory system physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the secretory system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: oocytes small
description: The size of haploid female germ cells (oocytes) are significantly smaller compared to control.

label: oocyte number decreased
description: A decreased number of celullarized haploid female germ cells (oocytes) are present in the gonad compared to control.

label: GLR development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the GLR accessory cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell compared to control.

label: rachis wide
description: The width of the nucleus-free core of germline cytoplasm in the gonad is larger compared to control animals.

label: rachis absent
description: The nucleus-free core of germline cytoplasm in the gonad is missing.

label: diakinesis region organization variant
description: Animals exhibit variations from control animals in the organization of the germ cell nuclei in the gonad that are in the diakinesis stage. In C. elegans the diakinesis region occurs in the proximal gonad arm and is preceded by the diplotene region. In the diakinesis region oocytes arrest until oocyte maturation occurs.

label: diakinesis progression during oogenesis variant
description: Developing oocytes show defects in their entry, progression through or exit from the diakinesis stage compared to control animals. Diakinesis is a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the final stage of prophase I in meiosis; the transition to meiotic metaphase I.

label: fewer coelomocytes
description: The number of coelomocytes are reduced compared to control animals. Coelomocytes are free-floating spherical cells lying in the pseudocoelomic cavity of animals that can endocytose many compounds.

label: axon regeneration defective
description: Animals do not regrow axons following axon loss or damage, to the same extent, or in the same manner as observed in control animals.

label: kinetochore organization variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the assembly, arrangement, orientation, or disassembly of the kinetochore, a multisubunit protein complex on chromosomes where the spindle fibers attach during cell division to pull the chromosomes apart.

label: increased pathogen survival
description: Pathogens internally associated with the animal exhibit an increase in survival compared to control animals.

label: mRNA expression ectopic
description: Any variation that results in the cellular expression of an mRNA in cells/tissues, that is otherwise not observed in control animals.

label: fewer pharyngeal cells
description: Animals contain fewer pharyngeal cells compared to control animals.  In C. elegans, pharyngeal cells are derived from MS-blastomere.

label: excess coelomocytes
description: The number of coelomocytes are increased compared to control animals. Coelomocytes are free-floating spherical cells lying in the pseudocoelomic cavity of animals that can endocytose many compounds.

label: gut granules enlarged
description: Animals exhibit larger inclusions within the intestinal cytoplasm, including birefringent crystalline objects and other dark-staining endosomes. In C. elegans these contents typically include glycogen granules (polysaccharide storage), rhabditin (carbohydrate storage), yolk granules (lipid and protein), and concentrated waste products (Wormatlas).

label: fewer seam cells
description: The population of the lateral, alae-producing epithelial cells (seam cells) is reduced compared to control animals.

label: axonal transport variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in nerve cell axons.

label: meiotic DNA double strand break formation variant
description: Any variation in the creation of double-strand breaks that occur during meiosis that may result in the initiation of meiotic recombination.

label: twisted pharynx
description: The growth of pharyngeal components occurs in a radial fashion around the longitudinal axis of the worm as demonstrated by bent radial contractile arrays within the pharyngeal muscle cells. The defect is more pronounced as development progresses resulting in a more obvious twisting phenotype. Depending on the allele, the twist can be right-handed or left-handed

label: extra distal tip cells
description: Animals produce an excess number of distal tip cells compared to controls.

label: gonad sheath contraction rate increased
description: Basal contraction rate and or peak contraction rate of the gonadal sheath is increased relative to control animals.

label: oocytes disorganized
description: Oocytes are no longer arranged in the gonad in the same manner as control animals.

label: oocytes stacked
description: Oocytes are found one on top of the other in the dorsal to ventral orientation in the gonad.

label: linker cell absent
description: The gonads of male animals do not produce the linker cell involved in guiding the developing male gonad to the sex organs in the male tail.

label: extra gonad arms
description: Animals produce an excess number of gonad arms compared to controls.

label: reduced levels of reduced glutathione
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the cellular levels of reduced glutathione (GSH), compared to control. Reduced levels of GSH may be an indication of susceptibility to oxidative stress.

label: fewer eggs laid
description: Animals lay fewer total number of eggs over the lifetime of the animal.

label: manganese toxicity resistant
description: Animals fail to exhibit toxicity to the concentration of manganese that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals. In C. elegans toxic responses to manganese include dopamine (DA) neuron neurodegeneration.

label: fat associated body size increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the size of fat containing organelles compared to control. In C. elegans this can be assayed by BODIPY 493/503 staining.

label: ventral closure defective
description: The animal displays defects in any step of the ventral enclosure process resulting an embryo that is not enclosed and or with interior cells protruding out of the embryo.

label: ventral enclosure variant
description: Any variation in the process that regulates the migration of ventral epidermal cells toward the ventral midline (to encase underlying cells in an epithelial monolayer) in developing embryos compared to control.

label: dorsal intercalation defective
description: Animals exhibit defects in the generation of the dorsal epithelial sheet, which entails distinct cell shape changes and movements to affect the interdigitation of two rows of dorsal cells resulting in a single row of cells across the dorsal midline.

label: hypodermal cell elongation defective
description: During epidermal morphogenesis, hypodermal cells do not properly undergo the characteristic cell shape changes necessary for the embryo to elongate.

label: serotonin deficient
description: Animals do not contain or are unable to maintain a perceivable level of serotonin capable of initiating or maintaining serotonin-dependent cell activity.

label: serotonin metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine), a monoamine neurotransmitter, compared to control.

label: P cell misalignment at ventral midline
description: Ventral midline blastomeres (P cells) are misaligned (not properly paired) along the ventral midline of larval animals.

label: dauer sensillum variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the sense organs comprised of ciliated sensory nerve endings enveloped by sheath and/or socket cells, from that observed in control animals.

label: dauer sensory system morphology variant
description: Any variations in the form, structure or composition of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the dauer sensory system, compared to control. The dauer sensory system is used to perceive the physical and chemical environment during the dauer larval stage.

label: dauer body morphology variant
description: Any variation in the overall structure or appearance of an animal progressing through an alternative larval stage in response to environmental stresses compared to control animals.

label: serotonin synthesis defective
description: Animals are unable to carry out the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of serotonin.

label: excess fatty acids
description: The concentration of fatty acids in the animal are greater than that observed for control animals.

label: lipid composition variant
description: The constituent parts or ratio of elements that make up lipids are altered when compared to that of control animals.

label: dauer nose morphology variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of any portion of the extreme anterior part of their body compared to control.

label: acetylcholine metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving acetylcholine, compared to control. Acetylcholine is the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline.

label: glucose intolerant
description: Animals do not live or live poorly in the presence of glucose concentrations that normally do not have an effect on control animals.

label: dauer excretory gland variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of a pair of large cells in the head that fuse to form a single gland whose contents are released into the excretory duct through a specialized secretory membrane, compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: aberrant posteriorly-directed neurite
description: Any neurite that is extended towards the posterior of the animal from neurons that in wild-type animals make only anterior projections (e.g. D-type neurons in C. elegans).

label: anterior posterior neurite growth variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern the directed extension of neurite projections along the anteroposterior  axis of the animal compared to controls.

label: dauer deirid sensillum variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the sensilla situated laterally in the anterior (ADE) or the posterior (PDE) of the animal compared to control. In C. elegans, each of the 4 deirid sensilla (2ADE, 2 PDE) contains a pair of neurons with ciliated dendritic processes that lie in a channel formed by a socket cell and invaginated sheath cell. The cilia of the deirids terminate in the subcuticle and are not exposed to the outside; however occasionally take up FITC.

label: small
description: Animals are shorter and thinner than control animals at the same developmental stage.

label: pheromone behavioral response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the behavioral response to pheromones, compared to control.

label: chemosensory behavior variant
description: Variations in behavior that is dependent upon the sensation of chemicals, compared to control.

label: dauer amphid sensillum variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of any specialized chemosensory organs located on the head, compared to that observed in control animals.

label: serotonin catabolism defective
description: Animals are unable to carry out any chemical reaction or pathway resulting in the breakdown of serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine), a monoamine neurotransmitter.

label: male turning defective
description: The inability of a male to properly turn during mating behavior. In C. elegans, males typically turn via a sharp ventral arch of the tail, as he approaches either the hermaphrodite head or tail.

label: dauer labial sensillum variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the sensilla of the mouth compared to control. In C. elegans, these sensillum are arranged in two (inner and outer) concentric rings around the mouth.

label: ectopic cleavage furrows
description: Extra cleavage furrows are observed in a cell about to undergo division.

label: dauer cephalic sensillum variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of a specialized sensory organ in the head that contains a CEP receptor neuron, compared to control. In C. elegans, cells in these organs are refractory to FITC dye uptake.

label: dauer outer labial sensillum variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the outer labial ring compared to control. In C. elegans, this ring consists of four sensilla (OLQ) or the two additional lateral sensilla (OLL), which are part of the labial sensillum.

label: CAN cell migration variant
description: Variation in the migration pattern of CAN neurons. In C. elegans, CAN neurons move posteriorly from their birthplace in the head to positions near the middle of the embryo.

label: dauer inner labial sensillum variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the inner labial ring compared to control. In C. elegans, the ring is composed of six sensilla, which include associated neurons IL1 & IL2.

label: tail withered
description: The girth of the region posterior to the vulva is reduced compared to that anterior to the vulva (the Wit phenotype). In C. elegans this phenotype is associated with anteriorward misplacement of the CAN neurons.

label: dopamine synthesis defective
description: Animals are unable to carry out the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of dopamine.

label: dopamine metabolism variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any chemical reaction or pathway involving dopamine, a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline, compared to control.

label: nuclei enlarged
description: Nuclei of specific cells are larger compared to control animals.

label: dopamine catabolism defective
description: Animals are unable to carry outany chemical reaction or pathway resulting in the breakdown of dopamine, a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline.

label: cleavage furrow termination defective
description: Cells exhibit defects in the maintenance or termination of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate during cytokinesis.

label: lysine chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute characteristic response to lysine as defined by control animals. In C. elegans, lysine is an attractant.

label: dopamine deficient
description: Animals do not contain or are unable to maintain a the level of dopamine capable of initiating or maintaining dopamine-dependent cell activity compared to control animals.

label: cleavage furrow initiation defective
description: Cells exhibit defects in the formation of the groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate at the onset of cytokinesis.

label: duration of self fertility variant
description: The window of production of self-fertilized eggs exceeds or does not extend to the same length as control.

label: body wall muscle myosin organization defective
description: The characteristic organization of myosin filaments into discrete A-bands within the muscle cells is disrupted. In C. elegans, myosin filaments no longer appear as continuous longitudinally oriented fibers across the muscle quadrants.

label: foraging hyperactive
description: Animals extend intensity of roaming and or dwelling activity compared to control animals. In C. elegans, hyperactivity may include an increase in nose-lifts per minute.

label: mRNA export variant
description: Any variation in the export of mRNA from the cell nucleus compared to control.

label: body wall muscle actin organization defective
description: The characteristic organization of actin filaments into I-bands is disrupted. In C. elegans, actin filaments no longer appear as thin continuous longitudinal stripes along the muscle quadrants.

label: body elongation defective
description: The epidermal cells of the embryo fail to elongate. In C. elegans, this elongation occurs along an anterior-posterior axis, which is required to transform the bean-shaped embryo into the elongated shape of the worm.

label: body elongation variant
description: Any variation in the elongation of embryonic epidermal cells compared to control. In C. elegans, this elongation occurs along an anterior-posterior axis, which is required to transform the bean-shaped embryo into the elongated shape of the worm.

label: cold resistant
description: Animals exhibit increased ability to survive at low temperatures compared to controls.

label: chromatin modification variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the nature and/or extent of chromatin modification, including but not limited to acetylation and/or methylation of histones, compared to controls.

label: engulfment failure by killer cell
description: Removal of cell corpses through a dedicated engulfment pathway is defective.

label: hermaphrodite sexual development variant
description: Genetically hermaphrodite animals exhibit deviations in the sexual program specific to hermaphrodites. In C. elegans, this refers to XX animals that develop as males or intersexuals instead of self-fertile hermaphrodites.

label: blast cell proliferation reduced
description: The processes governing the expansion of blast cell populations vary, such that cell populations are decreased compared to control.

label: cell proliferation reduced
description: The processes governing the expansion of cell populations are altered compared to control animals, such that cell populations are decreased.

label: body wall muscle cell polarization variant
description: Variations in the accumulation of muscle proteins at membranes where adjacent muscle cells contact each other and the hypodermis compared to control. In C. elegans, during early embryonic body wall muscle development, muscle, basement membrane, and hypodermal components are all colocalized in a continuous linear structure at the site of muscle-hypodermal contact.

label: neuronal ECM variant
description: Any variation in makeup, density or area of the ECM lending structure to neurons compared to control animals. In C. elegans, the neuronal ECM is sometimes referred to as a mantle.

label: extracellular matrix variant
description: Any variation in the makeup, density or area of the ECM compared to control.

label: outer labial morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the outer labial ring compared to control. In C. elegans, this ring consists of four sensilla (OLQ) or the two additional lateral sensilla (OLL), which are part of the labial sensillum.

label: labial sensillum morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the sensilla of the mouth compared to control. In C. elegans, these sensillum are arranged in two (inner and outer) concentric rings around the mouth.

label: feminization of XX and XO animals
description: Both hermaphrodites and males develop into fertile females.

label: odorant adaptation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic desensitization to a volatile organic chemo-attractive signal in a time-concentration dependent and reversible manner compared to control animals.

label: inner labial morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the inner labial ring compared to control. In C. elegans, the ring is composed of six sensilla, which include associated neurons IL1 & IL2.

label: fewer germ cells
description: Germ cell populations are reduced compared to control animals.

label: larval growth slow
description: Any variation that causes a reduction in growth rate during larval stages compared to control.

label: autosomal nondisjunction meiosis
description: A non-sex chromosome fails to segregate away from its homologous chromosome, resulting in gametes with no or extra copies of the non-sex homolog.

label: mRNA surveillance defective
description: Defects in the cellular machinery that targets aberrant mRNAs species (nonsense codons, splice errors, altered untranslated regions etc.) for degradation. In C. elegans, mutations in such loci often act as allele-specific non gene-specific recessive suppressors of certain allele phenotypes and cause abnormal morphogenesis of male and hermaphrodite genitalia.

label: mRNA turnover variant
description: Any variation in the ability of cells to monitor the quality of their mRNAs and degrade any transcripts that are poorly or incompletely translated compared to control.

label: embryonic cell patterning variant
description: Embryos exhibit variations in the patterning of differentiated cell types, compared to control.

label: sterile
description: Animals generate defective gametes, are otherwise unable to reproduce or they generate progeny that are unable to reproduce.

label: anterior body contraction defecation cycle variant
description: Variations in the anterior body muscle contraction (aBoc) step of the defecation cycle compared to control animals. Under normal conditions, anterior body wall muscles contract and pressurize the intestinal contents during the aBoc step.

label: anterior body contraction variant
description: Any variation in the defecation motor program that involves the contraction of the anterior body wall muscles compared to control.

label: deirid sensillum morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of the components of the sensilla situated laterally in the anterior (ADE) or the posterior (PDE) of the animal compared to control. In C. elegans, each of the 4 deirid sensilla (2ADE, 2 PDE) contains a pair of neurons with ciliated dendritic processes that lie in a channel formed by a socket cell and invaginated sheath cell. The cilia of the deirids terminate in the subcuticle and are not exposed to the outside; however occasionally take up FITC.

label: long defecation cycle
description: The mean time between the onset of the defecation motor program is greater than that observed for control animals.

label: short defecation cycle
description: The mean time between the onset of the defecation motor program is shorter than that observed for control animals.

label: cell growth variant
description: Variations in the process(es) by which a cell irreversibly increases in size over time by accretion and biosynthetic production of matter compared to control.

label: cell corpse appearance delayed
description: Animals exhibit a decreased rate programmed cell death pathway leading to the destruction of the cell, viewable in its terminally dismanteled form of a cell corpse, compared to that observed for control cells.

label: apoptosis protracted
description: Animals exhibit a decreased pace of the programmed cell death pathway, compared to that observed for control cells.

label: cell corpse degradation variant
description: Variations in the process(es) that constitute cell corpse degradation within the engulfing cell compared to control.

label: gonad migration variant
description: Variations in the gross movement of the whole structure of the gonad along the body wall, behind the gonadal leader cell and away from the developing vulva compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: male sperm fertilization defect
description: Any perturbation that renders male derived sperm ineffective at fertilizing an oocyte.

label: male sterile
description: X0 animals fail to generate viable cross-progeny.

label: dauer gonad arrest variant
description: Variations in the execution of the developmentally-regulated cell cycle arrest in the gonad during the dauer stage, compared to control.

label: protruding vulva
description: Animals undergo incomplete vulval morphogenesis, resulting in the formation of a single protrusion at the site of the vulva.

label: zygotic development variant
description: Variations in the progression of a zygote from formation (gamete fusion) to just prior to the first cell division compared to control.

label: dauer sensory response variant
description: Variations in the state or activity of a dauer stage organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus, compared to control.

label: vulvaless
description: No vulval tissue is produced. In C. elegans, this is usually a result of all six vulval precursor cells adopting a tertiary fate.

label: vulval cell induction reduced
description: Vulval precursor cells receive a decrease in inductive signal leading to fewer VPCs adopting vulval fates compared to control animals.

label: alpha amanitin hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to alpha amanitin at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: dauer reduced locomotion variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit a decrease in self-propelled movement on a solid medium compared to control animals.

label: defecation contraction asynchronous
description: The rhythmic contractions of the muscles coordinating the elimination of gut contents are no longer synchronized compared to control.

label: everted vulva
description: The eversion process, in which the vulval invagination is turned inside out during the final molt, is disrupted. In C.elegans, such variations in vulval eversion are primarily due to developmental defects in the somatic gonad (and sometimes vulva).

label: dauer feeding suppressed variant
description: Any variation in the inhibition of feeding which is induced/occurs during the dauer stage compared to control.

label: prolonged pharyngeal contraction
description: The time in which a muscle contraction event that controls feeding is increased compared to control. Contractions of the pharynx are necessary for bacterial uptake from the surrounding environment.

label: dauer gut variant
description: Dauer stage animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the chain of cuboidal cells which form a central lumen lined by microvilli that allow the passage of food, compared to control. Food passes from the posterior pharynx to the intestine where it is digested and then on to the rectum which processes the waste products for excretion.

label: dauer axial ratio variant
description: Any variation in the ratio of the body length to body width in a dauer stage animal, compared to control. Long thin animals will have a high axial ratio.

label: no germ line
description: Animals lack all germline progenitor cells, thereby resulting in the complete absence of a germline.

label: dauer pharynx morphology variant
description: Variations in the form or composition of the mouthparts at the anterior end of the digestive tract during the dauer stage, compared to control.

label: dauer cuticle variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the formation of the rigid external coating (which is secreted by the hypodermis, seam and some interfacial epithelial cells) during the dauer larva stage, compared to control animals (Wormatlas). The dauer larval stage is a developmentally arrested larval stage that is specialized for survival under harsh, or otherwise unfavorable environmental conditions.

label: dauer buccal cavity morphology variant
description: Variations in the form or composition of the cuticle-lined lumenal region which lies just behind the lips at the entrance to the pharyngeal lumen in dauer stage animals compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: exaggerated body bends
description: The maximum ventral and dorsal flex of the animal is greater than that observed for control animals.

label: cell cycle quiescence variant
description: Any variation in the cell cycle arrest process that results in arrest during G1 phase, whereupon the cell enters a specialized resting state known as G0 or quiescence before entering the S phase, compared to control.

label: linker cell migration variant
description: Variations in the stereotypical migration pattern of the linker cell in a developing male compared to control.

label: connection of gonad variant
description: Any variation that disrupts the connectivity between the somatic gonad and the adjoining tissues compared to control. In C. elegans this connnection is between the somatic gonad and the vulva in hermaphrodites and between the somatic gonad and proctodeum in males.

label: left right handedness variant
description: Any variation in the establishment of left-right asymmetry of the body axis compared to controls.

label: fewer gonadal sheath cells
description: Animals exhibit fewer somatic sheath cells surrounding each gonad arm, compared to controls.

label: endomitotic oocytes
description: Any variation that results in the presence of mature oocytes with distended polyploid nuclei. In C. elegans, such oocytes mature and exit diakinesis, but are often not properly ovulated or fertilized.

label: helical cuticle
description: Animals exhibit a helically twisted cuticle. In practice the degree of twisting is measured as the number of helical twists the alae make about anterior/posterior axis of the animal.

label: conflicting sensory integration variant
description: Animals behave differently from control animals in assays testing for the ability to resolve or respond to conflicting sensory inputs.

label: struts variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity or patterning of electron-dense columnar structures that join the basal and cortical cuticle layers, from that observed in control animals.

label: hypersensitive to laser ablation
description: Animals respond more severely to laser ablation than control animals subjected to the same laser ablation conditions.

label: synaptic vesicle endocytosis variant
description: Variations in the uptake of a small membrane-bound organelle, filled with neurotransmitter(s) and/or neuropeptides, by the invagination of small region of the plasma membrane to form a new membrane-bounded vesicle compared to control(Wormatlas).

label: gonad displaced
description: The specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces gamete is shifted from its customary place as defined by control.

label: nuclear anchoring variant
description: The nucleus or nuclei are not positioned in a similar manner or pattern in the cell or syncytium to that observed in controls.

label: dense core vesicle exocytosis variant
description: Variations in the process of secretion of a class of membrane-bound vesicles found inside neurons, gland cells, and some epithelial cells in which the central core appears darkly stained when viewed in thin section by electron microscopy, compared to control. Exocytosis occurs via the fusion of the vesicle with the plasma membrane of a cell (Wormatlas).

label: posterior cell migration variant
description: Any variation in the orderly movement of cells along the posterior axis of the animal (abolished, misdirected or incomplete) compared to control.

label: annulae morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the circumferential pattern of ridges in the outer cortical layer of the cuticle, compared to that observed in control animals of the same developmental stage.

label: resistant to copper
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of copper that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to copper to elicit the response compared to control animals.

label: presynaptic vesicle cluster localization variant
description: Animals display variations in the distribution of transmitter-filled vesicles in relation to the electron-dense membrane specialization of the neuron,compared to that observed in control animals.

label: zygotic lethal
description: Animals die after fusion of gametes without dividing.

label: spicules protrude
description: The elongated sclerotized structures covered by a hardened layer of cuticle in the male tail (which are actively everted during copulation to fasten the male copulatory fan to the vulva) constitutively extend into the external environment through the cloacal opening. In C. elegans males there are two copulatory spicules.

label: growth rate variant
description: The increase in size or mass of an organism over time during the lifespan of the organism or over any developmental stage(s) is not similar to that observed for control animals.

label: body elongation retracted
description: Embryos retract after the embryonic elongation process.

label: brood size variant
description: The number of offspring produced is altered compared to that of control animals.

label: transgene subcellular localization variant
description: Any variation in the subcellular localization of a gene product produced by DNA coded for by exogenous genetic material that has been introduced into the organism compared to its expression in control animals.

label: terminal bulb morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or organization of the posterior region of the pharynx compared to control.

label: chemosensation defective
description: Animals fail to receive, process or recognize a sensory chemical stimulus in the same manner as control animals.

label: chemosensation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any of a series of events in which an organism receives a sensory chemical stimulus, converts it to a molecular signal, and recognizes and characterizes the signal, compared to control.

label: sensilium sheath cell variant
description: Any variation in the form, structure or composition of an interfacial epithelial cell which forms a specialized environment surrounding the ciliated sensory ending(s) of one or more neurons and is often accompanied by a more distal socket cell compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: sensillum accessory cell morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of the sensillum channel including the sheath and or socket cells, their junctions with each other, channel neurons or surrounding epithelia compared to control.

label: feminization of germline
description: Hermaphrodites are transformed into fertile females; In C. elegans, XO fog animals are somatically male but produce oocytes instead of, or in addition to, sperm.

label: cephalic sensillum morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the quantity, structure or organization of any component of a specialized sensory organ in the head that contains a CEP receptor neuron, compared to control. In C. elegans, cells in these organs are refractory to FITC dye uptake.

label: masculinization of germline
description: The germ line is sexually transformed from hermaphrodite to male. In C. elegans, XX mog animals are somatically hermaphrodite, but germ cells that normally would become oocytes are transformed into sperm.

label: hyperactive
description: Worms move forward or backward with an increased rate of body bends per minute compared to control animals.

label: germ cell compartment small
description: Germ cell compartments are smaller than that of control animals.

label: germ cell compartment size variant
description: Any variation in germ cell compartment size compared to control.

label: germ cell compartment multinucleate
description: Germ cell compartments contain multiple nuclei.

label: germ cell compartment anucleate
description: Germ cell compartments do not contain a nucleus.

label: sluggish
description: Animals move more slowly compared with control animals.

label: germ cell partition absent
description: Animals lack germ cell partitions (germ cell compartments).

label: germ cell partition morphology variant
description: Any variation in the form or composition of the compartment partitions in the germline of females/hermaphrodites that exist when nuclei are still connected to a common cytoplasm (rachis), compared to control animals.

label: germ cell compartment large
description: Germ cell compartments are larger than that of control animals.

label: gonad vesiculated
description: Animals contain small, fluid-filled, anucleate, spherical membrane-bound structures within the gonad.

label: germ cell compartment expansion absent
description: The compartments of the germline do not increase in size.

label: germ cell compartment expansion variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the increase in size of compartments of the germline. In the C. elegans germline, syncytial compartments enlarge just prior to and coincident with the loop region, eventually abscising, to become fully enclosed germ cells (oocytes).

label: mechanosensory system variant
description: Variations in the progression of a set of interacting or interdependent entities forming the mechanosensory system over time from an initial condition to a later condition compared to control animals. The mechanosensory system is involved in the perception of a mechanical stimuli, its conversion into a signal and the recognition and characterization of the resulting signal.

label: short range axon migration variant
description: Animals exhibit axons with migration behaviors that differ from those observed in control animals before the axons reach a half-way point between opposing neural cords. In C. elegans this point is marked by the lateral seam cells between the ventral and dorsal cords.

label: odorant discrimination defective
description: Animals fail to discriminate between distinct odorants.

label: long range axon migration variant
description: Animals exhibit axons with migration behaviors that differ from those observed in control animals after the axons cross a half-way point between opposing neural cords. In C. elegans this point is marked by the lateral seam cells between the ventral and dorsal cords.

label: pentanedione chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of pentanedione.

label: AWC odorant chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of an animal in response to a volatile chemical stimulus that is usually received and processed by the AWC sensory neuron in control animals.

label: synaptic vesicle exocytosis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the fusion of intracellular neurotransmitter-filled membrane-bound vesicles with the pre-synaptic membrane of the neuronal cell compared to control.

label: constipated
description: Animals exhibit delayed or infrequent passage and/or expulsion of fecal matter.

label: cell membrane organization biogenesis variant
description: Variations in the process(es) involved in the assembly, transport, arrangement or disassembly of cell membrane structures or components compared to control.

label: neuronal synaptic transmission variant
description: Any variation in the process of information transfer between two neurons; usually in reference to chemical synapses, but can also be used to refer to electrical synapses compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: hypoxia hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to hypoxic (low oxygen levels) stress after a shorter exposure time compared to control.

label: spontaneous reversal variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern spontaneous backward locomotion compared to control.

label: reversal variant
description: Variations in the behavior by which an organism shifts from forward to backward movements.

label: detergent hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to a detergent at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals.

label: maternal effect sterile
description: Sterility caused by aberrant maternal components required for normal postembryonic development and/or function of the germ line.

label: sterile progeny
description: Any variation that compromises the reproductive ability of the progeny of an animal.

label: neuromuscular synaptic transmission variant
description: Any variation in the process of communication across a synapse between a neuron and a target muscle cell compared to control animals.

label: acetylcholinesterase activity variant
description: Any variation in the measured levels of acetylcholinesterase (AChE) activity compared to control animals.

label: ventral nerve cord maintenance variant
description: Any variation in the mechanisms used to ensure that axons in the ventral nerve cord maintain their correct positioning after termination of axonal outgrowth and target recognition compared to control.

label: GABA synaptic transmission variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the process of GABA neurotransmitter-based communication from a neuron to a target cell across a synapse compared to control.

label: high temperature induced L1 arrest
description: Animals undergo an irreversible high temperature-induced developmental arrest during the first larval stage.

label: rays missing
description: Any of the finger-like sensory sensilla that project from the tail and embed in the male fan are absent.

label: anchor cell fusion defective
description: Any perturbation that disrupts the fusion between the anchor cell and the surrounding utse syncytium. Such variations result in the loss of uterine-vulval connectivity and continuity.

label: Bacillus thuringiensis toxin resistant
description: Animals fail to be affected by toxins produced by Bacillus thuringiensis (Bt toxins) in the same manner as control animals.

label: spontaneous reversal rate variant
description: Any variation in the processes that govern the rate at which spontaneous backward locomotion is initiated compared to control. In C. elegans, animals moving forward consistently initiate backward locomotion approximately 10 times per 3 minutes.

label: social feeding increased
description: Worms are found in clumps and/or crowded at the border of the bacterial lawn more frequently than control animals. This behavior is not due to mobility defects.

label: extra gonadal sheath cells
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the number of somatic sheath cells surrounding each gonad arm compared to controls.

label: hypoxia response attenuated
description: Response to low levels of oxygen is reduced or weakened compared to the response of control animals.

label: solitary feeding increased
description: Animals disperse across a bacterial lawn and feed alone. When food is limiting, they can aggregate into swarms or clumps, but disperse once again when food is absent.

label: hypoxia resistant
description: Animals fail to respond to low amounts of oxygen that elicit a response in control animals.

label: embryonic growth variant
description: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) during the embryonic stage compared to control animals.

label: developmental growth variant
description: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) during any development stages compared to control animals.

label: sister cell division timing asynchrony reduced
description: Animals exhibit sister cells that have lost otherwise normal asynchrony of cell division timing, compared to control animals. This results in sister cells aberrantly dividing in synchrony.

label: tumorous germline
description: Germ cells do not exit the mitotic cycle, resulting in a expansion of the unspecialized germ cell population compared to control.

label: lysosomal refractile body accumulation
description: Lysosomal refractile bodies are apoptotic-like cell corpse; however, they differ in size and shape and can be described as resembling irregular cell corpses. These bodies have been shown to represent enlarged lysosomes and can occur in conjunction with altered programmed cell death programs.

label: hypodermis disorganized
description: Hypodermal cells fail to be organized in the same manner as observed in control animals. In C. elegans, hypodermal cells typically organize into distinct dorsal, lateral and ventral rows and cover the entire body.

label: non-living barrier escape defective
description: Animals are less successful than controls in extracting themselves from mesh or other non-living obstructing obstacles.

label: sterile F1
description: Any variation that compromises the reproductive ability of an F1 generation animal.

label: no dauer recovery
description: Animals fail to exit from the facultative diapause of the dauer larval stage of nematode development.

label: first polar body position variant
description: Variations in the placement of the polar body formed in the first division of meiosis of a primary oocyte, compared to control. A polar body is the by-product of meiosis (destined to degenerate) in female or hermaphrodite animals.

label: conditional attraction to bacterial lawn
description: Animals show a stronger preference for a particular bacterium that has been grown under conditions that differ from a control lawn.

label: neuron function reduced
description: Neurons show impaired ability in the detection, transmission, coordination or their response to information about an animal's internal and external environments.

label: presynaptic vesicle morphology altered
description: Vesicles in the presynaptic terminal differ in size, shape, or composition from those observed in control animals.

label: vesicle maturation defective
description: Vesicles, including those in cells, cell bodies, or synaptic terminals, do not properly form or maintain an intermediate state, such as remain coated with a clathrin coat.

label: constitutive enzyme activity
description: Any variation that results in the misregulation of enzymatic activity such that catalysis occurs at a constant rate regardless of physiological demand or the concentration of a substrate.

label: enzyme activity increased
description: Any variation that results in an increase in the catalytic activity of an enzyme compared to control. Catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein (can include an RNA component).

label: dominant negative enzyme
description: Any variation within an enzyme that causes it to act antagonistically towards the wild-type enzymatic product. These mutations usually result in an altered molecular function (often inactive) and are characterized by a dominant or semi-dominant phenotype.

label: noxious heat avoidance defective
description: Animals fail to execute their characteristic movements to avoid noxious heat in a manner consistent with controls.

label: mRNA poly-A tail length increased
description: Animals exhibit one or more mRNAs with increased length of the 3' polyadenine tail, compared to control.

label: mRNA poly-A tail length decreased
description: Animals exhibit one or more mRNAs with decreased length of the 3' polyadenine tail, compared to control.

label: sporadic pumping
description: Pharyngeal pumping contractions are brief and occur arhythmically in response to stimulus compared to control.

label: reversion of swimming paralysis
description: Animals that exhibit paralysis (reduced thrashing) revert back to normal swimming behavior that can be tabulated as a reversion index (number revertants/number paralysis) and reversion probability (time in reversion/time after paralysis).

label: cortical dynamics defective early emb
description: Little/no cortical ruffling or pseudocleavage furrow, or excessive cortical activity. In C. elegans, this is often characterized at the two-cell stage.

label: distal tip cell morphology variant
description: The morphological appearance of distal tip cells is varied compared to control animals.

label: cell induction variant
description: Variations in a cell's ability to influence the fate of another cell (often of different developmental potential or ancestry via short range signaling).

label: RNAi transport defective
description: Animals are deficient in the transport of silencing RNAs between cells during the systemic RNAi response process.

label: interphase entry defective early emb
description: Embryos do not enter or take longer to enter first interphase compared to control.

label: mitochondria localization variant
description: The subcellular localization of mitochondrial organelles differ from that observed in control cells.

label: pathogen avoidance variant
description: Variations in the characteristic movement away from specific disease causing agents (pathogens) compared to control animals.

label: neuron degeneration enhanced
description: Neurons undergo a dramatic decrease in cell volume, collapse of the vacuoles and processes, and complete disintegration of the plasma membrane and most organelles at a faster rate or greater extent than those under conditions that elicit this response in control animals.

label: xenotoxicity suppressor
description: Animals are resistant to the toxicity of an anti-infective xenobiotic such as R24. Such small molecules protect the host from bacterial infection by inducing antibacterial immune responses via the p38 MAPK pathway. These molecules tend to have toxic effects in addition to immunostimulatory activity.

label: cyclic nucleotide positive chemotaxis variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the characteristic movement towards cyclic nucleotides compared to control.

label: light touch habituation variant
description: Any variation in the decreased behavioral response to repeated light head or tail touch compared to control. A gentel touch to the animal's head causes backward movement, whereas a gentle touch to the animal's tail causes forward movement. When wild-type animals are touched repeatedly on the head or tail, after some repetition they stop responding to the touch stimulus.

label: resistant to bioactive compound
description: Animals fail to respond to the concentration of a bioactive compound that elicits a response in control animals. Alternatively, animals require increased concentration or longer exposure to this compound to elicit the response compared to control animals.  A bioactive compound is a chemical found in small amounts in organisms or, synthetically produced, that has effects on biological processes in another organism.

label: pheromone production variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the amount and/or quality of pheromone produced compared to control animals at a defined stage.

label: metaphase variant
description: Any variation in the second stage of cell division, between prophase and anaphase, during which the chromosomes become attached to the spindle fibers.

label: lithium chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to lithium. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards lithium.

label: supernumerary asters
description: Dividing cells exhibit additional arrays of microtubules emanating from a spindle pole that do not connect to kinetochores, compared to control.

label: iodide chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to iodide. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards iodide.

label: iodide chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of iodide.

label: fibrous body-membranous organelle (FB-MO) assembly variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the assembly of the fibrous body-membranous organelle (FB-MO), a nematode sperm-specific organelle involved in cytoplasmic partitioning during spermatogenesis, compared to control animals.

label: bromide chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to bromide. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards bromide.

label: bromide chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of bromide. In C. elegans, bromide is typically an attractant.

label: high pH avoidance defective
description: Animals fail to avoid a high pH (alkaline) environment as compared to control animals.  This is at very high pH, for example around pH11.

label: cGMP chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to cGMP. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards cGMP.

label: cGMP chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of cGMP.

label: early exit cell cycle
description: Cells leave the M phase (mitosis and cytokinesis) at an earlier time than sister or other control cells.

label: frequency of body bends increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the frequency of oscillations between adjacent body segments from that observed for control animals.

label: adult growth variant
description: Variations in the processes that regulate the change (increase) in size or mass of an integrated living unit (a cell, tissue, organ or organism) during the adult stage compared to control animals.

label: forward locomotion decreased
description: Animals spend less time in forward locomotion, compared to control animals.

label: forward locomotion variant
description: Variations in the spontaneous or induced forward crawling locomotion of an animal compared to control.

label: forward locomotion increased
description: Animals spend more time in forward locomotion, compared to control animals.

label: precocious seam cell fusion
description: Seam cells fuse to form a continuous syncytium along the body wall at an earlier stage of development compared to control.

label: alae secretion variant
description: Variations in the regulated release of proteins needed for alae formation by epidermal seam cells compared to control. Alae are small linear ridges running along the lateral lines of the cuticle, lengthwise along the body (WormAtlas).

label: sperm pseudopod physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for the pseudopod of the sperm to carry out its normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: cytokinesis variant emb
description: Any variation that disrupts the cytoplasmic division of a cell during embryonic development compared to control.

label: phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate levels reduced
description: The levels of phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate (a.k.a. PtdIns3P or PI3P) are reduced compared to those of control animals

label: cell proliferation increased
description: The processes governing the expansion of cell populations are altered compared to control animals, such that cell populations are increased.

label: cell proliferation variant
description: Any aberrancy in the processes that govern expansion of cell populations compared to control animals.

label: hydrogen peroxide levels reduced
description: Animals exhibit reductions in steady-state levels of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) compared to control.

label: embryonic lethal late emb
description: Animals die during the final stages of embryogenesis. In C. elegans, this lethality refers to death during the last (3-fold) stage of embryogenesis, which normally occurs 620-800 min after the first cleavage at 20C, the stage after elongation.

label: hydrogen peroxide levels increased
description: Animals exhibit increases in steady-state levels of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) compared to control.

label: precocious alae
description: Formation of alae occurs earlier in development compared to control animals; In C. elegans, adult lateral alae are typically generated during the late L4 stage.

label: satiety behavior variant
description: Any variation in the specific actions or reactions of an animal after completion of feeding, typically after a fast, compared to that observed in control animals. In C. elegans worms become behaviorally quiescent and cease feeding and moving when sated.

label: increased susceptibility to bacterial pathogens
description: Animals are more prone to infection by bacterial pathogens compared to control animals.

label: sexually dimorphic morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the outcome of morphogenic processes required for formation or proper placement of sex-specific structures that distinguish the animal as one sex or the other in the population, from that observed for control animals.

label: increased susceptibility to fungal infection
description: Animals are more prone to infection from fungal pathogens compared to control animals.

label: acetylcholinesterase reduced
description: Any variation that results in a decrease of acetylcholine esterase levels, compared to control.

label: tRNA expression decreased
description: Animals exhibit reduced levels of transfer RNA compared to control.

label: gene expression level reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the intensity of expression of a gene product compared to that observed in control animals.

label: basal lamina development variant
description: Any variation in the progression of the layer of connective tissue over the surface of tissues that serves to separate it from neighboring tissues, from its formation to its mature structure compared to control (Wormatlas).

label: hypercontracted
description: Excessive and often uncoordinated body wall muscle contraction leading to shortening of the body.

label: tRNA expression increased
description: Animals exhibit elevated levels of transfer RNA compared to control.

label: gene expression level high
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the intensity of expression of a gene product compared to that observed in control animals.

label: male sexual development variant
description: Genetically male animals exhibit deviations in the sexual program specific to males. In C. elegans, this often refers to XO animals being transformed into fertile hermaphrodites.

label: protein carbonylation increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the covalent modification of one or more native amino acid side chains in proteins to carbonyl derivatives such as an aldehyde or ketone.

label: transdifferentiation defective
description: The conversion of one differentiated cell type into another does not occur as it does in control animals. In C. elegans, the Y cell undergoes a dramatic redifferentiation from being a cell in of the rectum to a PDA neuron. This transdifferentiation requires the cell to withdraw from its established position, migrate, and then become a motor neuron.
