label: metabolite content increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the quantity of metabolites, small molecule products or intermediates required for the metabolic functioning of the cell or organism.

label: nuclear morphology variation early emb
description: Animals exhibit variations in the form, structure or composition of the membrane enclosed organelle which contains most of the cell's genetic material during the early embryonic stage compared to control animals (Wormatlas).

label: cell degeneration
description: Cells are observed to undergo a dramatic decrease in cell volume, collapse of the vacuoles, and complete disintegration of the plasma membrane and most organelles.

label: neuron degeneration
description: Cells specialized for receiving, conducting and transmitting impulses in the nervous system are observed to undergo a dramatic decrease in cell volume, collapse of the vacuoles and processes, and complete disintegration of the plasma membrane and most organelles.

label: sickened by nonpathogenic bacteria
description: Animals are negatively affected by bacteria that is nonpathogenic to control animals.

label: hermaphrodite morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the outcome of morphogenic processes required for formation or proper placement of sex-specific structures that distinguish the animal as a hermaphrodite in the population, from that observed for control hermaphrodites.

label: patchy coloration
description: Animals exhibit an uneven distribution of biochromes or any other substances that cause disparate transparency/translucency compared to control animals.

label: protein sumoylation variant
description: Variations in the process by which one or more SUMO moieties are added to a protein, compared to control.

label: pronuclear migration reduced early emb
description: Any variation in the movement/fusion of pronuclei in the fertilized oocyte compared to control. For example, lack of male pronuclear migration, female pronuclear migration variable, sometimes multiple female pronuclei, no or small spindle.

label: membrane fluidity increased
description: Animals exhibit increased fluidity of cell membranes, compared to control animals.

label: pronuclear envelope defective early emb
description: Any deficiency in the lipid bilayer, the equivalent of the nuclear envelope, that surrounds each pronucleus within gametes and within the early zygote after pronuclear reformation (Wormatlas).

label: apoptosis fails to occur
description: Cells do not undergo the form of programmed cell death characterized by rounding-up of the cell, retraction of pseudopodes, reduction of cellular volume (pyknosis), chromatin condensation, nuclear fragmentation (karyorrhexis), classically little or no ultrastructural modifications of cytoplasmic organelles, plasma membrane blebbing (but maintenance of its integrity until the final stages of the process) and engulfment by resident phagocytes.

label: cold hypersensitive
description: Animals respond more severely to cold than control animals subjected to the same cold conditions.

label: egg round
description: The overall structure or appearance of fertilized oocytes that are laid has every part of their surface equidistant from the center.

label: touch-induced suppression of head movement defective
description: Animals do not suppress exploratory head movements in response to anterior touch stimuli, unlike control animals.

label: regenerative axonal fusion defective
description: Following axon damage, animals do not undergo axonal fusion after reconnection between the regrowing axon and its separated segment to the same extent as observed in control animals.

label: gonad arm morphology variant
description: Any variation in the 'arm-like' form, structure or composition of the specialized tissue of the reproductive tract that produces gametes compared to control. In C. elegans the reproductive tract in the hermaphrodite has two equivalent gonad 'arms', while the male has a one-armed gonad.

label: axonal degeneration
description: Spontaneous axon breaks leading to degeneration of separated segments.

label: proximal germ cell proliferation variant
description: Any variation in the spatial pattern of proliferation and differentiation in the germ line compared to control. In C. elegans, this refers to an ectopic mass of proliferating germ cells that occupies the proximal adult germ line, a region normally occupied by gametes.

label: cholesterol depletion resistant
description: Animals are more resistant to the reduction of cholesterol in the environment compared to control animals.

label: larval behavior variant
description: Variations in the specific actions or reactions of a larvae in response to external or internal stimuli compared to that observed in control animals.

label: velocity of movement decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the net velocity of an animal.

label: pheromone induced dauer formation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the entry into the dauer stage when exposed to concentrations of chemicals that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: backward point velocity increased
description: Animals exhibit increased velocity of backward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: backward point velocity variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the velocity of backward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: starvation induced dauer formation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the entry into the dauer stage when exposed to nutrient poor conditions that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: backward point velocity decreased
description: Animals exhibit decreased velocity of backward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: amplitude of sinusoidal movement increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of a vibratory movement (as a worm bend) measured from the mean position to an extreme position compared to control.

label: starvation induced dauer formation increased
description: Animals are more likely to form dauers under nutrient conditions that do not induce dauer entry in control animals.

label: velocity of movement increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the net velocity of an animal

label: starvation induced dauer formation defective
description: Animals do not enter dauer under nutrient-poor conditions that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: frequency body bend reduced
description: Animals exhibit a reduction in the frequency of oscillations between adjacent body segments from that observed for control animals.

label: thrashing increased
description: The number of body thrashes within an aqueous environment in a given period of time is increased, compared with control worms.

label: anterior pharynx extra cells
description: Embryos generate an excess number of anterior derived pharyngeal cells. In C. elegans, embryos generate an excess number of AB blastomere-derived pharyngeal cells. This hyperinduction of anterior pharyngeal tissue is associated with defects in fate specification of the ABp blastomere.

label: reduced brood size
description: The characteristic number of offspring produced is lower compared to that of control animals.

label: track length increased
description: Animals exhibit increased length of the minimum enclosing rectangle surrounding the worm body on a solid medium, as viewed through the microscope.

label: track length variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the length of the minimum enclosing rectangle surrounding the worm body on a solid medium, as viewed through the microscope.

label: unfolded protein accumulation
description: Animals accumulate unfolded proteins in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) and or the mitochondria.

label: ER stress response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to the presence of unfolded proteins in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) or to other ER-related stressors compared to control.

label: cell polarity reversed
description: Contents or structures of the cell are oriented on the opposite side of the cell compared to control animals; In C. elegans, this can result in the fate pattern of descendants being flipped.

label: ammonium acetate chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to execute directed movement in response to ammonium acetate. In C. elegans, ammonium acetate is an attractant.

label: no cleavage furrow first division early emb
description: One-cell embryos do not form the shallow groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate at the onset of cytokinesis.

label: body wall contraction variant
description: Initiation, strength, extent or cessation of body wall muscle activity that results in the shortening of the muscle, is aberrant compared to control animals.

label: late stage egg laid
description: The eggs being deposited by adults are of a later developmental stage, compared to control. In C. elegans, this is likely to be a consequence of delayed active egg-laying periods.

label: path curvature decreased
description: Animals exhibit decreases in the extent to which the overall path of movement is curved, producing shallower, less frequent curves and an overall straighter path, compared to control animals.

label: path curvature variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the extent to which the overall path of movement is curved, compared to control animals.

label: path curvature increased
description: Animals exhibit increases in the extent to which the overall path of movement is curved, producing tighter and more frequent curves compared to control animals.

label: gubernaculum morphology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the structure or composition of the sclerotic cuticle that forms the roof of the proctodeum, from that observed in control animals.

label: gubernaculum development variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the development of the sclerotic cuticle that forms the roof of the proctodeum (gubernaculum) compared to control.

label: body wall contraction interval variant
description: Any variation in the time interval between successive contractions of the body wall muscles during the defecation motor program compared to cantrol.

label: track length decreased
description: Animals exhibit decreased length of the minimum enclosing rectangle surrounding the worm body on a solid medium, as viewed through the microscope.

label: L4 lethal
description: Animals die at the L4 stage of the life cycle.

label: male spicule development variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the development of the male elongated sclerotized structures covered by a hardened layer of cuticle in the tail (which are actively everted during copulation to fasten the male copulatory fan to the vulva) compared to control.

label: body proportion increased
description: Animals exhibit increases in the body-area-to-length ratio and/or the width-to-length ratio, compared to control animals.

label: body proportion variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the body-area-to-length ratio and/or the width-to-length ratio, compared to control animals.

label: nuclear rotation variant
description: Any variation in the rotation of centrosomes and associated pronuclei in one-cell embryo, occurring as a transition between pronuclear migration and pronuclear fusion compared to control.

label: body proportion decreased
description: Animals exhibit decreases in the body-area-to-length ratio and/or the width-to-length ratio, compared to control animals.

label: VPC cell division precocious
description: VPCs (vulval precursor cells) divide at an earlier stage of development compared to control animals; in C. elegans, VPCs divide in the mid-L3 stage to generate the 22 cells that comprise the vulva.

label: cell division precocious
description: Cells divide at an earlier stage of development compared to control animals.

label: no back end
description: Animals lack a properly developed posterior region compared to control. In C. elegans, mutants exhibit a severely deformed posterior region with a variable knob-like shape; accompanied by arrest at about the time of hatching with fairly normal pharyngeal and anterior development. Most mutants arrest as L1 larvae, and 5% do not hatch.

label: pale larva
description: Larva show deficiencies in chroma resulting in increased translucency.

label: cleavage furrow not discrete early emb
description: Embryos do not form a defined shallow groove in the cell surface near the old metaphase plate at the onset of cytokinesis.

label: backing decreased
description: Animals spend less time backing compared to control animals.

label: bent posture decreased
description: Animals exhibit decreased posture eccentricity (measure of circularity) or the mean number (and/or standard deviation) of instantaneous body bends.

label: bent posture variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in instantaneous posture with regards to eccentricity (measure of circularity) or the mean number (and/or standard deviation) of instantaneous body bends.

label: bent posture increased
description: Animals exhibit increased posture eccentricity (measure of circularity) or the mean number (and/or standard deviation) of instantaneous body bends.

label: complex phenotype early emb
description: Population of unhatched eggs exhibit a complex combination of defects that do not match other class definitions.

label: clear larva
description: Larva appear unusually transparent when compared to control.

label: thin
description: Animals exhibit a reduced girth compared to a control animal of the same developmental stage.

label: distal tip cell migration precocious
description: DTCs migrate at an earlier stage of development, compared to control.

label: head movement decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the movement of the most anterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: nose movement increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the movement of the extreme anterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: nose movement variant
description: The extreme anterior of the animal exhibits variations in its movement compared to control.

label: general pace of development defective early emb
description: Variations in the time from pronuclei meeting to furrow initiation during the first cell division compared to control animals.

label: nose movement decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the movement of the extreme anterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: enzyme expression level reduced
description: Variations that cause a decrease in the expression level of a biological catalyst, compared to control animals.

label: temperature induced dauer formation defective
description: Animals do not enter dauer at a temperature that induces dauer formation in control animals.

label: tail movement increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the movement of the most posterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: tail movement decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the movement of the most posterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: temperature induced dauer formation increased
description: Animals are more likely to form dauers at temperatures that do not induce dauer entry in control animals.

label: head movement increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the movement of the most anterior portion of the body to a new location compared to control.

label: Pausing decreased
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the amount of time spent in a paused state, which is neither moving forward or backward, compared to control animals.

label: Pausing increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the amount of time spent in a paused state, which is neither moving forward or backward, compared to control animals.

label: expression lipogenic enzyme reduced
description: The levels of an enzyme involved in the manufacture of lipids are decreased compared to control animals.

label: sodium chloride chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of sodium chloride. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, sodium chloride is an attractant.

label: pheromone induced dauer formation enhanced
description: Animals enter the dauer stage when exposed to lower concentrations or shorter exposure times of chemicals that induce dauer formation compared to that observed in control animals.

label: pheromone induced dauer formation defective
description: Animals do not enter dauer when exposed to chemicals that induce dauer formation in control animals.

label: mRNA levels increased
description: Animals exhibit elevated levels of messenger RNA compared to control.

label: turning frequency reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the frequency of execution of the behavior by which the animal alters its trajectory of movement compared to control, excluding shifts from forward to backward movements (this is reversal).

label: turning frequency variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the frequency of execution of the behavior by which the animal alters its trajectory of movement compared to control, excluding shifts from forward to backward movements (this is reversal).

label: mRNA levels reduced
description: Animals exhibit decreased levels of messenger RNA compared to control.

label: turning frequency increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the frequency of execution of the behavior by which the animal alters its trajectory of movement compared to control, excluding shifts from forward to backward movements (this is reversal).

label: AWA odorant chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of an animal in response to a volatile chemical stimulus that is usually received and processed by the AWA sensory neuron in control animals.

label: acetone chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of acetone. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, acetone is an attractant.

label: roaming increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in their high-speed movement in the forward direction with brief backward movement compared to control.

label: dwelling reduced
description: Animals exhibit a decrease in the low-speed/high turning movement that usually restricts them to a confined region compared to control.

label: dwelling variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the low-speed/high turning movement that restricts them to a confined region compared to control.

label: dwelling increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the low-speed/high turning movement that usually restricts them to a confined region compared to control.

label: stress induced lethality variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in survival when exposed to stress stimuli that induce lethality in control animals.

label: butanone chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of butanone. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, butanone is an attractant.

label: hexanol chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of hexanol. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, hexanol is an attractant.

label: stress induced arrest variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in cessation of development when exposed to stress stimuli that induce developmental arrest in control animals.

label: forward point velocity increased
description: Animals exhibit increased velocity of forward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: trimethylthiazole chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of trimethylthiazole. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, trimethylthiazole is an attractant.

label: forward point velocity decreased
description: Animals exhibit decreased velocity of forward translocation of any point along the animal's track from that observed for control animals.

label: pathogen induced cell death increased
description: Animals exhibit an increase in the extent of activation of programmed cell death by exposure to a pathogen or pathogenic cue, compared to control.

label: pentanol chemotaxis variant
description: Any variation in the directed movement of a worm in response to a specific concentration gradient of pentanol. In C. elegans, at specific concentrations, pentanol is an attractant.

label: large cytoplasmic granules early emb
description: Abnormally large granules are observed in the cytoplasm of P0.

label: excessive blebbing early emb
description: Excessive shaking and movements are seen in the cell membrane or cytoplasm of one-cell or two-cell embryos.

label: cytoplasmic dynamics defective early emb
description: Cytoplasmic movements are atypical.

label: trimethylthiazole chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute characteristic response to trimethylthiazole compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of trimethylthiazole.

label: butanone chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute characteristic response to butanone compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of butanone.

label: sodium chloride chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute characteristic response to sodium chloride compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards attractive concentrations of sodium chloride.

label: multiple cytoplasmic cavities early emb
description: Multiple vesicles, vacuoles, or cavities are seen during early embryogenesis.

label: hexanol chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute characteristic response to hexanol compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of hexanol.

label: pentanol chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute characteristic response to pentanol compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of pentanol.

label: acetone chemotaxis defective
description: Failure to execute characteristic response to acetone compared to control. In C. elegans, animals move towards typically attractive concentrations of acetone.

label: larval defecation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the elimination of fecal matter during the larval stage compared to control animals.

label: thermotolerance reduced
description: Animals are not able to survive at temperatures above standard cultivation temperatures to the same extent as control animals.

label: premature spermatocyte germ cell differentiation
description: Unspecialized male germ cells (spermatocytes) prematurely acquire the specialized properties of functional sperm.

label: protrusion at vulval region
description: Large protrusion at the normal position of the vulva, as seen in C. elegans lin-12 null animals.

label: organism high sodium chloride hypersensitive
description: Animals respond to sodium chloride at a lower concentration or a shorter exposure compared to control animals. In C. elegans, this is often assayed through generation time and progeny number.

label: nose twisted
description: The extreme anterior part of the body appears distorted, usually due to uncharacteristic winding.

label: no rectum
description: Animals lack the passage connecting the posterior intestine to the rectal valve.

label: magnesium chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to magnesium. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards magnesium.

label: potassium chemotaxis defective
description: Animals fail to exhibit the same taxis behavior as control animals in response to potassium. In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure of the animals to move towards potassium.

label: variable cell division timing
description: Animals exhibit larger variations in cell division timing events than in controls.

label: corpse engulfment initiation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in recognition of cell corpses and initiation of corpse engulfment, compared to controls.

label: inactive phase long
description: Animals display uncharacteristically long periods during which they do not lay eggs compared to control, usually based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events. In C. elegans, long inactive phases can be observed in HSN-ablated and serotonin-deficient animals.

label: inactive phase variant
description: The period during which the animal is less likely to lay eggs is not typical compared with control animals, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: phagosome sealing defective
description: The closure of a phagosome does not occur and it remains connected with the plasma membrane, leaving the lumen open to the outside.  Complete closure usually occurs once an apoptotic cell has been surrounded by an engulfing cell.

label: egg laying phases variant
description: Fluctuation pattern between inactive, active, and egg-laying states is atypical, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events compared to control.

label: late paralysis arrested elongation two fold
description: In C. elegans, movement and elongation stop nearly simultaneously soon after the twofold stage of elongation. However, mutant embryos twitch at the one-and-a-half-fold stage of elongation, like control animals, and move as well as control animals at the two- fold stage.

label: age dependent somatic depletion of fat
description: A depletion of somatic, but not germline, lipid stores are observed near the end of the reproductive period.

label: AWA odorant chemotaxis defective
description: In C. elegans, this is characterized by the failure to move towards typically attractive volatile organic molecules sensed by the AWA compared to control.

label: neurotransmitter response variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in their response to a specific neurotransmitter compared to that observed in control animals.

label: egg laying serotonin resistant
description: Animals are not induced to lay eggs in reponse to exogenous serotonin. Serotonin stimulates egg-laying in C. elegans.

label: starved L1 larvae aggregation variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in the aggregation behavior of starved L1 larvae, compared to controls.

label: active phase variant
description: The active phase of egg-laying, the period during which animals are more likely to display multiple egg-laying events, is atypical compared with control animals, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: tumor prolapse frequency increased
description: Animals with a tumorous germline exhibit an increased frequency of the presence of a tumor prolapse, a protrusion of tumor cells from the vulva, compared to control.

label: tumor prolapse frequency decreased
description: Animals with a tumorous germline exhibit a decreased frequency of the presence of a tumor prolapse, a protrusion of tumor cells from the vulva, compared to control.

label: fewer egg laying events during active
description: Fewer egg-laying events occur within the active phase of egg laying, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events, compared to control.

label: increased egg laying events during active
description: More eggs are laid during the active phase compared with control animals, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: active phase switch defective
description: Activation of the active phase of egg laying is defective, leading to an abnormally long inactive phase, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: inactive phase short
description: The period during which a worm usually does not lay eggs is short compared with control animals, based on the analysis of the distribution of the log intervals of egg-laying events.

label: vulval muscle physiology variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in any physical or chemical process required for cells as a collective unit of the vulva muscle system to carry out their normal functions or activities or be able to perceive and respond to stimuli, compared to control animals.

label: vulval muscle unresponsive to serotonin
description: The vulval muscle does not respond to serotonin in the same manner as control animals. This phenotype is often assayed by imaging of calcium transients in response to serotonin.

label: vulval muscle homeostasis metabolism variant
description: Variations in the chemical reactions and pathways involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium within the vulval muscles compared to control.

label: egg laying response to food variant
description: Animals exhibit variations in egg-laying behavior in response to food compared to control. In C. elegans, well-fed animals lay more eggs compared with starved animals.

label: chromosome segregation variant karyomeres early emb
description: Karyomeres in AB or P1 often accompanied by weak/thin wobbly spindle.
